title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions and drain. Meanwhile mix meat sauce and tomato sauce in a medium-sized bowl. In another bowl, mix Ricotta cheese, egg, onion, parsley, salt and pepper.
In each of 2 (11 x 7-inch) baking dishes, spread 1/2 cup tomato sauce mixture.
Top with a layer of noodles.
Spread each with 1/4 of Ricotta mixture and sprinkle with 1/4 of the Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
Spoon on 1 1/2 cups tomato sauce mixture.
Repeat layers, ending with a final layer of noodles and topping with remaining tomato sauce mixture.
Dishes now may be wrapped and frozen.
Thaw before baking.

title: lemon ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients together well in electric mixer.
Pour into container of a hand-turned or electric freezer and freeze according to manufacturer's directions.
Let ripen for a while. Makes 1 gallon.

title: cranberry-orange bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda. Stir in cranberries, walnuts and orange peel.
Combine egg, orange juice and salad oil.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just to moisten.
Bake in greased 9 1/2 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan in 350° oven for 50 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan and cool.

title: faye's cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl; chill overnight in refrigerator. Form into ball and roll in 1 cup finely chopped pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: tabitha's favorite pecan pralines
directions: In large heavy saucepan, combine sugar, soda, buttermilk and salt.
Cook over high heat 5 minutes, stirring often.
Scrape bottom of pan.
Add butter and pecans and continue cooking another 5 minutes to soft-ball stage.
Remove.
Add vanilla.
Cool.
Beat until creamy.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Mix with all other ingredients except cheese and crackers.
Put cheese and crackers over top and bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: nassi
directions: Four hours before preparing this, pepper and salt chicken. Marinate in soy sauce.
This can also be done the night before. Cook enough rice for your family according to the package.
Brown the chicken until done.
Add to rice.
Add slightly cooked, sliced celery and fried eggs.
Mix all together.
Add curry until rice is yellow looking.
Serve hot.
Great with Peanut Butter Sauce.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: In saucepan, cook sliced squash (unpeeled) and chopped onions in boiling water 5 minutes; drain.
Combine soup, sour cream, stir in carrots, fold in zucchini and onions.
Combine stuffing mix (dry) with butter or margarine.
Spread 1/2 stuffing mix on bottom of casserole.
Spoon vegetable mixture on top.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing over top.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix well. Refrigerate until congealed.

title: lemon sesame dressing
directions: Whisk together.
Stir in cooled sesame seed.
Pour over steamed vegetables or salads.
Refrigerate.

title: broken glass torte
directions: Mix each jello with 3/4 cup hot and 3/4 cup cold water.
Put in separate containers the night before.
Soften unflavored gelatin into 1/4 cup cold water.
Add 1/2 cup sugar to each carton of whipping cream as beating; add vanilla to whipping cream as beating (beat until stiff).
After gelatin is softened, dissolve in 1 cup hot pineapple juice, slowly put into whipping cream.
Then cut jello in cubes.
Fold into whipping cream.

title: crab and shrimp casserole
directions: Saute onions, mushrooms and garlic in large pan in melted butter until tender.
Do not brown.
Combine with all remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture into a 3-quart baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.
Can make ahead and refrigerate.
Bake approximately 1 hour from refrigerator.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cookies from a cake mix
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine dry cake mix, oil and eggs in a bowl; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Cool for 1 minute.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: chili dip - meets the four f's (fine finger football food)
directions: Saute pepper and onion in butter.
Add ground round and brown; drain fat.
Add taco seasoning and water (per package directions); simmer 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together the butter and peanut butter.
Beat in white sugar and brown sugar.
Stir in egg, vanilla, baking soda and flour.
Arrange by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Press flat with a floured spoon or mark with a fork.
Bake until firm, 10 minutes, at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together in mixing bowl.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Can be made the day before and refrigerated.
Before baking, sprinkle about 1/2 package Pepperidge Farm cornbread stuffing mix on top.
Cover well with stuffing mix but do not stack it.
Bake uncovered for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Cook chicken pieces in enough water to cover until tender. Set aside to cool; discard skin, remove bones and cut into pieces. Mix dressing with 1/2 stick melted butter.
Layer 1/2 of the dressing in a casserole dish.
Mix mushroom soup with 1 cup chicken broth (or water).
Layer chopped chicken pieces over the dressing in casserole.
Mix cream of celery soup with 1 cup chicken broth (or water).
Pour over chicken.
Top with rest of Stove Top Dressing.

title: beans and franks
directions: Open pork and beans.
Add catsup, brown sugar and turkey franks (cut into bite size pieces).
Bake at 300° until bubbly, or cook in skillet on top of stove or "slap" in the microwave.

title: dr. zan's geologo-chili
directions: *May be reduced or eliminated by the terminally wimpy.

title: vinaigrette dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients, pour into a jar with tight fitting lid. Shake well before serving. Chill and serve over salad. The combination of water and wine vinegar can be changed to your own taste. Also, can use 1 pkg. sweetener, according to your own taste. This is fat free, sugar free and good! It makes the lettuce or other salad greens so crispy and tasteful.

title: cornmeal rolls
directions: Add milk to corn meal slowly.
Cook until thick, remove from heat.
Add sugar, margarine, and salt.
Let cool.
Dissolve yeast in water and let stand 10 minutes.
Add yeast to beaten egg and corn meal.
Add flour and knead, will be very soft.
Let rise once.
Roll out 3/4 inch thick and cut with cookie cutter and let rise.
Use for hamburger buns or rolls.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: beef chowder
directions: Brown beef.
Remove from pan.
Saute onion, celery, and green pepper until tender.
Drain pan drippings and add rest of ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour and serve.

title: wiener schnitzel
directions: Cut veal into 6 serving-size pieces.
Coat cutlets with a mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Dip into a blend of egg and milk.
Coat with bread crumbs.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes to "seal" coating.
Melt the butter in a large skillet.
Add the cutlets. Cook over medium heat until browned and tender, about 20 minutes on each side.
Remove cutlets to a warm serving platter.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and top each portion with fried egg.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pecan corn muffins
directions: Line muffin tins with paper bake cup.
In bowl, stir together flour, corn meal, ground pecans, sugar, baking powder and baking soda.
Make a well in middle.
In smaller bowl, mix eggs, milk and melted oleo.
Add to flour mixture and stir just until moist. (Batter should be lumpy.) Gently fold in chopped pecans.
Fill cups 3/4 full.
Bake in 375° oven for 18 to 20 minutes.
Remove and serve warm.

title: italian corn crusted baked fish
directions: Mix tomato, olives, garlic and olive oil in bottom of a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Separate fish fillets and cut smaller, if they are large.
Dip each in cornmeal seasoned with the salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes or until baked crusty.
Serve Parmesan cheese on top.
Makes 4 servings.

title: edible aquarium
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Combine cold water and ice cubes to make 1 1/4 cups ice and water.
Add to gelatin, stirring until slightly thickened.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Pour gelatin into 4 dessert dishes.
Place gummy fish in gelatin.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: chicken marsala(serves 4)
directions: Flour chicken lightly.
Heat 2 tablespoons of butter in a large skillet.
Saute 3 to 4 minutes on each side.
Add salt and pepper. Lightly brown chicken, adding more butter if needed.
Remove chicken.
Add 1 tablespoon butter.
Saute mushrooms and garlic for 3 minutes.
Add wine and broth.
Bring to boil.
Return chicken to pan.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add parsley.

title: wheat muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour in muffin tins.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in a 425° oven.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Boil green bell pepper, purple onion and zucchini until tender.
Mix sour cream and cream of chicken soup.
Melt butter into bread crumbs.
Line bottom of casserole dish with 1/2 breading and soup (after greasing), then pour on mixed vegetables. Top with remainder of breading and soup mix.
Place Parmesan cheese on top during last 10 minutes of baking.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked pineapple casserole
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and egg to blend well, then stir with bread and pineapple.
Bake in greased casserole (I put butter in the casserole pan or Easy Off the pan) at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: In a greased
baking pan place chicken; sprinkle with salt & pepper.
Place sauerkraut over chicken and top with swiss cheese. Pour dressing evenly over cheese, cover with foil and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325° or until fork can be inserted in chicken with ease.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Make batter using 1/2 cup sugar, 1 cup flour and 3/4 cup milk. Mix by hand; it will be lumpy.
Melt butter in pan you will be making cobbler in.
Spread butter evenly over bottom.
Pour batter in pan and spread evenly, then add fruit and liquid from fruit. Use remaining sugar and sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° until top is golden brown, about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: virginia apple nut pie(cake)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in greased pie pan.
Dot with 2 tablespoons margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Serve hot or cold.

title: banana date bread(microwave recipe)
directions: In large glass mixing bowl, melt butter on High (maximum power) 1 1/2 minutes.
With electric mixer, gradually beat in all remaining ingredients except dates.
When smooth, stir in dates. Grease a 2-quart glass casserole and place a straight sided glass in center (or use a micro-proof ring mold).
Pour batter around glass.
Cook on 70 (Roast) 15 minutes or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Rotate dish if bread seems to be rising unevenly.
Let stand 10 minutes before twisting glass to remove and inverting dish on cooling rack.
Cool before slicing. Makes 8 to 10 servings.
Total cooking time:
16 1/2 minutes.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Prepare cornbread according to package directions.
Cool. Crumble cornbread into large container.
Add onion, celery, pepper and tomatoes to cornbread.
Combine sour cream and mayonnaise. Add to cornbread mixture and stir well.
Chill.
Yields 12 servings.

title: southwestern casserole
directions: Brown ground beef until crumbly and no longer pink; drain. Combine beef, onion, chiles, sauce and soups.
Cut tortillas into halves or fourths; layer with ground beef mixture and cheese in a 9-inch by 13-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese chilies cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Whisk together eggs, yogurt and oleo in a medium bowl. Add dry ingredients and mix until just well blended. Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased 10-inch heavy skillet and bake 40 minutes.

title: bean casserole
directions: Saute ground beef and onions in skillet.
Drain off fat.
Mix well other ingredients, except bouillon.
Put in casserole dish. Pour bouillon over all and bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Gradually add milk. Mix in corn and margarine.
Beat egg yolks a little and stir in mixture.
Beat egg whites until forms soft peaks.
Pour into mixture, then pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: Cut the chicken breasts into 3/4 to 1-inch chunks, removing and discarding any tough tendons as you go along.
Toss the chicken, celery and apples together in a large bowl.
Place the raisins and wine in a small saucepan.
Heat to boiling over medium-high heat.

Reduce the heat and simmer for 3 to 4 minutes. Add the raisins and liquid to the chicken and toss to combine. Add the lime juice, ginger and curry powder and toss again. Bind the salad with the mayonnaise and season to taste with salt. Transfer the salad to a serving bowl and garnish with the apple slices. Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mamma ellard's pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add syrup, butter and eggs.
Mix all together and add pecans, vanilla or rum extract and salt.
Preheat oven to 400° and cook for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pineapple or coconut pie
directions: Cream sugar and flour.
Then add eggs with a little milk.
Add to scalded milk and stir until thick.
Add drained pineapple or coconut.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with egg whites or Cool Whip.

title: coffee cake
directions: Butter Bundt pan and sprinkle nuts in.
Cut rolls in 2 pieces. Place in pan.
Sprinkle dry pudding mix over rolls.
Melt margarine and sugar and pour over rolls.
Let set out overnight, covered with Saran Wrap.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes and remove from pan.

title: beef and cheese ball
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.
Shape into two balls. Roll in pecans.

title: fried chicken
directions: Cut up fryer.
Rinse in cold water; soak in cold salt water over night.

title: cracker dressing
directions: Break up crackers into a large bowl; add celery, onions, parsley, eggs, salt and pepper.
Set aside 1/4 cup broth to mix in cornstarch.
Heat chicken broth, stir in cornstarch mix; keep stirring until mixture thickens and has the consistency of gravy. Keep hot.
Just before serving, pour small amounts over crackers; toss to moisten.
Do not have too wet.

title: old-fashioned chocolate gravy
directions: In a skillet, mix sugar, cocoa, flour and just enough water to make a thick paste.
Add the milk and boil until thickened.
Serve over hot biscuits with butter.

title: chicken enchiladas with sour cream
directions: Boil chicken breast, debone and reserve 1 cup broth.
Steam or microwave 18 corn tortillas until soft.
Fill each with a mixture of boiled chicken, shredded cheese and minced onion.
Roll and lay in a 9 x 12-inch well-greased baking dish.
Blend 1 can green chilies, chicken soup, broth and milk in blender.
Pour over enchiladas.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with jalapenos and sour cream.
Serves 6.

title: meat ball soup
directions: Mix ground beef lightly with parsley, salt, water and steak sauce in a bowl; shape into 36 small balls.
Brown in butter or margarine in a kettle; remove and set aside for next step; pour off drippings.
Heat 6 cups water to boiling; stir in soup mix, celery and rice.
Cover.
Cook 15 minutes; stir in carrots and meat balls.
Cook 5 minutes longer or until rice is tender. Ladle into soup bowls; garnish with parsley sprigs.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat egg whites separate.
Mix in other ingredients one at a time.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes in 450 degrees in preheated oven.
Then reduce oven to 325 degrees til pie cuts clean with knife (about 20 to 30 minutes).

title: instant sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix cranberry sauce, Russian dressing and onion soup mix together.
Place chicken pieces in baking dish and cover with this mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, covered, and for 30 minutes, uncovered, or bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Fry onion and carrots until onion is tender.
Add hamburger; season with garlic, chicken stock, salt and pepper to taste.
In separate pan, boil potatoes.
Add milk and butter to mash, stiff not creamy.
Drain fat from meat mixture; add water to cover.
Cook until carrots are tender.
Sprinkle with Tones brown gravy. Thicken with McCormick brown gravy and flour.
Layer in baking dish.
Top with potatoes.
Ruffle surface with fork.
Top with grated cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° until brown. Keep everything from edge of pan.
This is a real Australian dish.

title: quick hoppin john(6 servings)
directions: Heat water, onion, salt, Tabasco and rice to boiling.
Cover and cook 20 to 25 minutes (use timer).
Stir in remainder of ingredients and let stand 10 minutes.
Eat immediately.

title: german potato soup
directions: In Dutch oven, cook potatoes, bay leaves, celery and whole onion until potatoes are soft.
Drain and take onion and bay leaves out.
Mash potatoes with hand masher.
Add oleo and eggs; stir with masher.

title: no bake fudge cookies
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter.
When melted, add coconut.
Put with spoon on wax paper or cookie sheet to cool.

title: reese balls
directions: Mix milk, sugar, peanut butter and margarine.
Shape into balls and place onto wax paper.
Melt wax and chocolate chips in double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate and place on wax paper. Chill balls in refrigerator.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, adding eggs, one at a time.
In separate bowl, blend all remaining ingredients together and sift into pumpkin mixture.
Blend well.
Pour into 2 small or 1 large greased loaf pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix together, adding shrimp last.
Serve on your favorite cracker.

title: mexican nacho dip
directions: In a 7 x 12-inch pan, spread cream cheese.
Spread chili on top.
Top with chilies and green pepper. Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: shrimp and fried rice(by alice lee renfrow, a friend)
directions: Bring chicken broth to a boil and add rice.
Cook rice very dry.
Put rice aside to cool.
In large skillet, add your peanut oil and let it heat very slowly.
Scramble eggs well, then add rice and mix thoroughly; add cooked shrimp and soy sauce until desired color has been made.
Just before serving, heat this mixture for about ten minutes before adding the crisp spring onions.

title: pecan pies
directions: Beat eggs until mixed (not fluffy).
Add brown sugar, Karo, salt, cream, and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shells and dot with butter.
Spread chopped pecans on top; bake at 350 for about 45 minutes or until center is firm.
(It takes an hour in my oven)
(cover the crust with foil the last 15 minutes so it doesn't get too brown.)

title: ozark pudding(serves 4)
directions: Mix egg and sugar until very smooth.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into egg mixture.
Add nuts and chopped apples.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve with whipping cream.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Roll or drop by teaspoon.
Press down with fork.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: pimento and cheese
directions: Put all in blender and mix well.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni in rapidly boiling salted water and cook until tender.
Chill.
Mix remaining ingredients with French dressing and mayonnaise.
Chill thoroughly.

title: spinach borek
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Use about 1 1/2 pounds of cheese.
You may use any combination or proportion as long as the total amount is about the 1 1/2 pounds.
Do not open the filo package until butter is melted and filling prepared.
Place a damp, well wrung out towel over the filo that you are about to use.
Have eggs and cheese at room temperature.
Put eggs, cheese, dill and cayenne in blender and mix well.
Put mixture into bowl and add spinach and nuts. Stir and blend.

Using a 2-inch wide paint brush dipped in melted butter, butter 8 or 10 sheets of filo dough, 1 at a time and place 1 on top of another in a large buttered 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan. Spread filling evenly over these sheets.
Butter 8 or 10 more filo sheets.
Place them on top of the filling.
Cut borek into serving size pieces.
If borek is difficult to cut, put pan into refrigerator for an hour; it will then be much easier to cut.
It can also be frozen at this point and baked later.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350° or until top is nicely browned.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Butter a square glass 2-quart 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Peel potatoes and cut crosswise in thin slices.
Arrange overlapping slices in rows, in prepared baking dish, making sure top is flat. If not they may get brown.
Pour butter over potatoes and sprinkle with salt.
Bake in a preheated 500° oven until potatoes are tender when tested with a fork and top and bottom layers are slightly crisp, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with Swiss and Parmesan cheese.
Return to 500° oven until cheese is melted, about 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Add soda to peeled apples and set aside.
Beat oil and sugar until well mixed.
Add eggs one at a time and beat.
Add flavoring.
Add flour 1/2 cup at a time.
Beat well.
Add nuts to apples and stir into batter.
Bake in tube pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Combine pineapple, flour and sugar.
Boil for 2 minutes, or until liquid is clear.
Bake 2 pie shells according to directions. Slice bananas; put in bottom of pie shells.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup nuts in each shell and 1/2 of the pineapple mixture.
Put 1/3 cup coconut in each shell.
Spread with Cool Whip; sprinkle remaining coconut (which has been toasted) on top.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: *Broccoli, green beans, green peppers and others of your choice can be used.

title: chop suey
directions: Bring meat to boil and pour off water.
Add vegetables and enough water to cover meat and vegetables.
Cook 1 hour.
Add molasses, sugar, salt, pepper and soy sauce.
Cook for another 1 1/2 hours.
Ten minutes before it is done, add bean sprouts.
When finished, thicken with cornstarch and water.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: tasty taco pie
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce and seasoning mix; simmer 5 minutes.
Press dough onto bottom and sides of ungreased 12-inch pizza pan, pressing edges together to form seal.
Prick bottom and sides with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until deep golden brown.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll into medium sized balls.
Place into ungreased pan.
Press down in a crisscross pattern on top with fork, on the top of cookies.
Place into an oven at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: crispy potato wedges
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Place potatoes in a large bowl.
Add cold water to cover.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Spray a nonstick baking sheet with vegetable cooking spray.
Set aside.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in refrigerator.

title: beef italiano
directions: Brown beef, peppers and onions in large skillet.
Add tomatoes, broth and seasonings.
Bring to a full boil, breaking up tomatoes with edge of spoon.
Stir in rice.
Cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.

title: tuna macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
In bowl, blend together soup, milk, mayonnaise and mustard.
Stir in cheese, tuna and pimento.
Gently fold in macaroni.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Combine crumbs, butter and paprika. Sprinkle atop casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cook meat and onion; drain fat.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper. Add liquid and simmer for 30 minutes in covered skillet.
Cut green peppers in half.
Remove the seeds and cook in boiling water for 3 minutes.
Drain off water, fill pepper halves with mixture and arrange in greased baking dish.
Add 1/4 cup hot water in bottom of baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Two pepper halves per serving.
Yield:
4 servings.
Carbohydrate 12 g, protein 17 g, fat 12 g, calories 224.
One serving = 2 medium fat exchange, 2 vegetable exchange.

title: dorothy's pecan pies
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Cook at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Saute rice in butter in large skillet.
Add mushrooms and onion.
Cook until tender; add consomme and water.
Stir well in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: green bean supreme
directions: Cook beans; drain.
Fold soup into beans, adding salt, pepper and garlic, as desired.
Place in greased casserole.
Sprinkle onion rings over top.
Heat until bubbling in slow oven.

title: pig-picking cake
directions: In a blender, mix oil, eggs, and mandarin oranges.
Blend until oranges are pureed.
Using a mixer, combine the cake mix and the puree.
Beat until smooth.
Spread evenly in a greased and floured 9 x 14 inch cake pan.
Bake at 325 degrees for 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool on a rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
Cut cake into 2 layers.
Spread one-third of the frosting on bottom layer. Top with remaining layer of cake and frost top and sides.
Top with coconut.
(This is called "Pig Picking" cake because it is so good that you will tend to "pig-out" on it.)

title: bo-bo's peanut butter fudge
directions: Grease large platter with butter.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add cream.
Cook on high heat until boiling.
Reduce heat to medium; stir constantly.
Have 2 small bowls of ice water on the stove. Test a few drops of mixture; do this until it forms a ball. Remove from heat; add peanut butter.
Beat on high speed until smooth and creamy.
Pour on greased platter.
Spread with knife. Let cool, then eat.

title: faye's zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour mixture into 2 loaf pans that have been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350 degrees for 50 to 55 minutes.
Test with cake tester or knife until no batter is observed on the tester.

title: cherry and cream cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare and bake cake as directed on package.
Cool cake completely.
Mix sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Spread over cake.
Spoon pie filling over sour cream mixture.
Store cake in refrigerator.

title: southern greens and ham hocks
directions: Need one large pot (6 or 8-quart).
Boil ham hocks for 1 hour. Clean all greens and remove stems.
Add all greens and season to taste after 1 hour.
Boil for another 2 hours.
Add water if needed.
Done when ham hocks are tender and have fallen off bone. Makes 2 to 4 servings.
Great with cornbread.

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve jello and water together, then pour in pineapple juice, nuts and cottage cheese.
Mix. Set in refrigerator until firm.
Serve with Marshmallow Topping.

title: rainbow muffins
directions: Mix biscuit mix and sugar; add egg and milk.
Mix until just blended.
Gently stir in fruit cocktail.
Spoon into greased or lined muffin pans.
Mix 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Sprinkle over tops.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Serves 9.

title: stuffed artichokes(with mashed potatoes and browned garlic)
directions: Working with one artichoke at a time, cut off stem to the base. Remove bottom leaves and tough outer leaves, leaving tender heart and bottom; trim about 2-inches from the top of artichoke.
Steam artichokes, covered, 20 minutes; cool to room temperature.
Gently spread leaves; remove fuzzy thistle from bottom with a spoon. Preheat oven to 375.

title: pizzazz tomato-topped fish
directions: Thaw fish if frozen.
In a large skillet, cook bacon until crisp, turning often.
Remove bacon; drain on paper towels.
Add onion to drippings in skillet.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes or until tender; drain.
Stir in tomato.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 1 to 2 minutes or until heated through.
Crumble bacon and stir into tomato mixture.

title: french onion pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheet to 325°.
Reserve 1/2 cup of the onions.
Sprinkle remaining onions on bottom of pie shell. Sprinkle cheese over onions.
Combine eggs, milk and seasonings. Pour over cheese.
Bake on preheated cookie sheet for 45 minutes. Sprinkle reserved onions around edge of pie.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes more (or until a knife inserted in pie center comes out clean). Let stand before serving.
Serves 6.

title: crunchy granola
directions: In one bowl combine oats, coconut, nuts and wheat germ.
In another bowl combine brown sugar, margarine and honey.
Mix the two together.
Press firmly into well-greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Get out of pan immediately and spread out on a piece of waxed paper.
Cool.

title: drop cheese biscuits
directions: Measure and place in a sifter over the mixing bowl, flour, baking powder and salt.
Sift the flour mixture into a bowl.
Cut in the shortening with a pastry blender or using two knives until flour mixture looks like coarse crumbs.
Add the grated cheese and milk.
Stir with a fork until flour mixture leaves the side of the bowl.

title: ooey-gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix and melted butter with one egg.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 13 pan which has been sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over cake mix.
Mix cream cheese, two eggs, and powdered sugar until smooth.
Pour over chocolate chips.
Top with chopped pecans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35-40 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Place pineapple and juice in oblong Pyrex dish.
Spread cake mix on top; sprinkle pecans over the mix.
Spoon melted oleo over top.
Last, sprinkle coconut over top.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.
Put whipped cream on top after it has completely cooled.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Drain clams and reserve juice.
Melt the butter in a large saucepan.
Saute the onions for 10 minutes, stirring frequently. Add the bottled clam juice and reserved clam juice, water, potatoes and pepper.
Cover and cook over low heat for 25 minutes. Add clams and cook 5 more minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs in bowl.
Add sugar, corn, salt, pepper, milk and sliced pieces of margarine.
Stir.
Bake at 350° to 375° until firm and starting to brown.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal.
Let stand at room temperature for 10 minutes.
Add brown and white sugar and butter. Stir until butter melts.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and cocoa.
Add flour to sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Add about half the chips.
Pour batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle walnuts and remaining chocolate chips on top.
Bake in preheated oven to 350° about 40 minutes.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl, stir eggs, corn syrup, sugar, chocolate chips, butter and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans. Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
Serves 8.

title: corn bread surprise
directions: Prepare corn bread according to directions.
Add other ingredients.
Mix together.
Baked in a 350° oven until brown; slice.
Serve hot with your favorite gravy.
Wonderful with or instead of stuffing or potatoes.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Cook margarine, cocoa, sugar and milk until bubbles form around side.
Remove from heat and add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop on wax paper; cool and serve.

title: sausage strata
directions: Space 6 slices bread, buttered side down, in a 3-quart baking dish.
Spread 1/2 of cheese and sausage over bread.
Add eggs and milk, which have been beaten together.
Add remaining 6 slices of bread and rest of sausage and cheese.
Press gently so bread will absorb liquid.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
In the morning, bake for 1 hour at 325°.
May be served with mushrooms.

title: six layer cookies
directions: Add each in order in layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares while still warm.
Remove from pan when cool.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix and add 2 cups raw zucchini, grated.
(Add 1 cup nuts, if desired.)
Bake at 325° for about 55 to 60 minutes.

title: mexitalian lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine salsa, chili, mushrooms, Parmesan cheese and Italian seasoning.
In small bowl, combine cottage cheese and parsley flakes.
In 9-inch baking dish, coated with cooking spray, layer 3 noodles, 1/2 cup cottage cheese, 1/3 of chili mixture and 1/3 of Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat to make 3 layers.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Put lemon juice over bananas.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Put into container and freeze overnight.

title: cool whip pie
directions: Put lemon juice in the milk and stir well.
Add Cool Whip, pineapple and nuts.
If not thick enough, add more lemon juice. Put into shells and chill.

title: low-fat brownies
directions: Over very low heat, melt chocolate.
Cool slightly.
In blender or food processor, puree all ingredients, except chocolate and powdered sugar until smooth.
Add melted chocolate.
Blend well.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan, sprayed with Pam.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until just set at 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut into 16 squares.

title: coconut pies
directions: In a large bowl, mix together well the eggs, sugar, flour, milk, margarine, flavoring, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes two 9-inch pies in aluminum pans.

title: painless corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8-inch square baking dish. Saute onion and pepper in oleo 3 to 5 minutes. Add milk, half and half and rest of ingredients to bowl with eggs.
Pour into baking dish.
Set dish in larger pan, place in oven, pour 1 inch of boiling water in outer pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Remove from water bath and serve.
Yields 6 servings.

title: applesauce salad
directions: Melt cinnamon candies in
1 cup
boiling water and pour over orange Jell-O.
Add
the applesauce, mayonnaise and cream cheese, which have been mixed together.
Let cool until almost thick. Add
nuts and
celery.
Chill
until
firm.
Mold
if desired.

title: nonna zelenda's lasagna
directions: Sauce:
Brown meat.
Saute onions (add peppers or mushrooms if desired), then add 2 jars of Ragu, parsley flakes, salt, pepper, 2 small cans tomato puree and 1 can tomato paste.
Simmer 1/2 hour.

title: green beans tarragon
directions: Cook beans in water with salt and pepper.
Add tarragon the last 20 minutes of cooking time.

title: creamy broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli.
Add cream of mushroom soup, mixing with milk. Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix Bisquick and margarine until crumbly; sprinkle over cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.

title: orange pumpkin custard
directions: Mix rind of orange and lemon with orange juice, pumpkin, sugar, salt and spices.
Beat the eggs until foamy and stir into pumpkin mixture gently.
Pour into 6 custard cups.
Place in pan of hot water and bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes, or until a silver knife inserted in the center of custard comes out clean.
Cool and serve with whipped topping.

title: blueberry dessert(four layer pie)
directions: First Layer:
Melt margarine and mix pecans and flour.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until brown.
Cool completely.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw French fries enough to break apart and mix with ingredients.
Add onion, cheese, soup, sour cream and salt and pepper.
Mix well and place in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle corn flakes on top and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: carrot salad
directions: Combine ingredients and mix lightly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hamburg pie
directions: Mix together the meat, onions, crumbs and 1/2 can sauce.
Pat into oiled pie plate to form a crust for the pie.
Mix rice, cheese, water and 1 1/2 can sof sauce.
Pour into meat "crust". Cover with foil.
Bake 35 minutes.
Uncover.
Bake an additional 15 minutes to brown.

title: red hot sandwich rolls
directions: Combine franks, cheese, scallions, olives, eggs, chili sauce and mayonnaise; mix thoroughly.
Open buns; fill each with about 1/3 cup of frank mixture.
(Bun will close only partially.)
Wrap each bun in heavy-duty or broiler foil, twisting ends tightly. Store in refrigerator until ready for use.
Before serving, place wrapped buns on grill for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: vickie's italian meat loaf
directions: Saute onion; add tomato sauce, paste and whole tomatoes. Season with oregano, sugar, hot sauce and Worcestershire sauce. Cook 30 to 45 minutes.

title: green grape pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Put strips of dough across top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: crazy fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix in same pan cooking in (9 x 12-inch rectangle).
Put all dry ingredients in pan.
Add all wet ingredients.
Stir well.
Bake until springs back in middle to touch, about 20 to 25 minutes.
Best chocolate cake around!

title: pink cloud
directions: In a large bowl, mix pie filling, fruit cocktail and pineapple.
Add milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: owens sausage and spaghetti frittata
directions: In a separate pan, saute crumbled sausage, onion and garlic until sausage is just done.
Heat an ovenproof skillet.
Add olive oil and continue heating until oil is hot.
In a bowl, combine sausage mixture, egg, spaghetti and 1/2 of the cheese; mix thoroughly.
Add meat mixture to skillet and cook until bottom is browned and egg has almost set.
Place olive slices in an attractive pattern on frittata.
Sprinkle remainder of cheese on frittata and broil in oven until top is golden and crusty. Garnish with sliced orange and melon.
Serves two for breakfast or four as a pasta course.

title: generation-to-generation banana pudding
directions: Pour half of one box of wafers into a clean dish towel.
Use a rolling pin to crumble to medium-fine crumbs.
Place in a bowl and add the sugar and butter.
Blend together well.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Day Before:
Drain yogurt to make cheese (see following). Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease an 8-inch pie pan or a 7-inch spring-form pan.
Place yogurt cheese in a medium size bowl.
Add sugar, cornstarch, lemon juice and vanilla.
Mix with wire whisk until well blended.
Stir in egg substitute.
Pour into prepared pan and smooth top with spatula.
Bake until center is set, 20 to 25 minutes for pie pan, 45 to 55 minutes for spring-form.
Chill in fridge.
Serves 16.
Contains 97 calories, 57 mg. sod., 6 gm. protein, 3 gm. fat and 11 gm carb.

title: summer blt spread
directions: Reserve 1 teaspoon bacon for garnish.
Combine remaining bacon, sour cream, mayo and tomatoes in medium bowl.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 3 cups.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix and put in refrigerator.

title: mandi's peanut butter cake
directions: Put egg whites in small bowl.
In large bowl mix butter, peanut butter and brown sugar.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Measure milk and vanilla.
Beat whites with white sugar.
Cream butter and brown sugar, add egg yolks and beat well.
Add liquid and flour and beat until well blended.
Add in beaten egg whites. Pour into two 8-inch pans or one 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pans. In a large bowl with fork, mix first 8 ingredients.
In a medium bowl with fork, beat eggs, pumpkin and salad oil until blended. Stir pumpkin mixture into flour mixture just until flour is moistened. Gently stir in raisins and walnuts.
Spoon batter evenly into loaf pans.
Bake bread 1 hour and 15 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool bread in pans on wire rack 10 minutes; remove bread from pans. Cool on rack. Makes 2 loaves.

title: chicken jambalaya
directions: Fry chicken in oil until brown.
Remove from pot.
Add onions and garlic to fry until brown.
Return chicken to pot.
Add water, salt, red hot and seasoning; simmer until hens are tender.
Add rice; cook rapidly for 5 minutes.
Lower fire, cover and cook for 20 minutes without lifting lid.
Cook until done.
Serves 14.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: In oblong glass dish, mix together rice, soups, chopped vegetables and water.
Arrange chicken pieces on top.
Pour melted butter over chicken and sprinkle with paprika.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Good company dish!

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Melt margarine in large pan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat.
Add cereal. Stir until well coated.

title: fruitcake for the holiday
directions: Mix all ingredients into a large bowl.
Beat eggs well; add butter, milk, brown sugar, vanilla and salt.
Stir until moist. Then add flour and baking powder.
Stir in mixed fruit, nutmeg, ground allspice, cinnamon and all other candied fruits and nuts. Pour into tube pan with heavy wax paper in bottom of pan.
Bake at 275° to 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Decorate cake top with red and green cherries and pecan halves.

title: cranberry, orange and apricot bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bottom only of 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Combine first six ingredients, mixing well; set aside. Beat eggs and oil with fork or wire whisk to blend thoroughly; mix in orange juice, water and orange peel.
Add to dry ingredients, mixing just until moistened.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool completely.
Makes 16 servings.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt and shortening as for pie dough.
Reserve 1 cup crumbs for topping.
Add egg and sour milk to which the soda has been stirred.
Mix and pour into two 8-inch pans. Sprinkle crumbs on top. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash, onion, and butter.
Drain and add soups, sour cream, and salt and pepper.
Crumble cornbread into mixture and bake until brown.

title: cheesy cornbread
directions: Combine
cornmeal and salt;
add remaining ingredients, stir just
until dry ingredients are moistened.	Spoon into a greased 10-inch iron skillet.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or golden brown.

title: corn casserole
directions: Drain whole kernel corn.
Mix all ingredients in big baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done in center.
Top will be golden brown.

title: pudding in a cloud
directions: Or use Jell-O cook and serve pudding and pie filling prepared with milk as directed on package.
Refrigerate 2 hours before assembling dessert.

title: squash pie
directions: Cook squash and drain well. Blend in blender until smooth. Set aside.
Beat eggs slightly.
Combine with other ingredients, including squash.
Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake another 40 to 45 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: homemade dog biscuits
directions: Combine all dry ingredients, except yeast.
In separate bowl, dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
To this add chicken stock. (You can use bouillon, pan drippings or water from cooking vegetables.)
Add liquid to dry ingredients.
Knead mixture for about three minutes.
Dough will be quite stiff.
If too stiff, add extra liquid or an egg.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Roll dough out on floured board to 1/2-inch thick.
Immediately cut into shapes with cookie cutters (I use dog shapes for mine).
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and brush well with a wash of egg and milk.
Place in oven.
After 45 minutes, turn off heat and leave biscuits overnight in oven to get bone hard.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and put into loaf baking dish.
Cook on Medium for 12 to 14 minutes.
Brush top with ketchup.

title: good granola
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients. Add honey, oil and vanilla. Mix well. Spread on a cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes (watch so it doesn't scorch).
Cool on paper towels.
Eat for a snack or with milk for breakfast.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs and butter.
Line 9 x 13-inch baking dish with mixture and set aside.
Mix pudding according to package.
Spread pudding evenly over graham cracker crust.
Cover with sliced bananas.
Then layer pineapple.
Then layer whipped topping.
Refrigerate overnight, it will be firmer. Garnish it with nuts.

title: cranberry-pineapple jello mold
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Let cool.
Add the strained cranberry sauce, crushed pineapple with juice and the chopped walnuts.
Mix all together.
Place in large, lightly greased jello mold pan.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add melted oleo, egg yolks, milk and vanilla.
Pour into deep-dish unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: doughnut muffins
directions: Using a fork, beat egg in mixing bowl.
Add oil and milk; continue beating with fork.
Sift flour; measure and sift with sugar, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Add to mixture and stir well with a fork very lightly, just to hold together.
Turn into muffin tins, well-greased.
Sprinkle each muffin with mixture of sugar and cinnamon and put a dot of butter or margarine on top of each.
Bake in a 400° oven for about 15 to 20 minutes (check at 15).

title: golden penny salad
directions: Slice, cook and drain carrots.
Add green pepper and onion. Combine rest of ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 days.
Keeps a long time.

title: turtles
directions: Melt caramels, condensed milk and butter.
Add nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet and freeze.
Melt 3/4 pound chocolate and dip frozen balls in chocolate.
Let set.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain.
Arrange in flat casserole; cover with tomatoes, Swiss cheese and sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: you'd swear it had meat
directions: Mix all together well. Spread on finger sandwich bread.

title: shrimp or crab dip
directions: Soften cream cheese; blend with mayonnaise.
Heat soup.
Add gelatine that has been dissolved in water.
Cool slightly.
Add onions, celery and pepper to cream cheese and mayonnaise; blend with soup mixture.
Add shrimp or crabmeat.
Pour into mold and chill overnight.

title: crab imperial
directions: Saute green pepper in butter for 2 minutes.
Remove pan from heat.
Add pimento, salt, Worcestershire sauce and salad dressing mix thoroughly.
Add crabmeat; put in casserole.
Cover contents with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake uncovered for 20 minutes in 400° oven.

title: potatoes supreme
directions: Cook potatoes in small amount of salted water until tender. Drain and refrigerate overnight (covered).
Grate cold potatoes coarsely.
Mix in remaining ingredients and bake in a shallow pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut cookie roll into 1/4 inch slices and cover round ungreased pizza pan. Bake per directions or until light brown on top. Mix cream cheese and sugar. Cool crust, then cover with cream cheese mixture, using all of the cheese. Add the fruit in layers, topping with the fruit that matches the glaze. Spread glaze over fruit. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: egg noodles
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add water, salt and pepper.
Gradually add flour until stiff.
Roll out on floured surface.
Cut and drop into broth.
Cook until tender.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix all together; fill muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Mix the cake mix and jello in a large bowl.
Add eggs and sour cream; hand mix until blended well.
Add the chocolate chips and mix.
Spoon the mixture in a Bundt pan that has been sprayed with Baker's Joy.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Beat until creamy sugar, vanilla, cream cheese and Cool Whip. Mix well.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Top with cherries, then extra Cool Whip and nuts, if desired.
Refrigerate.

title: aunt clara's sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco.
Add sugar.
Cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well after each.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed ingredients, alternating with sour cream and milk.
Add extracts, mixing well.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Use large steeple pan that is sprayed with Baker's Secret.

title: cranberry mold salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in mold. Cranberries have to be put through a grinder, not a blender.

title: peach marshmallow icebox cake
directions: Soak gelatine in 1/4 cup cold water for 5 minutes.
Cream together butter and sugar; add egg yolks.
Cook over low heat until thoroughly thickened.
Remove from heat and add soaked gelatin.
When slightly cooled, add marshmallow pieces.
Blend slightly and cool.
Fold in peaches and egg whites.
In a mold, alternate layers of cookie crumbs and peach filling, beginning with cookie crumbs and ending with cookie crumbs.
Chill until set.
Serve with or without whipped cream.

title: poor man's chop suey
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter.
Combine the first 3 ingredients together and mix with the soup, rice and water.
Pour into casserole dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in baking dish, seasoning with salt and pepper. Cover tightly and boil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: brandied fruit pork chops
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Cook pork chops in oil over medium heat until lightly browned.
Turn and cook until browned well and meat is no longer pink.
Season with salt and pepper.
Remove chops and keep warm, drain drippings.
Combine peaches, pineapple, marmalade and brandy in skillet.
Cook and stir until heated. Spoon over chops.
Top with orange and lime slices and cherries.

title: coconut caramel pie
directions: Lightly brown coconut and pecans in margarine.
Let cool.
Mix condensed milk and cream cheese together.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour 1/4 of mixture in each pie shell.
Drizzle with caramel. Sprinkle with coconut pecans.
Repeat process.
Put pies in freezer.

title: squash patties
directions: Combine squash, onion, sugar, salt and pepper in a medium bowl.
Cover and let stand 30 minutes. Drain thoroughly.
Add flour and eggs.
Stir well.
Melt margarine in a large skillet over medium heat. Drop squash mixture by tablespoon into hot margarine. Cook until golden brown, turning once.

title: russian spice tea
directions: Place 3 or 4 teaspoons (or to taste) of mix per serving in a cup of boiling water to make a delicious spicy tea.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream sugars, butter and eggs.
Mix in a little flour at a time.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Add carrots and walnuts last. Bake in greased, floured pan at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve plain or add your favorite frosting.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill until firm (this step is optional, makes rolling easier).
Roll into walnut size balls. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 48 to 50.

title: honey cake
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and shortening or oil well. Add honey and beat well. Add alternating with coffee the rest of the ingredients. Sprinkle with nuts and raisins with tablespoon of flour and add to batter. Bake in a deep greased Bundt pan at 350 degrees for 35 to 40 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: chicken fajita pasta
directions: Saute green pepper and onion.
Add fajita strips to onions and green peppers; set aside/
Boil spiral pasta as directed; drain.
Mix green peppers, onions and chicken with pasta.
Chip oleo; mix well.

title: pepperoni loaf
directions: Thaw bread in plastic bowl in refrigerator.
After completely thawed, roll it into a rectangle approximately 10 inches wide. Brush with olive oil.
Top with basil, pepperoni and cheese.
Roll it and place on a greased baking sheet.
Bake until golden brown, approximately 15 to 20 minutes, at 350°.
Cut into 1-inch slices.

title: marzetti
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper; drain off fat. Stir in the next 9 ingredients. Spoon into a greased 3-quart casserole; top with cheese. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt into pot double boiler.
Add boiling water; blend and cook, stirring constantly until thick. Beat egg yolks and stir into mixture.
Cook 2 more minutes. Remove from heat.
Add lemon juice, butter and rind from lemon. Mix well and cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff, adding 6 tablespoons sugar gradually.
Swirl over pie filling and bake in moderate oven at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes until golden brown.

title: impossible pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In blender container, combine all ingredients, except coconut.
Blend on low 3 minutes.
Pour mixture into greased 10-inch pie plate.
Let stand 5 minutes. Sprinkle coconut over top.
Carefully place in oven; bake 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted near edge comes out clean.
Cool slightly.
Serve warm or chilled.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: mock chow mein
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together.
Add remaining ingredients, except chow mein noodles.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours. Sprinkle with chow mein noodles during the last 20 minutes of baking.

title: no bake peach pie
directions: Mix together and pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Chill several hours.
Garnish with fresh peach slices.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: mexican-style meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and mix thoroughly.
Put mixture into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan that has been sprayed with release agent.
Press mixture to remove air pockets.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
If using glass baking pan, bake at 325°.
Serves 8.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar, mix well. Add vanilla.
Spread over cool cake.

title: mattie's texas tumbleweeds
directions: Saute onion in a little oil.
Add a can of tomato paste and enough water to make a thick sauce.
Add all spices.
Prepare the tumbleweeds (young and tender, 4 to 5 inches high).
Pull off the roots.
Wash greens in a colander and blanch.
Add this to tomato mixture and simmer a few minutes.
Serve as a side dish or over a bed of rice.
Enjoy!

title: spaghetti seafood delight
directions: *Seafood Salad is available at most supermarket deli counters.

title: sweet dills
directions: Combine vinegar and sugar in saucepan; boil.
Let cool.
Slice and rinse baby dills (inexpensive works well).
Pour out juice from jar and rinse.
Return sliced dills to jar; pour cooled vinegar mixture over top into jar and recap.
The longer the pickles set the better tasting they are.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Follow directions on cake mix. Fold in berries.
Pour in 11 x 13-inch pan and bake according to directions on box.

title: paco pepper snacks
directions: Separate rolls into 4 rectangles; press to seal. Set aside. Combine all other ingredients; blend well. Spread 1/4 cup cheese mixture on each rectangle; roll up and cut into 10 slices. Place cut side down on a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes 40 appetizers.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Mix all together.
Makes 1 large pie.
The pie will form its own crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: one dish chicken and rice
directions: Combine all vegetables and pour in large pan.
Place cut up chicken on top of mixture and cover.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into two unbaked pie shells. Cook 10 minutes at 400°, then reduce heat to 300°.
Cook until done.
Makes 2 pies.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: In saucepan, melt butter and blend in flour, salt and pepper. Add milk.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add onions, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Cube the cheese and stir all together until melted.
Pour over cooked macaroni and turn into casserole.
Cover with potato chip crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: caramel pecan squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place cake mix in large bowl and cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Press into bottom of ungreased 15 x 10-inch pan.
Top with pecans.
In heavy saucepan, combine brown sugar, butter and honey.
Bring to a rolling boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 3 minutes; remove from heat.
Stir in cream until well blended. Pour hot mixture evenly over pecans.
Bake at 350°
for 17 to 22 minutes until entire surface is bubbly.
Cool completely before cutting into 48 bars.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Wash and drain lettuce.
Break into bite size pieces.
Place in large salad bowl.
Add pepper, onion, celery, eggs, peas and bacon.
Mix mayonnaise with sugar.
Mix together with other ingredients in bowl.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and melt the butter.
Add all ingredients together and stir well.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell and bake in oven for about 40 minutes at 350°.
Makes 1 pie.

title: marshmallow waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle apples with lemon juice.
Add marshmallows, celery and nuts.
Add enough mayonnaise to moisten.
Toss lightly.
For each serving, place a mound of salad on a lettuce covered plate.

title: microwave peanut butter fudge
directions: Sift sugar.
Heat milk and margarine until margarine is melted.
Microwave	on High 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Add sugar and peanut butter.
Stir until smooth.	Pour into a greased 8-inch square dish.

title: peanut patties
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and milk; place in heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly until drops of mixture forms soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Take off heat, add butter, vanilla and raw peanuts.
Stir until mixture thickens and drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: 9-inch pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, salt, melted butter and corn syrup together with rotary beater.
Add pecan halves.
Mix in.
Pour into pastry lined pie pan.
Bake in a 375° oven for 40 to 50 minutes or until set and pastry is nicely browned.
Cool.

title: sassy onion dip
directions: In small mixing bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cover and chill.
Stir before serving.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Heat spinach until melted only.
Drain well.
Mix sour cream and onion soup mix and add to spinach.
Put in baking dish and top with crumbs and cheese.
Dot with margarine.
Bake 20 minutes, covered, at 375°.
Uncover and bake a little longer until brown. Serves 6 .

title: oat or maypo cake
directions: Mix all ingredients 5 minutes with medium speed of electric mixer.
Grease Bundt pan and coat with oats.

title: pepper steak
directions: Makes 4 servings.
To cook by microwave:
Heat oil in 12x8-inch dish at medium-high 2 minutes.
Add steak, soy sauce, and ginger. Cook at medium-high 5 to 6 minutes; stir once.
Season with salt and stir in peppers and onions.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook at medium-high 3 to 3 1/2 minutes, or until vegetables are tender crisp.
Blend cornstarch with broth until smooth.
Stir into dish. Cook at medium-high 3 to 3 1/2 minutes, or until sauce is thickened; stir once.

title: tangy cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts, mixing well.
Shape into 2 balls and coat with pecans.
Chill 8 hours.
Serve at room temperature.
Yield: 4 1/2 cups.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make into small balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: crab meat dip(here's a pleasant tasting dip you'll find easy to prepare)
directions: Again this is blended with an electric mixer.
If you are serving a small party, or several dips, you may wish to cut these recipes in two.
No trouble.
Goes well on party crackers.

title: clam chowder
directions: Simmer chopped onion and celery in microwave in the milk and 1 teaspoon Butter Buds until vegetables are soft.
Add clams and potatoes.
Cook until potatoes are done.
Thicken with instant mashed potatoes.,
Add no salt; celery has all that's needed for flavor.
Calories:
125 per 1/2 cup; low cholesterol, low fat and low calorie.

title: sopa xochitl(zucchini soup)
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender, not brown.
Stir in broth, zucchini, corn, chili peppers and spices.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat and cover.
Cook until zucchini is tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in milk.
Heat until piping hot.
Add cheese. Garnish with parsley.
Serve with hot buttered and rolled tortillas.

title: vegetable and beef soup
directions: Cube beef and brown in large pot in small amount of oil.
Add tomatoes after putting them through blender.
Add onion, celery, zucchini, carrots, beans, butter beans, cabbage, potatoes and butter.
Cook slow for about 1 to 2 hours, the longer the better.

title: dk wright's favorite artichoke spread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain artichoke hearts and chop.
Add cheese, mayonnaise, sour cream and seasonings to taste.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool for 5 to 8 minutes before serving.
Serve as spread for crackers.
Makes 6 servings.

title: "best ever" spinach dip
directions: Thaw frozen chopped spinach and squeeze dry.
Stir soup mix, sour cream and mayonnaise until blended.
Stir in spinach, water chestnuts (chopped) and chopped green onions.
Cover and chill 2 hours.
Stir before serving.
Makes 4 cups.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, cheese, onion and mayonnaise.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with bacon and olives.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: cherry vanilla ribbon pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
On low speed, beat in water and pudding; mix until smooth.
Fold in whipped cream. Spread half the pudding mixture into prepared shell; top with half cherry pie filling.
Repeat.
Chill for 2 hours.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: fried green tomatoes or eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant or cut off ends of green tomatoes; cut into thin slices.
Soak eggplant for 10 minutes in salted water.
Dip in egg; roll in flour.
Fry in hot oil in skillet until brown.
Drain on absorbent paper; serve.

title: crispy fried okra
directions: Combine cornmeal, salt and pepper.
Dredge okra in cornmeal mix.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Mix with egg and buttermilk.
Bake on cookie sheet at 450° for 40 minutes or until crisp.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar, then add eggs and beat.
Sift flour and soda together; add to creamed mixture.
Add oats and mix well. I like to keep these refrigerated overnight.
These can be dropped from spoon or rolled out or formed into balls.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Rather underbaked than overbaked.
I prefer 3 cups of oats.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Put all ingredients in a large saucepan and bring to a boil. Add yellow food coloring as desired.
Slice apples in jar and pour filling over them.
Process 20 minutes in hot water bath.
Makes about 10 quarts.

title: philadelphia dip
directions: Beat ingredients until smooth and soft as warm butter.
Put in serving bowl and place in refrigerator.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, lemon and vanilla with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended; add eggs.
Pour into crust.

title: low carb squash casserole
directions: Stir-fry the squash and onion in butter until slightly tender, but still crisp. Do not add salt. Combine remaining ingredients with squash and put in a casserole dish. Top with Atkins chips and cheese. You can also use regular chips, seasoned dressing or crackers as a topping. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: piquant sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl, stirring well. Yields about 1 1/4 cups.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix soup and milk together and add to green beans.
Stir in water chestnuts and 1/2 of the can of onion rings.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350° and then top with the rest of onion rings.
Put back in oven for 10 to 15 more minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix together pecans and coconut.
Sprinkle in greased 10 x 13-inch pan.
Make cake mix according to directions.
Pour cake mix over pecans and coconut.
Beat together cream cheese, oleo, vanilla and powdered sugar.
Spread over top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Rich and no frosting.
It's in the cake.

title: italian creamy dressing
directions: Shake all ingredients together in a covered jar until blended. Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: mrs. g's brownies
directions: Melt margarine, add cocoa.
Add sifted dry ingredients with beaten eggs and vanilla. Blend thoroughly.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 22 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Tear toasted bread into pieces and place in lightly greased casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over toast. Let stand 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.

title: easy chicken dish
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Sprinkle onions and green pepper and salt and pepper to taste over chicken.
Pour water and bouillon over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Take out and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake for 15 minutes more.

title: parisian vegetable casserole
directions: In 9 x 13-inch casserole, spread vegetables (partially cooked).
Mix Cheez Whiz and soup; heat and pour over vegetables. Top with a layer of croutons or Pepperidge stuffing mix (crushed). Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: mexican corn bread casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a skillet, brown ground beef with onion, green pepper and garlic; drain off fat.
Stir in tomato paste, water and 1 teaspoon chili powder.
Spread into a 2-quart oblong baking dish or 9-inch square pan.
In a small bowl, blend cream cheese with 1 egg until smooth; stir in corn.
Spoon corn mixture over beef; sprinkle with cheese.
In a medium bowl, combine cornmeal, flour, baking powder, salt and remaining 1/2 teaspoon chili powder.
Stir in milk blended with egg and margarine just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon onto cheese; gently spread to cover corn and cheese layer.
Bake 30 minutes or until top is golden.
Makes 6 servings; 450 calories per serving.

title: peaches and cream cheesecake pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed until smooth.
Pour batter into a greased 8-inch cake or pie pan.
Drain peaches, reserving 3 tablespoons liquid.
Set peach liquid aside.
Arrange peach slices over the batter.

title: patience cake
directions: Bake cake as directed and split each layer in half, making 4 layers.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread on cooled cake. Refrigerate 3 days before cutting.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns.
Mix all ingredients except crumbs.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Top with cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: coffee punch
directions: Dissolve coffee and sugar in boiling water.
Add milk.
Serve over equal parts of chocolate and vanilla ice cream (2 gallons each flavor).
Serves 100 people.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion in margarine until tender.	Add other ingredients.
Simmer but do not boil.
Cook until thickened stirring often.
If too tart add more sugar.
Makes 2 cups.

title: cherry cake
directions: Spread filling in the bottom of microwave tube pan.
Combine rest of ingredients and spread over filling.
Microwave on Medium power for 12 minutes and on High for 3 minutes.
Invert on serving plate.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook ground beef.
Add minced onion, crushed garlic, tomato paste, tomatoes, basil, oregano, salt and pepper.
Simmer gently about 30 minutes.
While sauce is cooking, cook lasagna noodles according to package directions.
Mix Ricotta cheese and Parmesan cheese.

title: sweet green relish
directions: Combine with first mixture and cook all together for 20 minutes.
Place in hot jars and seal.
Makes 7 quarts.

title: potato bread
directions: In a bowl, mix together all ingredients except flour. Gradually add flour and knead.
Place in warm area, covered, and let rise.
Put into 3 loaf pans. Let rise until doubled in size. Bake in a preheated 375° oven until done.

title: chicken with drop dumplings
directions: In Dutch oven or stock pot over medium heat, brown chicken on all sides in butter and olive oil mixture.
Add water, celery, onion, garlic, thyme, parsley, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Cover and bring to a boil; lower heat and simmer for 2 to 3 hours, or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken; remove meat from bones and return meat to pot.
Put flour in a cup; blend in enough cold water to make a smooth paste.
Stir flour paste into hot stew, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add dumpling batter and proceed according to directions.

title: diabetic fruit cup
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze in Dixie cups.
When ready to serve, let thaw slightly.

title: spinach madeline
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Reserve 1/2 cup liquor.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onions.
Cook until soft and clear.
Add flour. Cook smooth but not brown.
Add seasonings.
Add cheese.
Cut into small squares.
Add cooked spinach.
If too dry, add liquor from spinach.
Put buttered bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: seven layer cookie
directions: In a 9 x 12-inch pan, melt oleo.
Add in order: crushed graham crackers, Angel Flake coconut, chocolate chips and sweetened condensed milk.
Pat down with spatula.
Sprinkle chopped nuts. Cook in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Keep and freezes well!

title: scalloped apples
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Slowly add flour and cheese.
Drain apples and pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Spread cheese mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until top is golden brown or you can tell it is done.

title: creamy carrots
directions: Boil carrots and chicken bouillon in water for 15 minutes. Saute scallions in butter.
Add Cheez Whiz, sour cream and milk. Mix all together in a buttered baking dish and cover with parsley and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in salted water; save broth.
Pick meat from bones and arrange in bottom of bake pan or casserole dish.
Blend melted margarine with stuffing mix.

In large bowl, mix the 2 cans of soup with 2 cups of the broth left from the cooked chicken. Cover chicken with alternate layers of stuffing and soup mix, allowing a small amount of stuffing to sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° to 375° about 20 to 25 minutes or until browned on top.

title: smoky salmon spread or dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill. Use on your favorite crackers.

title: mattie's chili
directions: Soak pinto beans overnight.
Next day, drain beans and rinse well.
Place beans in large pot with ham hock.
Let it cook.
When the beans are ready, cut up the ham hock with the beans (chop fine).
Cook the beans with chicken broth.

title: vanilla fudge
directions: Place all ingredients, except vanilla and nuts, in saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils. Continue cooking, stirring constantly, to soft ball stage (238°). Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Cool to lukewarm (110°).
Then beat until fudge begins to thicken and loses its gloss.
Pour in nuts.
Quickly spread into an 8-inch square pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 2 pounds.
If desired, add 1/4 cup candied maraschino cherries.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour mixture into a Bundt pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool.
Invert in platter.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: 5 pound chocolate fudge
directions: Boil sugar, milk and salt exactly 8 minutes.
Remove from fire and add chocolate chips, oleo, marshmallow cream until all thoroughly mixed.
Stir in 2 cups pecans.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet.
Chill in refrigerator.
Keeps indefinitely in fridge or can freeze candy in Saran and carton.

title: crock-pot stroganoff
directions: Place beef, onion soup mix and cream of mushroom soup in crock-pot.
Cook all day on low.
Just before serving, add sour cream.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: rocky road nut cake
directions: Sift together first 3 ingredients.
Add eggs and vanilla. Then stir in walnuts and margarine.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Use Rocky Road Frosting.

title: cranberried chicken
directions: Cut chicken cutlets (or whole breasts) in half.
Microwave rice per directions.
Slice mushrooms into thick slices.
Mince the garlic and saute in skillet with warm olive oil until soft. Add the chicken and cook quickly on both sides but don't brown the meat.
Cut scallions in 1/2-inch pieces and add to pan, stirring until soft.
Meanwhile, in a mixing bowl, stir together the cranberry sauce and wine and add mixture to the skillet.
Cover and simmer for about 10 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink in center.
Add mushrooms and stir to moisten.
Cook another few minutes until sauce is bubbly.
Serve over rice.

title: vanilla nuggets(cookies)
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Beat egg, milk and vanilla together.
Mix flour, baking powder and nuts.
Mix wet and dry ingredients thoroughly.
Drop from a teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 300°.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: shrimp soup
directions: Mix all ingredients and heat thoroughly.
Garnish with chives or parsley.
Serves a large group.

title: finger jello
directions: Dissolve 2 packs Knox gelatine in 1 1/4 cups cold water; stir and set aside.
Combine 1 cup cold water and 1 (6 oz.) package Jell-O; add 1/3 cup sugar.
Bring to a boil and remove from heat. Add cold mixture to hot mixture, plus 1/2 cup cold water and pour into pan.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
After jelled, cut into squares.
Keeps without refrigeration.
Pull the cubes out from pan with your fingers.
They will come out clean, not jagged.
(Try eliminating sugar).
Use 8 or 9-inch pan.
Note:
To double or triple recipe, put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
I do not use sugar.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook diced onion, green pepper and celery in oleo until tender.
Stir in flour and gradually add broth and milk to make a thin white sauce.
Add cheese, olives, mushrooms, pimento and cooked, deboned chicken, cut in bite size pieces.

title: meat balls
directions: Combine all ingredients; shape into balls.
Brown in shortening.
Use with
favorite sauce.

title: no-fat rice salad
directions: Combine rice, tomato, peas, corn and green onions in serving bowl.
Beat together remaining ingredients for dressing and pour over rice, mixing well.
Cover and chill for 15 minutes.
Toss again before serving.

title: marlene's new year's dinner
directions: Place pork roast in 5-quart Dutch oven.
Add Polish sausage and sauerkraut.
Add 1 quart of water and cover with lid.
Cook until pork is tender, about 2 1/2 to 3 hours in a 375° oven. Remove from the oven.
Arrange canned biscuit dough over top of dish and bake an additional 30 minutes.
You have a complete meal ready to eat.

title: yummy holiday applesauce nut bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine sugar, applesauce, oil, egg whites and skim milk; mix thoroughly.
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Combine until all ingredients are well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Spread batter in an oiled and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: sara's peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and margarine in saucepan.
When starts boiling, boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter.
Stir until mixed.
Add vanilla and marshmallow cream. Pour in buttered pan.
Cut when cool.

title: chicken garlic bake
directions: Pound chicken breasts to about 1/8-inch thick.
Combine softened cream cheese, garlic powder, onions, salt and pepper to make paste.
Place 1/4 of mixture on half of each chicken breast. Fold other half over to seal mixture inside and secure with toothpick.
Roll lightly in bread crumbs.
Saute in skillet in hot vegetable oil for 3 minutes per side.
Transfer to baking sheet and bake in preheated 400° oven for 6 minutes or until done. Garnish with chopped tomatoes.

title: pasta-in-a-pot
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add onion, garlic, spaghetti sauce, stewed tomatoes and undrained mushrooms.
Mix and simmer for 20 minutes.
Cook macaroni; drain and rinse with cold water.

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add chili powder and milk.
Mix well.
Add flour, juice and beans.
Stir well.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: basic pie crust
directions: Mix flour, Crisco and salt until it is well blended.
Add 5 tablespoons of cold water and mix.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Line 9-inch round pan with plastic wrap.
Melt chips.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanuts.
Pour into pan.
Place candy corn on top to decorate.
Cool completely.
Remove from pan.
Peel away plastic wrap.
Cut in wedges to serve.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix the butter, peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Roll in balls.
Dip in the chocolate and paraffin mixture.

title: christina's pumpkin pudding
directions: Mix until crumbly the oats, flour, brown sugar and butter. Press down in a 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Press a little up the sides.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.

title: grandma mildred's molasses cookies
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Add boiling water and mix well. In another bowl, mix remaining dry ingredients, then combine with first mix and finally add nuts and raisins.
Chill dough until firm.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add vinegar to water and stir until thickened over medium heat.
Add 2 tablespoons oleo and stir.
Let cool a few minutes and pour into 8-inch pie shell.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon.
Serve warm.

title: brownie swirl cheesecake
directions: Prepare brownie mix according to package directions for chewy fudge brownies.
Spread into a greased 9-inch spring-form pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes (brownies will not test done). Cool for 10 minutes on a wire rack.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease baking pan.
Sprinkle rice over bottom.
Heat soup with milk.
Pour over rice.
Place chicken pieces evenly in pan.
Place pats of butter on top of chicken.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and paprika over all.
Seal pan with foil and bake at 325° for 1 hour or until chicken is done.

title: golden granola
directions: Combine all ingredients except raisins in an ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan and mix well.
