Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Stir occasionally.
Stir in raisins and cool thoroughly.
Store in a tightly covered container in a cool dry place (or refrigerate).
Yields 6 cups.

title: pancakes
directions: Sift together dry milk, flour, cinnamon and salt.
Set aside. Combine margarine and egg yolks.
In a medium bowl, beat egg whites with sugar until stiff.
Lightly fold yolk mixture into whites, then gradually fold in sifted ingredients.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Heat nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Drop batter, 1 tablespoon at a time, into skillet.
Lightly spread with back of spoon to form pancakes.
Cook until underside is browned; turn pancakes.
Cook until underside is browned.
Turn pancakes and cook 1 minute longer.
Serve hot.
Makes 2 servings.

title: cheese bread roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven
to
Trim crusts from bread and cut each slice in
half.
Lay strip of bacon and place 2 slices of bread vertically,
covering
almost
all the strip.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Roll
up
and secure with a toothpick.
Bake in broiler pan
for 20 minutes, turning once.	Remove toothpicks and cut in half.
Makes approximately 100 hors d'oeuvres.

title: hot ham and cheese spread
directions: Mix cream cheese, Cheddar cheese and ham until well blended. Spoon into ovenproof crock or bowl. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until puffed and lightly browned. Serve warm as a spread with crackers. Makes 2 cups.

title: milky way squares
directions: Melt candy with butter; stir until blended. Stir in cereal; mix well. Pat into greased 11 x 7 inch pan. Refrigerate until firm. Cut into squares.

title: hot diggity dogs
directions: Split hot dogs within 1/2 inch of ends, insert strips of cheese in hot dogs.
Place hot dogs on crescent rolls dough and roll up.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degree for 12-15 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large mixing bowl; mix well. Stir in buttermilk.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture, stirring only until ingredients are well moistened.
Stir in nuts.
Pour batter into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Let cool before slicing.

title: ribbon jello salad
directions: Dissolve each package of Jell-O in 1 1/2 cups of water, instead of the usual 2 cups.
(Dissolve Jell-O as needed for layers.)
Dissolve the 2 envelopes of plain gelatine in cold water and set aside.
Put the milk and sugar in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add the softened gelatine.
Put sour cream in a bowl and slowly add the milk mixture.
Add vanilla.

title: wheat bread for automatic bread machine
directions: Add all ingredients in the order listed into a large automatic bread machine and push start.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until tender.
Stir in meat and oregano.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Heat through. Pour mixture into buttered, shallow 2-quart casserole.
Spoon mashed potatoes over hash.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt and pepper.
Add beet juice; cook until thickened.
Add the orange juice.
Add beets.

title: confetti cream cake
directions: Prepare confetti by dissolving each package of orange, lime and strawberry jello in 1 3/4 cups boiling water.
Pour each jello mixture into a shallow pan and chill until set; cut into small cubes.
Prepare crumb crust and line a spring-form pan.
Dissolve lemon jello and sugar in 1 cup boiling water; cool to room temperature.
Whip the cream with dash of salt, 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and 2 tablespoons sugar until stiff and refrigerate.
In a large bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in cooled lemon jello; fold in whipped cream and blend well.

title: mint tea
directions: Pour boiling water over the bark, first breaking it into bits. Cover the pitcher containing it and let stand until cold.
Add lemon juice if desired and sweeten to taste.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix and put into a graham cracker pie crust. Refrigerate.

title: deluxe lemon cake
directions: Lightly grease and flour angel food cake pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend all ingredients; beat 2 minutes.
Pour in cake pan. Bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: butter dips
directions: Mix all ingredients, except butter, until you can knead it. Fold 6 to 10 times.
Flatten to 8-inch square.
Cut into 16 equal pieces.
Roll in melted butter.
Bake in 425° preheated oven for 8 to 12 minutes until light brown.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix together and stuff in casing.
Cut into pieces, size of a wiener and can in jars.

title: sliced baked potatoes(microwave)
directions: Slice potatoes 3/4 way through.

title: easy cereal-peanut butter bars
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup in saucepan and bring to a boil. Remove from heat, stir in peanut butter.
Pour over cereal in a bowl and mix well.
Spread in greased 9-inch square pan.
Melt chocolate in saucepan over very low heat, stirring constantly. Spread over cereal mixture in pan.
Let stand until chocolate is firm.
Cut into 2 x 1-inch bars.
Makes about 32.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: In a small mixing bowl, combine sugar, onion, salt and mustard.
Add vinegar; mix well.
Gradually add oil while beating on medium speed; beat for 5 minutes or until very thick.
Stir in poppy seeds.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serve over fresh fruit or salad greens.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Yield: 1 2/3 cups.

title: chicken divan
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put vegetables.
Next, layer meat from chicken breasts.
Next, combine chicken soup, mayo and curry powder.
Spread over chicken.
Top with corn bread crumbs and shredded cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Pour hot water over cut dates. Add shortening.
Let cool, then add sugar, slightly beaten eggs and vanilla.
Mix these ingredients, then add flour, soda and cream of tartar, then fold chopped nuts in last.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center of loaf comes out clean.
Use 2 medium size bread pans.

title: cheese, ham and bacon soup
directions: Mix bouillon cubes, water, salt, onion, celery and potatoes together.
Cover and cook 20 to 30 minutes.
Add remaining vegetables and cook until tender.
Add cream of chicken soup and 1 cup of water.
Add cheese and cook slowly until all cheese is melted.
Sprinkle in bacon and ham.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Place rice on bottom of greased round casserole.
Place chicken pieces on top of rice.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over chicken.
Add mushroom soup mixed with water.
Cover casserole; bake in 325° oven for 2 hours.

title: chicken divan
directions: Arrange broccoli pieces in greased baking dish; season to taste.
Place chicken on top (shredded).
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry powder and cheese and heat gently until cheese melts.
Pour over chicken.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until thoroughly heated.
Trim with pimento strips and parsley.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: easy chicken-chilies casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F.
Lightly coat 13 x 9 inch baking dish with non - stick cooking spray.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: sour cream rhubarb pie
directions: Mix the ingredients and let stand for 10 minutes.
Pour into unbaked crust.
Cover with top crust.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: family's favorite rolls
directions: Melt oleo in small baking pan.
Cut biscuits in half, making half moon shape.
Dip both sides in oleo and place in pan. Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Combine cake mix, fruit cocktail, 1 c. coconut and eggs in large mixing bowl. Blend 2 minutes at medium speed. Pour into a 9 X 13 greased pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar. Bake at 325 degrees for 45 minutes. Bring oleo, granulated sugar and evaporated milk to a boil. Boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in remaining coconut and spoon over hot cake in pan. Serve warm or cold.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Peel boiled potatoes and slice thinly.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, horseradish and celery seed.
Combine onion and parsley.
In a glass serving bowl, layer potato slices, salt, sour cream mixture and parsley mixture.
Repeat until potatoes are used up, ending with parsley mixture.
Store covered in refrigerator at least 8 hours.

title: orange marmalade
directions: Cover fruit with 3 times its bulk of cold water.
Let stand overnight.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Let stand overnight.
Bring to rolling boil; add equal quantity sugar.
Cook until jelled.
Pour in open dish for 24 hours.
Place in jars or dishes without reheating.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan or dish with mixed milk and instant pudding.
In separate bowl mix remaining ingredients and combine both mixtures and stir well.
Pour over cookies in pan. Sprinkle with cookies.

title: heavenly orange fluff
directions: Mix jello in boiling water.
Stir in orange juice.
Add oranges and pineapple.
Refrigerate until jelled.

title: easy chocolate icing
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine melted butter or margarine, cocoa and sugar.
Add milk gradually and vanilla.
Mix all well.
Place over medium heat.
When mixture comes to full boil, boil then for 1 minute.
Let cool before spreading on cake.

title: sounds weird - tastes great chicken
directions: Put chicken breasts in casserole dish.
Mix the cranberry sauce, dressing and dry soup mix together and pour over chicken pieces.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sour cream raisin bars
directions: Mix oatmeal, flour, brown sugar, butter and soda.
Put 2/3 in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: custard(this is a good custard recipe.)
directions: In a bowl, beat egg yolks, then add hot milk and sugar; beat well.
Put mixture in a double boiler and add salt.
Cook until thickened, being careful not to let double boiler go dry.
Let cool, then stir in vanilla.

title: dill dip for veggies
directions: Mix all ingredients and blend in blender.

title: italian meat sauce
directions: Brown ground beef or pork in large skillet.
Add onion and garlic and cook until onion is tender.
Stir in tomato puree, water, tomato paste, parsley, sugar, basil, salt and pepper. Simmer 30 minutes.

title: carrot raisin salad
directions: Combine carrots, raisins and chopped walnuts in a bowl. Combine remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Add to carrot mixture.
Toss gently.
Yields 4 servings.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix 1/4 cup powdered sugar, 1/2 cup butter and flour.
Press in an 8 x 11-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Beat eggs, lemon rind and juice, sugar, baking powder and flaked coconut.
Pour in crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Frost with 1/2 cup butter mixed with 3/4 cup powdered sugar.
Cool and cut into small pieces.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding, oil,
club soda and eggs well at medium speed.
Add nuts.	Pour into
greased
and
floured 9-inch pans.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 325°.

title: thai beef kabobs
directions: Cut meat into strips at least 2 inches thick.
Partially freeze the strips and then cut across the grain in long strips about 1/4-inch thick.
Mix together all other ingredients and use to marinate meat for up to 2 hours.
Be sure to stir occasionally. Skewer meat strips with onion chunks and grill to your liking.

title: pancakes
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Combine flour, milk, eggs and nutmeg in mixing bowl.
Beat lightly, but leave batter a little lumpy.
Melt butter in 12-inch skillet.
When very hot, pour in batter and bake for 15 to 20 minutes to golden brown.
Sprinkle with sugar and put briefly back in oven.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Serve with raspberry jam.

title: fresh apple cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by teaspoons on baking sheet.
Bake 11 to 14 minutes at 400°.
Ice while still warm.

title: zucchini
directions: Cut up zucchini and saut with onions in a little water. When almost tender, add mushrooms. When mushrooms are almost tender and water is cooked down, add soy sauce. You can add boneless, cooked chicken for a stir-fry if you'd like.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar. Sift flour, cocoa, salt and baking powder. Add eggs and flour mixture to the first 3 ingredients, alternately. Mix well. Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Let cool in pan.

title: coleslaw
directions: Grate cabbage and carrot. Set aside.
Mix mayonnaise, Miracle Whip, vinegar, sugar and milk.
Beat by hand until mixture is creamy. Pour over cabbage and carrot.
Mix well.

title: donuts
directions: Mix shortening and eggs.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add to eggs and shortening.
Put milk in, then add rest of ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Roll out dough using flour to sprinkle to keep from sticking.
Cut out dough with cup, pulling the centers apart to make a hole.
Fry until brown on both sides; roll in powdered sugar.

title: chicken balls
directions: In a bowl, mix thoroughly all ingredients except corn flakes. Shape into small balls about 1 inch in diameter.
Roll in flakes; arrange on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until crunchy and golden brown.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: brunswick stew(can be frozen to serve at a later date.)
directions: Brown chicken pieces in large skillet in just enough oil to cover the bottom of the pan, drain. Brown chuck and both sausages, drain.
In a VERY large stew pot saute celery and onions in 1 tablespoon of oil until tender, not brown.
Add chicken pieces, beef, sausage, ham hocks, tomatoes, parsley and red pepper and basil.
Salt to taste.
Barely cover with water, bring to a boil then reduce heat to simmer, cover and cook until chicken is tender (about an hour).

title: banana nut bread
directions: Beat
eggs
well.
Add sugar and beat until light.
Add mashed bananas,
flour
and
soda, dissolved in a little warm water, vanilla, salt, melted butter and nuts,
stirring after you add each
item.
Pour into a Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: beer steak
directions: In skillet, heat beer.
Chop up onion, green pepper and mushrooms.
Set aside.
Add steak to skillet.
Cook on high until juice runs out, about 5 to 10 minutes, then add onion, green pepper and mushrooms to skillet.
Reduce heat.
Cover; let cook until the beer evaporates.
Serve.

title: old fashioned pot roast
directions: Cook roast almost done.
Cover with water.
Add vegetables and salt.
Cook for 20 minutes, then add gravy mix.
Simmer 20 minutes longer.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Saute onion and pepper in margarine.
Add seasonings.
Add clams, juice and bread crumbs.
Cube cheese and stir into mixture. Place in ovenproof dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: key lime cake
directions: Mix well. Bake in 4 layers at 350° until done when tested with toothpick (or use 9 x 13 pan instead of layers).

title: popcorn balls
directions: I sometimes use maple syrup, which makes it extra delicious!!

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, eggs and onions.
Blend in broccoli.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese.
Melt margarine and add seasoned crumbs. Mix well and spread over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots in salted water with small amount of sugar until tender.
Drain and place in buttered casserole dish.
Melt together the cheese and oleo; pour over carrots.
Sprinkle buttered cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, or until bubbly.
Makes a big dish.

title: grilled tuna with tomato-basil vinaigrette
directions: To make vinaigrette, whisk together 4 tablespoons olive oil, vinegar, shallots, garlic, parsley, basil, salt and pepper.
Add tomatoes and stir.
For tuna, set grill rack 3 inches above coals. Lightly brush steaks with olive oil and grill for 2 to 3 minutes on each side.
Arrange tuna on warm plates and spoon vinaigrette over or around them.
Garnish with basil leaves.
Serves 4 generously.

title: alternate chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken tender with a little salt and just a dusting of pepper.
When chicken is done and falls off the bone, tear it into bite-sizes (do not put it in your food processor).
Add apples, celery, raisins, nuts and mayonnaise.
Serve on romaine or escarole (not iceberg) lettuce.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter and stir in syrup.
Beat egg with buttermilk.
Mix together the dry ingredients, then stir in the eg mixture and the syrup mixture.
Pour into a 9-inch square pan that has been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Bake for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° and bake 25 minutes. Serve with ice cream, yogurt or sorbet.
Makes 9 servings.

title: brack (irish fruit bread)
directions: Overnight:
Soak the fruit and sugar in 1 cup cold strong tea. The next morning add the flour and the well beaten egg.
Mix well.
Pour into a well-greased, foil lined loaf pan.
(It will look awful, but don't give up!)
Bake for 2 hours on middle shelf at 300°.
Take out of oven and leave in the pan until next day. Slice and serve with butter.
Keeps well wrapped in foil.
Can be frozen.

title: german sweet chocolate mousse pie
directions: Heat chocolate and 2 tablespoons milk in pan over low heat. Stir until chocolate is melted.
Beat the sugar into the cream cheese.
Add the chocolate mixture and the remaining milk; beat until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze four hours.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Coat chicken breasts with beaten egg, then place in bread crumbs and coat again.
Then place in a 9 x 13 pan for baking. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Then cover with spaghetti sauce and cook for 20 more minutes.
About 5 to 10 minutes before it's done, add Parmesan cheese on the top for melting.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells according to package directions, drain.
(Keep separated in cool water.)
Combine cheeses, eggs, parsley oregano, salt and pepper.
Fill each shell with 1 1/2 tablespoons cheese mixture.
Spread thin layer of sauce on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Place shells in pan, cheese side up.
Cover with remaining sauce. Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes, or until hot and bubbly. Fills about 36 shells; yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: no crust fudge pie
directions: Grease pie pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Best when topped with ice cream.

title: waldorf chicken sandwich
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Serve on whole grain bread.
Makes 3 servings.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix ingredients and press into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Mash bananas and mix in butter mix along with eggs.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Then add nuts to mix.
Place in greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Allow to cool, then turn out of pan.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter. When limp, add chili pepper. Saute for 1 to 2 minutes. Add White Sauce, hominy and cheese. Put in buttered casserole and bake for 25 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle dash cayenne and paprika on top before baking.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Beat eggs.
Stir in all other ingredients.
Beat batter, but not too much, lumps okay.
Cook on 380° griddle.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs; sift dry ingredients.
Gradually add the dry ingredients to the beaten eggs alternating with the Wesson oil; beat well.
Add fruit and nuts; work well into mixture.
Bake in prepared tube pan at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.
Eat and enjoy plain with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: venison stir-fry
directions: In a large skillet, brown strips of venison, onion, celery and mushrooms.
Add onion powder, garlic powder, parsley flakes, pepper, beef bouillon, peas, carrots, soy sauce and water.
Simmer until heated through.
Add rice and cook until rice
is done, about 5 to 10 minutes.

title: clam chowder
directions: Pour juice from clams over vegetables in saucepan.
Cover with water to barely cover.
Simmer 20 minutes or until tender.

title: zucchini cheddar cheese bake
directions: Add salt and pepper to cooked squash.
Mix next three ingredients. Fold in egg whites.
Layer half the squash, then egg mixture, then cheese in rectangular baking dish.
Top with crumbled bacon.
Repeat layers. Mix butter with bread crumbs and sprinkle over top. (Add Parmesan cheese, if desired.)
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serves about 8.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into 4 pieces. Roll into balls. Mix sugar and cinnamon. Roll balls in sugar and cinnamon. Place in greased baking dish. Melt butter. Pour over biscuits in dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crab muffins
directions: Mix together crab meat, margarine and cheese.
Cut English muffins.
Spread on mixture.
May cut into quarters if you would like.
Heat up in the broiler or microwave.

title: tahitian salad
directions: Drain all fruit.
Fold in 8 to 16 ounces of sour cream.

title: impossible pie
directions: Blend all ingredients 3 minutes.
Lightly grease pie pan. Pour in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Boil 1 minute.
Stand for 10 minutes.
Add coloring and Certo. Stand for 10 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all together well.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Put all ingredients in food chopper on medium.
Chop and chill.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Brown beef and onion, drain grease.
Mix tomato sauce, garlic salt, soy sauce and cooked rice; simmer for 15 minutes.
While sauce is simmering boil peppers for a few minutes.
Use cake pan. Cut green peppers in half, pour sauce on top then slice of cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: green bean-zucchini salad
directions: In a small saucepan with enough boiling unsalted water to cover, cook the green beans until tender but still crisp, 3 to 4 minutes.
Drain in a colander, rinse under cold running water to stop the cooking and drain again.
In a medium sized bowl, combine the olive oil, garlic, tarragon and pepper.
Add the green beans, zucchini and onion and toss well.
Cover and chill in the refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours, tossing occasionally.
Just before serving, add the vinegar and toss again.
Serves 4.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl. Mix 1/2 cheese and save half for the top. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until done. Place the remaining cheese on the top and melt.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mash bananas.
Mix all the ingredients together and pour into an oiled and floured Bundt pan.
Cook at 350° for about 40 to 50 minutes.
Watch for cake to pull away from pan.
Very moist cake. You can serve with or without icing or with a dollop of whipped cream.

title: veg-beef soup
directions: Stir-fry meat with meat tenderizer, salt, pepper and 1/2 onion.
In large pot add potatoes, carrots, corn, peas, green beans, okra and 1/2 onion.
When meat is tender and cooked, mix in with vegetables and tomato sauce.
Spice to taste.
Add water if needed.
Cook on medium to medium-low for 2 hours.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat in fat.
Add onions, garlic and celery.
Cook until golden.
Stir in flour; add remaining ingredients and mix well. Turn into a 3-quart greased casserole.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cover casserole for first hour.
Serve on noodles or mashed potatoes.
Serves 6.

title: rosey glow cranberry punch
directions: In large saucepan, combine all ingredients and blend well. Simmer over low heat 10 to 15 minutes, or until warm.
If desired, remove cinnamon sticks and nutmeg.
Serve warm in mugs or cups. Garnish as desired.
Yields 24 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Blend in flour and salt.
Remove from heat and stir in milk with wire whisk.
Place on medium heat and stir constantly until the mixture thickens and bubbles.
Cook and stir 1 minute longer.

title: apple-cranberry relish
directions: Combine sugar, water and orange rind in heavy, medium size saucepan.
Bring to boiling.
Lower heat; simmer until clear, about 2 minutes.
Add pared, cored and chopped apples to orange rind mixture in saucepan.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, for about 5 minutes.
Coarsely chop cranberries; add to ginger, allspice and cinnamon.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, for 7 to 8 minutes, or until cranberries are soft.
Stir in raisins. Transfer relish to bowl.
Let cool; refrigerate overnight.

title: eye of round roast
directions: Rub entire roast with cooking oil, season with salt, pepper, and garlic powder.
Wrap in aluminum foil.
Bake in oven at 195°-200° for 4 - 5 hours.

title: coconut custard pies
directions: Cream sugar, cornstarch and softened butter together.
Mix one egg at a time until all eggs are in the batter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place mixture in 2 (9-inch) unbaked and thawed pie shells.
Bake at 400° for about 30 to 35 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight before serving.
Makes 2 (9-inch) deep dish pies.

title: mykonos salad
directions: Make dressing of 1/2 cup olive oil, 1/4 cup salad vinegar (part balsamic), salt and pepper. Toss lettuces with next 6 ingredients. Pour dressing over salad; toss again. Top with Feta cheese. (I usually pit the olives.) Makes 6 servings.

title: tuna crunch casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Reserve 1/2 the noodles.
In greased casserole, arrange in layers 1/2 tuna, 1/2 noodles, onion and chestnuts.
Add second layer.
Mix soup with liquid and pour on top.
Bake, uncovered, 20 minutes.
Sprinkle reserved noodles on top and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: meal in itself baked beans
directions: Put beans in a large baking dish.
Fry bacon pieces until almost done.
Drain and add to beans.
Fry potatoes in bacon grease.
Fry onions in the bacon grease.
Add potatoes and onions in beans, then add all the rest of ingredients and bake at 350° about 3/4 to 1 hour.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and eggs.
Add bananas; mix well.
Add flour, soda, salt and baking powder; mix well.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Check doneness with a toothpick.

title: juicy hamburgers
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make patties and grill.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix with mixer and bake at 350°.
Bake in 8-inch pans.

title: cupcake brownies
directions: Combine chocolate and margarine in a heavy saucepan. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until melted. Cool mixture slightly. Combine sugar, flour, eggs, vanilla and butter flavoring in a large mixing bowl. Add chocolate mixture, stirring until batter is smooth. Stir in pecans. Spoon into paper-lined muffin pans, filling each cup 2/3 full. Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes, until done.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook onions and bell peppers in the butter until tender.
Add all the other ingredients except cheese.
Pour into casserole dish; put cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until everything is cooked through good and cheese is done.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line a 9 x 13-inch dish with sliced bread.
Brown and crumble meat.
Combine with other ingredients and pour over bread. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: mock crab newburg
directions: Prepare surimi; set aside.
Melt butter in saucepan; add green pepper, mushrooms and parsley and saute.
Combine flour, salt, mustard and pepper.
Blend into melted butter and vegetables.
Add milk and wine; stir until slightly thickened.
Place surimi into buttered seashells, ramekins, pastry shells or casserole dish and pour sauce over.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Bake cake in two layers.
Slice layers with a string.
Let cool.
Mix sour cream, strawberries and sugar to make filling. Spread 1/2 of filling between sliced layers.
Take remaining 1/2 of juice and mix with Cool Whip.
This is the frosting for cake. Top with fresh strawberries.

title: burgundy beef and vegetable stew
directions: In Dutch oven, heat the oil over medium heat until hot.
Add beef and garlic, half at a time, and brown.
Stir occasionally. Pour off drippings.
Season beef with thyme, salt and pepper.
Add broth and wine to beef and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low. Cover tightly and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: stay soft icing
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and cornstarch together in a pan. Add milk and water.
Cook until thick. Remove from heat and add milk and butter.
Stir.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and put in casserole dish.
Mix corn, beans and tomato soup together and spread on top of ground beef.
Spread a layer of mashed potatoes on top of bean and corn mixture. Sprinkle cheese on top of potatoes.
Put in oven at 350° until cheese melts.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and 2 quarts water in large bowl mixing well. Freeze until firm. Thaw until slushy, to serve.

title: chicken and peas
directions: Take a cold chicken, open it up.
Put peas in, put it in the oven.
Cook at 90° for 10 minutes.
Chicken is done when buzzer goes "eeehhhtt!"

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Melt butter and blend in flour. Gradually stir in broth and evaporated milk. Cook, stirring constantly over low heat until thick.
Blend in cheese until melted. Stir in chicken and mushrooms.
Season.
Serve over cooked noodles.
Serves 6.

title: crock-pot barbecue
directions: Put meat, sugar, salt and vinegar in crock-pot and cook until well done.
Remove meat from crock-pot.
Remove bones and cut into small pieces.
Mix remaining ingredients for sauce and toss with meat.
Heat in crock-pot again until hot.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over sugar, salt and Crisco.
Stir until Crisco is dissolved and cool until mixture is lukewarm.
Add yeast which has been dissolved in lukewarm water.
Add egg which has been beaten.
Mix well.
Stir in enough flour to make soft dough.

title: grilled salmon steaks
directions: In a saucepan melt 1/3 cup margarine.
Stir in lemon juice, chopped parsley, dried tarragon, garlic powder and paprika.
Brush mixture over salmon steaks.
Place over medium coals (or gas grill) for 5 to 8 minutes on each side.
Baste frequently.

title: lasagna
directions: Pour oil in a medium to large pot and add chopped onion and garlic.
Let brown.
Add ground beef.
Let brown.
Drain and add tomato sauce and pureed tomatoes and 8 ounces water.
In a separate bowl, mix Ricotta cheese, parsley, Mozzarella cheese and eggs. Boil lasagna sheets.
In a baking dish, put one layer meat sauce, one layer lasagna sheets and one layer cheese mix and repeat steps and bake at 425° for 30 minutes covered with foil.

title: o'henry bars
directions: Cream margarine and sugars together.
Add oatmeal and stir well.
Put into greased cookie pan with sides.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes.
Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter together.
Spread on top of baked crust.
Cut into squares.

title: pineapple philly pie
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients together, stirring constantly until thick.
Cool.
Cream together cream cheese, sugar and salt; add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Add vanilla and milk. Put pineapple mixture in unbaked pie shell.
Top with cheese mixture and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes; then at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Inserted toothpicks should come out clean.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Mix flour, cocoa, salt, cinnamon, allspice and soda together.
Add alternately with blackberries and juice to first mixture.
Add raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Good with caramel sauce.

title: eggplant caviar
directions: Bake eggplant for 1 hour at 400 degrees.
Peel and chop. Saute other ingredients in a large skillet.
Add to the eggplant and simmer in a skillet about 15 minutes until mixture is thick. Chill.
Serve with crackers or pita chips.

title: zucchini dressing
directions: Melt margarine in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook zucchini and onion in melted margarine until tender.
Mix dressing according to directions on box.
Mix in with zucchini.
Add sour cream and chicken soup.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well; add hot water, then dry ingredients.
Then add potatoes, nuts and vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into mixture.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: In a skillet melt butter over medium heat.
Saute onions until tender.
Stir in potatoes, soup and milk.
Add cheese, green pepper and 1/2 cup of cracker crumbs.
Pour into shallow baking dish.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Mash cream cheese with fork until soft.
Whip milk and cream cheese until smooth.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Place in refrigerator until chilled.

title: individual cheesecakes
directions: Line small muffin tin with foil liners. Place one vanilla wafer in each liner.
Mix cheese, sugar and vanilla on medium speed. Add eggs.
Mix well.
Pour over wafers.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°.
Can be topped with fruit or nuts.

title: pear relish
directions: Peel pears and put in blender and grind pears, onions and peppers. Put in saucepan and add vinegar, turmeric, sugar and salt. Bring to boil. Simmer 20 minutes and put in jars and seal.

title: steamed squash, onion and zucchini
directions: Wash vegetables and chop into bite sized pieces.
Place in 2 to 3-quart microwave dish with lid.
Pour in water.
Microwave for about 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender, but not mushy! Season to taste and serve.

title: watergate salad
directions: Put pineapple in bowl.
Add cherries and nuts.
Sprinkle pudding over top and fold in rest of ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: mandarin cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and beat for 4 minutes.
Bake at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Mix pineapple and pudding mix.
Fold into Cool Whip.
Spread on top of cooled cake.

title: bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
Mix vegetable oil, egg and milk together.
Thoroughly blend all ingredients.
Grease 12-cup muffin pan.
Half-fill each cup.
Place in oven.
Cook 25 minutes.
Let muffins cool at least 1 hour before removing them from pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together and bake in oven at 350° for one hour.
On top melt 2 tablespoons margarine and cracker crumbs.

title: good pound cake
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed for 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating just until yellow disappears.
Add flour to butter mixture, alternating with half and half, beginning and ending with flour.
Mix at low speed just until blended after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let cool in pan on a wire rack for 10 to 15 minutes. Remove from pan; cool completely on wire rack.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix in order, batter will be rather stiff, but keep mixing. This makes a big batch of cookies.
They are very good!!
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to

title: swedish raisin bread
directions: Heat milk and add butter.
Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add salt, cardamon and raisins.
Pour in warm milk and add yeast which has been dissolved in a little water.
Add enough flour to knead into a soft dough.
Set aside to rise.
Shape into loaves and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: fruit slush
directions: Heat together the 1 cup water and 2 cups sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Let cool.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Put in freezer and freeze for 12 to 24 hours, stirring once or twice while freezing.
Remove from the freezer 1 hour before serving.

title: one bowl microwave peanut butter rice crispie treats
directions: Spray large (gallon size) Tupperware bowl with Pam.
Place butter and marshmallows in bowl and microwave until marshmallows lose shape and foam up, about 2 minutes or less.
Do not overcook, this is what makes the bars too hard.
Remove from microwave, stir to blend, then add vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir thoroughly. Stir rice cereal into same bowl and stir until coated.
Press gently into 9 x 12-inch cake pan sprayed first with Pam.

title: pat's peach cobbler
directions: Mix flour, milk, sugar, baking powder, salt and egg.
Pour in pan.
Add vanilla to the peaches and pour this over the batter. Melt butter or margarine and pour over top.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.
I usually double the recipe for my pan.

title: egg mold
directions: Mix mayonnaise and grated eggs.
Set aside.
Mix gelatin and cold water.
Let soften.
Stir.
Add hot water, then add lemon juice, onion juice and seasonings.
Stir.
Add to egg mixture. Pour into ring mold and refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: meat ball soup
directions: In 3-quart pot, brown 1/2 cup green onions in oil.
Then add water, salt and pepper. Bring to boil.
Add 1/2 cup cracked wheat.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Drain the pineapple juice into a bowl. Add the sugar and flour and mix well. Stir in the pineapple chunks and cheese. Spoon into a casserole. Top with the cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: honey applesauce cake
directions: Pour hot applesauce over honey and butter.
Mix well. When cool, add beaten eggs.
Sift together flour, spices, soda and salt.
(Use small amount of dry mix to dredge raisins and nuts.) Add flour, raisins and nuts and mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: barbecue hamburgers
directions: Cook ground beef in skillet on medium heat until browned. Drain.
Add onion; reduce heat to low.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown the ground beef.
Add the tomato sauce and seasonings. Simmer slowly for 20 minutes.
Prepare lasagna noodles.
Arrange 1 layer of lasagna in parallel strips in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with 1/3 Mozzarella cheese and 1/3 cottage cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with cottage cheese.
Top with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: meatballs and onion soup
directions: Mix together well the hamburger, oats, milk, egg and spices. Shape into 18 medium-sized meatballs.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until browned.
Drain grease.
Cook onion soup mix and water, with meatballs added, in a Dutch oven pan over low heat for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix well.
Store several hours or overnight.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add other ingredients.
Mix until well blended. Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Stir once, halfway through baking.

title: five minute fudge
directions: Heat over low heat to boiling, evaporated milk, sugar and salt.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring continuously so it does not scorch.
Remove from heat and add marshmallows, nuts, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Stir with wooden spoon until all ingredients are melted.
Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool.
Makes 2 pounds fudge.

title: hawaiian stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Mix hot water and oleo in bowl.
Stir in stuffing mix, peppers and 1/2 pineapple and syrup.
Spoon stuffing on breasts and roll up tight.
Secure with toothpicks.
Place in 9-inch pan with remaining stuffing in center.

title: biscuit pot pie
directions: Brown the ground beef.
Drain.
Mix in next 5 ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Pour in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with biscuits.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Easily doubles.

title: liquid egg custard
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl with a wire whisk.
Pour mixture through a strainer.
Chill.

title: frito pie(chili)
directions: Brown beef.
Add other ingredients except beans, cooking oil and flour.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
In a small bowl, mix cooking oil and flour together until smooth.
Add undrained kidney beans. Add bean mixture to kettle.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally for about 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.
Assemble Fritos, chili, cheese, lettuce, tomatoes, chopped onion, taco sauce, sour cream and guacamole.
Let each person serve themselves, beginning with Fritos and topping with guacamole.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute bell pepper and onion in bacon drippings.
Add remaining ingredients, except shrimp and simmer for at least ten minutes. Add peeled and cleaned shrimp and cook until tender.
Remove packet of shrimp spice before serving.
Serve on bed of rice.

title: fettuccine with pepper sauce
directions: Spray a large skillet with nonstick coating.
Stir-fry broccoli, pepper and onion for 3 to 4 minutes; remove from skillet.
Add chicken; stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes or until no longer pink.
Add soup, water and basil to skillet; mix thoroughly.
Stir in pepper mixture.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat.
Add cheese, stirring until cheese is almost melted.
Serve over hot cooked pasta; top with Parmesan.
Serves 4.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine all ingredients and mix well. Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake around 45 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken almondine
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except the soup and milk.
Mix the soup and milk together and pour over mixture.
Mix together and pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Bake for 40 minutes at 375° or until bubbly.
Serves 4.

title: sinkhole stew
directions: If using oysters, make sure any shell particles are removed. In large saucepan, cook onion and celery in margarine until tender.
Add mushrooms and cook for one minute.
Over low heat, stir flour, salt and pepper into vegetable mixture.
Add milk gradually until thickened, being careful not to boil.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Add crab (or oysters), soup, pimento and hot pepper sauce.
Over low heat, cook for 5 to 10 minutes or until oysters begin to curl.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: the bible cake
directions: Cream a and b. Beat c and d until frothy; add e, mixing well. Add to creamed mixture and beat thoroughly.
Sift f with g and add to first mixture.
Chop h and i and sprinkle well with a little of f before adding j, 1 teaspoon each and beat 5 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Chop cabbage and place in greased baking dish.
Brown meat and onions.
Stir in rice and pour on top of cabbage.
Mix soup and water; pour over entire casserole mixture.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 325°.
Add a little water, if necessary.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Alternate layers of shrimp and onions in a very large jar with lid.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over shrimp. Marinate in fridge for at least 24 hours.
Turn jar over often. May be kept a week to 10 days.

title: bread pudding
directions: Scald milk; add bread cubes and butter.
Beat eggs and add sugar and salt.
Add milk mixture and vanilla to egg mixture. Pour into baking dish; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Place in pan of hot water and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: party sandwiches
directions: Melt in a 200° oven. Spread on bread and cover.

title: "no roll" pie shell
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt into a 9-inch pie pan.
Add milk to oil; whip with fork (in a cup).
Pour into flour mixture; blend with a fork.
Press evenly with fingers to line bottom of pan. Prick with fork.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: baked chicken with crackers
directions: Crush saltine crackers.
Dip chicken in mayonnaise, then in cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
You can add salt, pepper or garlic powder.
Also good on pork chops.

title: no cook banana pudding
directions: Mix instant pudding with 3 cups cold milk according to directions on the package. Add condensed milk and mix. Stir in Cool Whip and layer wafers and bananas. Can top with Cool Whip, too.

title: sweet potato flan(yields 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Put sugar, water and lemon juice in a small pan and boil until mixture caramelizes and turns light gold color. Pour in dish with straight sides and flat bottom. Rotate until it coats pan.
Use 2-quart pan.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Wash green peppers and cut off the tops.
Clean out insides with a teaspoon, then re-wash peppers.
In frying pan, brown ground beef.
Add onion.
Season to personal preference and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots (sliced) for 10 minutes.
Drain.
Melt butter; stir in brown sugar until dissolved.
Add carrots.
Cook over low-medium heat for 10 minutes, stirring often.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 6 people.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix
first
five ingredients.
Add rest and refrigerate overnight.	Serve over lettuce.
Also good made with shrimp.

title: pineapple bread
directions: In a bowl, sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Set aside.
Rinse raisins with boiling water and set aside.
In a bowl, gradually beat sugar and butter. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add drained raisins and nuts.

Sift in about half of the flour mixture. Stir, do not beat, until well moistened and fairly smooth. Add undrained pineapple. Stir in rest of flour quickly. Pour into greased and floured loaf pan. Sprinkle with a mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 60 to 70 minutes.
Makes a medium size loaf.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Combine in large bowl first four ingredients. Bring the next six ingredients to a boil. Pour over cabbage mixture. Seal. Do not stir for four hours. Keeps a long time in refrigerator.

title: seafood linguine(4 servings)
directions: Heat olive oil in heavy large skillet over medium-high heat. Add onion and garlic and saute until onion is golden brown, about 6 minutes.
Stir in flour and coriander and cook 1 minute.
Add wine and cream and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add shrimp and scallops and simmer until shrimp are cooked through, stirring occasionally, about 5 minutes.
Mix in parsley.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Pour over linguine and serve.

title: thalhimers' deviled crabs
directions: *Special crabmeat is taken from the body.
Since this recipe is so highly seasoned, use this or other (such as claw) less expensive types of crabmeat rather than lump or backfin.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix.
Sprinkle some cheese on top before baking.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Mix
potatoes,	mayonnaise, cheese and onions together. Season with
salt	and
pepper.
Place
in
x 9-inch Pyrex container. Top with crumbled bacon and sliced olives.	Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Place sheet of foil under it while it cooks. Serves 8.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients together and bake at 350° until done.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach and onion for 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Put in colander and mash gently.
In large bowl, combine soup, cheese and mayonnaise.
Add spinach and egg.
Top with buttered stuffing. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix together.
Pour in 1 1/2 gallon freezer and fill with milk up to 2-inches of top.
Freeze with salt and ice.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: molasses crumb cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients into crumbs.
Set aside 1 1/2 to 2 cups of crumbs for topping.
Into the rest of the crumbs, add remaining ingredients.
Blend with spatula and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 45 to 55 minutes.

title: quickie roll
directions: Combine all ingredients. Mix well and drop by spoonful into well greased muffin pan. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Makes 12 rolls.

title: red barbecue sauce
directions: Mix and boil. Simmer 30 minutes.

title: choco-scotch clusters
directions: Mix chocolate, butterscotch chips and peanut butter together in a double boiler over hot but not boiling water.
Stir until well blended.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies.
Stir until well coated.
Drop by tablespoon onto wax paper.
Let stand until cool.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Put peanut butter on crust in small piles and let sit for a while.
This will make it easier to spread.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Add boiling water to oats and Crisco. Allow to cool to lukewarm. Add molasses, salt and yeast (dissolved in lukewarm water) with 1 teaspoon sugar (to be sure yeast is good). Add flour to make stiff dough. Knead well.
Let rise until double in bulk. Knead very little.
Divide into 4 greased bread pans.
Let rise again.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°, then lower oven to 350° for another 15 minutes, being sure to turn.

title: pineapple cream cake
directions: Preheat oven 350 degrees. In large bowl combine the cake mix, eggs, mandarin oranges and the reserved pineapple juice. Add mayonnaise. With electric beater on medium speed, beet for about 5 min. or until well blended. Pour in 9x13 baking dish that has been coated with nonstick baking spray. Bake 25 to 30 min. until golden brown. Allow to cool in pan.

title: dahi murgh - chicken and yogurt curry(origin: india and pakistan)
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces or use chicken pieces of one kind: drumsticks, thighs or half breasts.
Put into container of electric blender the onion, garlic, ginger, fresh coriander or mint.
Blend to a smooth puree.

title: pepparkakor cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking soda and spices into a medium bowl.
Set aside.
Cream sugar and butter in a large bowl.
Add the egg, molasses and water.
Stir the dry ingredients into this mixture 1 cup at a time.
Cover and chill dough in the refrigerator for at least an hour.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle flour onto countertop and spread evenly.
Divide the dough into 2 balls. Roll each ball 1/8-inch thick.
Use cookie cutters to cut out shapes that are about the same size.
Put the cookies 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes, until lightly browned on the bottom.
Watch carefully, they burn easily. Cool on wax paper.

title: easy buns
directions: Place sugar milk, 2 cups flour and salt on bowl, beat 2 minutes. Add egg and shortening. Beat one minute. Add rest of flour. Stir until dough is formed. Raise dough about 20 minutes or till easy to handle. Form into biscuits. Let raise and bake at 350 degrees until golden brown. Can also be used for sweet rolls or coffee cake.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in saucepan; over low heat, bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate morsels until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into 12 x 9-inch buttered pan.

title: coconut pecan frosting
directions: Combine milk, sugar, eggs, butter and vanilla.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened, about 12 minutes.
Add coconut and pecans.
Spread between top and sides of German chocolate cake mix baked according to directions.
Yield: 4 cups.

title: quickie blender quiche
directions: Place eggs, baking mix and milk in blender and blend for 30 seconds.
Grease a 10-inch pie pan or quiche pan and spread cheese over bottom.
Pour blended mixture over cheese and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Filling will puff slightly and be golden brown on top.

title: egg nog
directions: Add a sprinkle of salt to the egg whites. Beat egg whites and set aside. Put sugar in a pot. Add egg yolks and stir. Add cream while stirring. Put on low fire while adding other cream. Add vanilla and nutmeg to your own taste. Cook for 20 to 25 minutes, constantly stirring. Add beaten egg whites while stirring for thickness.

title: snackin' reubens
directions: In a small bowl, combine corned beef and dressing.
Place on the bread slices.
Top with kraut, cheese and pickle.
Broil on baking sheet 5-inches from heat for 4 minutes, or until cheese melts.

title: cookie sheet cake
directions: Sift the first 3 ingredients together.
Boil the oleo, water and cocoa and pour over dry mixture.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to mixture.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Cream cheese and pineapple.
Add onion, pepper, salt and 1 cup pecans.
Chill for a while (about 1 hour), then form into a ball and roll in the other cup of pecans.

title: mama's biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients.
Add enough buttermilk to make stiff dough. Mix well.
Put on floured paper; mash out flat.
Cut out and put into greased pan.
Bake at 475° for 10 to 15 minutes, until done.

title: fresh fruit cake
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add milk and vanilla.
Pour into a greased and floured 9-inch pan.
Slice fresh fruit.
Lay it on batter. Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: relish
directions: Cut peppers in half and remove seeds.
Chop peppers and onions fine.
Pour boiling water over them; let stand 5 minutes.
Drain off water, again cover with boiling water; let stand 10 minutes. Pour into muslin bag and drain overnight.
Add vinegar, sugar and salt; boil 20 minutes.
While hot, pour into sterile jars and seal. Makes about 3 pints.

title: cake that won't last
directions: Mix all ingredients well together.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: marinated tofu
directions: Cover bottom of dish or pan with tamara and add 1 or 2 tablespoons of water (depends on amount of tofu used and size of pan).
Add spices.
Place tofu in marinade for 10 to 15 minutes, turning occasionally.
Heat small amount of oil in skillet (cover bottom).
Saut over medium heat until brown on both sides.
For a savory sauce, add a little water and remaining marinade to skillet. Heat and serve over tofu or accompanying food.
For a more robust flavor, you may add any of the following:
chili powder, parsley flakes, canola, soy or olive oil, paprika, oregano, lemon juice.

title: betty's california chicken
directions: Boil chicken breasts with skin and bones and salt, pepper and onions.
Cool and pick out the white meat.
Add flour to cool broth.
Bring to a boil while stirring.
Add heavy cream, drained peas and carrots and chicken pieces.

title: potatoes and chicken rosemary
directions: Microwave the potatoes 8 to 10 minutes until tender. While potatoes cook, in a large skillet, toss and brown chicken and garlic in oil over high heat 5 minutes. Add potatoes and rosemary. Saute and toss until potatoes are lightly brown.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Cream butter and
crunchy
peanut butter; gradually add sugar, beating at medium
speed
of
an
electric	mixer until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Stir in
flour,
blending
well.
Stir
in vanilla, chocolate morsels and
chopped
pecans.
Spoon
batter
into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch	pan.
Bake
at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Cut
into	2 x 1 1/2-inch bars. Yields 3 dozen.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix water, sugar, vinegar and ketchup.
Bring to a boil, then add flour mixture.
(Mix flour with water to make a medium texture, probably 1/3 cup of each.)

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and oil and mix well. Add dry ingredients and continue mixing well.
Take one teaspoonful of dough and roll it into a ball.
Dip ball in sugar and press it down on cookie sheet with fork or decorative glass.
Do not grease cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Pound out chicken until flat.
Place 1 slice ham and 1 slice cheese on bottom half of chicken.
Fold over.
Press edges to seal; sprinkle cornstarch over.
Melt butter over high heat.
Add chicken; cook 3 minutes on each side.
Serve with lemon.

title: annette's grilled teriyaki chicken
directions: Combine cooking oil and margarine in a large pot and heat. When oil is hot, add onions.
Saute onion mixture until tender and transparent.
Add garlic powder and black pepper.
Stir well to blend seasoning.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Simmer for 20 minutes until a red gray sauce forms.
Cook 10 minutes more.
Set aside.

title: pickled red beets
directions: Cook red beets; peel, cut and put in quart jar with cinnamon and cloves.
Boil rest of ingredients for 1 minute.
Pour into jars and put jars in pots of water for 30 minutes and seal.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in saucepan. Add water and cook until very thick and clear. Add jello. Let cool. Add strawberries. Toss to coat. Pour into pie shell. Chill.

title: bread pudding
directions: Put brown sugar in bottom of double boiler; break one slice of bread over sugar.
Add raisins.
Break another slice of bread over ingredients.
In bowl, mix egg, milk, salt and vanilla and turn over bread mixture.
Cook until knife comes out clean.
Turn out onto a large plate with a lot of delicious brown sugar syrup.

title: stuffed green pepper soup
directions: Place all ingredients in a slow cooker and cook overnight on the low setting.

title: mama hara's working girl batter rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and mix all other ingredients well.
Spoon batter into greased muffin tins and bake at 350°. This batter will keep well in the refrigerator if kept well covered.

title: dirty rice
directions: Cook rice as directed on package and set aside.
Saute chicken livers.
Cool and chop fine.
In heavy pan, cook sausage for 5 minutes.
Add vegetables and cook until onions are transparent. Add salt, sage and chicken broth.
Simmer for 30 minutes over low heat.
Add chicken livers and remove from heat.
Mix well.
Cover and let set for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: potato soup
directions: In large pot, bring water to boil. Add frozen vegetable mix and broccoli; return to boil. Add frozen hash browns, bouillon cubes and onion. Simmer 3 minutes. Add chicken soup, milk, cheese, black pepper and white chicken. Stir until cheese is melted. Serves 10 to 15.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and put in casserole.
Top with 1 cup of shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake, uncovered, about 1 hour at 350°.

title: tomato soup florentine
directions: Cook rice first, then add to remaining ingredients.
Cook until spinach is done.

title: autumn fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add cracker crumbs, pineapple, coconut and baking powder; mix well.
Then add nuts.
Bake in greased tube pan for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°.
When cake is cool, ice with following:

title: potato dish
directions: Mix all together; cover with 2 cups of crushed potato chips and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes, then uncover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: apple crisp
directions: Arrange apples in buttered 9-inch pie pan.
Combine brown sugar, flour, oats and cinnamon; cut in margarine until crumbly. Press mixture over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until top is browned.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: skillet spanish rice
directions: In large skillet, put onion, green pepper, garlic, rice and hamburger.
Stir over high heat until lightly browned.
Add the tomato sauce and remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Mix well and bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese over top before serving.
Serves 6.

title: harbor banana bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and pinch of salt.
Rinse raisins and dry well.
Chop apricots.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Chop nuts and fruit well.
Flour all fruit with the 3/4 cup flour; set aside.
Cream butter and brown sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift the dry ingredients together and add to sugar and butter mixture.
Fold the nuts, fruit, milk and wine into mixture; mix well.
Drop by tablespoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: roll-out cookies
directions: Pre-heat oven to 400°.
Cream butter and sugar, beat in egg and vanilla. Mix baking powder and flour, add to creamed mixture one cup at a time, mixing after each addition.
The dough will be very stiff; blend last flour in by hand (if dough becomes too stiff, add water a teaspoon at a time).
Do not child dough.
Roll out on a floured surface to 1/8 inch thick.
Dip cutters into flour before each use.
Bake cookies on an ungreased cookie sheet on top rack of oven for 6-8 minutes until cookies are lightly browned.

title: pasta salad
directions: Pour dressing and vinegar over the other ingredients. Mix thoroughly and refrigerate at least 4 hours. Mix before serving.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Combine yeast, 2 cups water, 3/4 cup sugar and 3 tablespoons instant potato flakes in bowl; mix well.
Let stand, loosely covered, at room temperature for 8 hours to 1 week.
Feed starter once a week or more frequently if necessary.
Feed with 3/4 cup sugar, 1 cup water and 3 tablespoons instant potato flakes; mix well.
Let stand 8 hours or more before using.

title: honey-ginger-bourbon balls
directions: Combine crumbs, 1 cup sugar and nuts in a large bowl.
Combine chocolate and honey in small bowl over hot water.
Stir until chocolate is melted.
Blend in bourbon.
Stir bourbon mixture into crumb mixture until well blended.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Sprinkle remaining powdered sugar over balls.
Refrigerate until firm.
Makes about 4 dozen balls.

title: carrot salad
directions: Grate carrots.
Drain pineapple and mix together and add raisins.
Put marshmallows and about 1/2 cup mayonnaise and a little pineapple juice in a saucepan and melt, stirring all the time to keep from sticking.
Pour over carrots and let chill.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into strips, dredge in flour.	Brown meat in butter in a skillet.	Add onion; saut until a little brown.	Add remaining ingredients except sour cream and noodles.	Cover tightly and cook until meat is tender 1-2 hours.
Add sour cream, heat slightly.
Do not boil.
Serve on noodles or rice.

title: corn and chicken dinner(yields 8 servings)
directions: In a Dutch oven or large skillet over medium-high heat, saute 2 of the garlic cloves in 2 tablespoons butter.
Add the chicken and brown on both sides.
Reduce heat.
Add corn and water.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon tarragon, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix lemon cake mix, 1 egg and 1 stick of butter. Press mixture with fingers into 9 x 13 pan.

title: strawberry cake and icing
directions: Mix together all ingredients for 4 minutes. Pour into 3 round cake pans or an oblong 13 x 9 inch pan and bake at 325° for 30 - 40 minutes.

title: coleslaw
directions: In a
large bowl, combine the cabbage and carrots.
Mix rest of
ingredients and pour over cabbage mixture.
Stir well and refrigerate at least 30 minutes before serving.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook butter, sugar and milk.
After it starts to boil, time it for 4 minutes.
Do not overcook; it will turn to sugar.
Remove from heat.
Add Marshmallow, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until creamy.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and enjoy.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook hamburg; drain and mix in taco mix.
Let cool.
Shred lettuce.
Chop tomato and onion and mix in large bowl with cheese. Crush chips and mix in bowl.
Add cooled hamburg.
Mix in dressing when ready to eat.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Use ungreased baking dish.
Put chicken in bottom and then add broccoli.
Cover with cheese, soup and milk.
Top with crumbs. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: canned green tomatoes
directions: Slice green tomatoes; pack in jars and fill with water.
Add 1 teaspoon canning salt.
Place in open top canner; bring water in canner to a boil, then time for 20 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Stir the first 4 ingredients together, then add remaining ingredients.
May substitute other fruit, such as mandarin oranges, fruit cocktail, blueberries, strawberries, etc.
Also cooked rice could be added.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken.
Cut off bone and into pieces.
Save 1 1/2 cups chicken broth.
Combine chicken, broth, soup and vegetables.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Mix together milk and flour.
Add margarine and stir well.
Pour over entire top of chicken mixture. Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown and bubbly.

title: zucchini corn bread bake
directions: Coarsely shred enough zucchini to make 1/3 cup; set aside. Cut remaining zucchini into 1/4-inch slices.
In a 10-inch skillet brown sausage.
Remove from skillet and reserve drippings.
To the drippings add the zucchini slices and the onion, stirring to coat. Cover and cook over medium-low heat for about 5 minutes or until the zucchini is slightly softened, stirring twice.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Melt oleo for 45 seconds.
Stir in eggs and sugar.
Microwave 6 minutes.
Stir in pineapple; set aside.

title: puppy chow(for adults and children)
directions: Place powdered sugar in large paper grocery bag.
Mix cereal and peanuts.
Mix chips, peanut butter and butter.
Melt in microwave (High) 20 seconds or stove top 3 minutes.
Pour over cereal and nuts and mix (be gentle).
Pour into paper bag.
Shake, Shake, Shake.
Pour out on waxed paper to dry.
Store in sealed container.
Servings:

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Place chicken in a baking dish (10 x 10-inch).
Mix soup, mayonnaise and 1/2 cup broth with chopped onion.
Pour over chicken.
Crumble cornbread and add black pepper (heavy).
Moisten with remainder of chicken broth.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.

title: made from scratch pizza
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in sugar, salt, oil and 2 cups flour.
Mix well.
Add 1 1/2 cups more flour.
Knead several times to work in flour.
Shape into ball and oil surface lightly. Cover and let rise 30 minutes.
Mix tomato paste, water, salt, oregano, parsley and anise to make sauce.
Roll crust very thin and put on greased pizza pans.
Spread on sauce.
Add hamburger and/or sausage, onions, peppers, mushrooms, etc. may be added. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift plain flour and baking powder together.
Stir in flour and milk a little at a time, beating well after each. Add flavoring and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: apple-oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a medium bowl, combine oats, flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Stir to combine. Stir in raisins and apples.
In a large bowl, combine egg, honey, oil and milk.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Mix to form a smooth batter.
Drop batter onto ungreased baking cookie sheet using a rounded teaspoonful of dough for each cookie.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly golden.

title: stir-fry vegetables
directions: Heat oil in wok or skillet; add onion.
Saute until limp.
Add vegetables; cook until limp or to desired doneness.
Add meat. Stir until heated (3 to 4 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Let stand 4 or 5 minutes to heat and blend flavors.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix chopped nuts and coconut.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix as directed on package.
Pour over mixture in pan.
Mix cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Spoon over cake mix.
Bake at 350° approximately 45 minutes.

title: favorite chili rellenos
directions: Place half the chili peppers in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Top with cheeses and remaining peppers.
Blend eggs with evaporated milk in a bowl; pour over layers.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Serve with salsa.
Yields 6 servings.

title: pineapple custard
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and cook.
After the pudding is cooked, add pineapple.
Use egg whites for meringue.
Put in baked pie shell and bake meringue.

title: make-ahead spaghetti supreme
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions. Drain.
Brown meat, then stir in spaghetti sauce, salt and pepper to taste. Remove from heat. Combine cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream and green onion.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer half of the spaghetti and cover with all the cheese mixture.
Add remaining spaghetti and pour butter over top.
Spread meat sauce over top. Add Cheddar cheese over entire top. Chill up to 24 hours or bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
If refrigerated, remove 5 to 10 minutes before baking.

title: chicken breasts and orange sauce
directions: Blend flour, salt and seasonings. Coat chicken with flour mixture. Heat oil in pan; brown chicken well. Add other ingredients; cover and cook on low (225°) about 30 minutes, until tender. About 15 minutes after cooking chicken, add carrots, sliced, if desired.

title: rainbow chicken kabobs
directions: Arrange chicken and peppers alternately on four 10 to 12-inch skewers.
Brush with 1/4 cup of the dressing; cover.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour or overnight to marinate.
Preheat grill to medium heat.
Place kabobs on grill.
Grill 12 to 15 minutes or until chicken is cooked through, turning and brushing occasionally with remaining 1/4 cup dressing.

title: stuffed crabmeat(hor d'oeuvres)
directions: Combine first eight ingredients.
Mix well.
Separate biscuits into 24 sections.
Fit biscuits into small muffin pans (tassie pan).
Fill with crabmeat mixture and sprinkle with paprika.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Combine and pour in tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: quick and easy punch
directions: Cut the orange sherbet in half and place in punch bowl.
Chop up sherbet with knife or spoon.
Pour one can Hawaiian Punch over sherbet.
Pour one 2-liter bottle of Sprite over sherbet and Hawaiian Punch.
Will foam up pink.
Makes 2 punch bowls full.

title: treasure chest bars
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Set aside.
Cream together brown and white sugars and butter.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating after each.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Drain cherries, saving juice.
Add nuts, chocolate chips and cherries.
Bake in jelly roll pan at 325° for 30 minutes.
Make frosting with powdered sugar and cherry juice.
Frost while still warm.

title: creamy fruit salad
directions: Combine sour cream and Cool Whip.
Combine fruits and coconut. Stir in the sour cream mixture.
Chill, covered, 2 to 24 hours before serving.
Stir and sprinkle with toasted coconut, if desired.

title: sweet and sour carrot salad
directions: Peel and slice carrots; cook until tender.
Drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain well.
Add green pepper and onion.
Mix together tomato soup, sugar, salad oil, vinegar, pepper, salt and mustard. Pour over vegetables and cover and set overnight.
Stir before serving.

title: khoresh baden jan(kho' resh ba' den joon; eggplant casserole)
directions: Remove stem from eggplant and cut in half widthwise.
Cut smaller half into 4 to 6 pieces and larger half into 6 to 8 pieces. Combine 4 to 5 cups water, 1/4 cup salt and cut eggplant.
Soak at least 20 minutes to remove the bitterness of the eggplant.
Drain water and dry eggplant with paper towel.
Rinse meat.
Saute in a saucepan with 1 tablespoon oil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add 4 cups water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat allowing meat to cook slowly.
While meat is cooking, saute onions until golden brown. Remove and drain as well as possible onto paper towels.
Saute eggplant until golden turning to ensure even frying.
Again drain onto paper towels.
When meat is almost cooked (approximately 1 cup water is left) add tomato sauce, onions, salt, pepper and cinnamon. Cook on medium heat for 10 to 15 minutes.
At this point, the meat should be fully cooked.
Line eggplant on one side of a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Likewise, line the meat on the other side.
Pour the sauce (there should be at least 2 cups) over the eggplant and meat. Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 250° for an additional 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: play dough recipe
directions: Add just enough water to make it the consistency of bread dough (too sticky, add flour).
Add a sprinkle of food coloring or dried tempera.
For smell, add cinnamon or nutmeg (or 2 drops of cloves for preservation).
Store in plastic bag for 1 month.

title: arroz con pollo
directions: Saute achiotes in oil until oil is well colored. Remove achiotes and discard. Cook chickens in oil until brown. Add remaining ingredients, except rice, and simmer for 1 hour or until tender. Remove chicken. Add rice and simmer until cooked. Add chicken and reheat.

title: cheese and tomato pie
directions: Grate cheese and toss with flour.
Saute onion in butter until golden.
Spread approximately 1/2 of cheese over bottom of pie shell, then spread onion over cheese.
In butter left in pan, heat tomatoes with basil for two minutes.
Arrange tomato slices over onion, then cover with remaining cheese.
Beat eggs with milk or cream and pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until firm.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Mix lemon cake mix, butter and 1 egg until very stiff.
Grease oblong pan; press mix into bottom of pan until flat.
Blend lemon icing and cream cheese until softened.
Set 1 cup aside for icing, then add 2 eggs and beat 3 to 5 minutes.
Pour over cake and spread.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool for 20 minutes and frost with remaining cup of icing.

title: dump cake
directions: Put pineapple and cherry in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour dry mix over (do not stir).
Pour melted butter over top, then chopped nuts. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: bing cherry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Divide between two graham cracker crusts and chill until set.

title: microwave caramel breakfast ring
directions: In a 6-cup plastic ring mold or 1-quart glass dish, add brown sugar, butter, water and cinnamon.
Heat 1 minute.
Blend the ingredients and stir in nuts.
Separate biscuits; arrange in an overlapping ring (or for a crowd, cut each biscuit into quarters). Spoon the caramel mixture over biscuits (or stir to coat).
Push biscuits to sides of dish, placing a small glass in the center. Microwave (High) for 2 to 3 minutes, rotating 1/4 turn halfway through cooking.
Rest 2 to 3 minutes.
Biscuits should be firm not doughy or tough.
Remove glass from center, invert on serving plate.
Serve warm by pulling sections apart.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: noodles chicken divan
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Add red pepper, scallions and broccoli.
Cook, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes.
Stir in chicken broth, cream, noodles and chicken. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer over low heat 25 to 30 minutes or until noodles are tender.

title: broccoli and cauliflower soup
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in 1 1/2 quarts boiling water.
Add potatoes, celery and onion.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add carrots, broccoli and cauliflower.
Cook until tender.
Add 2 cans of soup (undiluted).
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add cheese; stir until melted.

title: cottage cheese and potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, celery, green pepper, pimiento, onion and pickle.
Toss ingredients lightly and chill.

title: peppermint microwave candy
directions: Crush mints in blender until fine.
Melt white chocolate in microwave on 70% power for 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir to finish melting.
Add mints and food coloring.
Stir.
Pour onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Spread as thinly as desired.
Cool completely and break into pieces.
Store in airtight containers.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Melt Provolone cheese in top of double boiler over boiling water.
Add American cheese and stir in heavy cream.
Add cream cheese and stir until all cheeses are melted.
Remove from heat and beat in seasonings and yellow food coloring.
Serve warm with crackers or fresh vegetables.

title: baked alaska
directions: Trim cake leaving 1 inch larger on all sides than ice cream. Place on wooden cutting board or cookie sheet.
(A strip of wax paper under cake will help you slip dessert onto plate later.)

title: corn meal dumplings
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients. Add water to make thick pancake-like consistency. Form into cakes and drop into pot.

title: party hot wieners
directions: Cut wieners in bite size pieces.
Put banana peppers and vinegar in saucepan and start to simmer.
Add cut up wieners to this mixture.
Simmer about 15 minutes.
Let them set for awhile before serving.

title: pudding cake
directions: Melt butter; add flour and mix.
Add nuts.
Press in tin pan and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: dreamy cinnamon breakfast rolls
directions: Mix cake as directed on box. Add 2 cups flour. Beat 3 minutes with mixer, then stir in as much of the remaining flour with wooden spoon. Knead on floured board about 3 minutes. Place in large greased bowl. Let rise for 1 hour. Punch down and divide in half. Cover and let stand 10 minutes. Roll each half and spread with butter, sugar and cinnamon. Roll up like a jelly roll. Cut in 1-inch pieces. Place in two 13 x 9-inch pans.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Spread cream cheese thinly over individual ham slices. Sprinkle green onions on cream cheese and roll ham up like a jelly roll.
Cut ham roll into about 1/2-inch wheels.
Spear wheels with toothpicks.
Arrange on a platter and garnish with parsley.

title: never fail biscuits
directions: Stir ingredients together in a medium bowl.
Blend well.
Spoon into muffin pan.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.
Yield:
6 biscuits.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Stir in eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° until firm and brown.

title: no-weep meringue
directions: Combine and cook over low heat until it turns white; cool. Beat 3 egg whites very stiff, then fold in cooled mixture.
Spread on pie and brown in oven at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken and bulgur
directions: Saute vegetables in oil until onions are soft.
Stir in bulgur, coat well with oil.
When sizzling add chicken broth and bring to a boil.
Stir well, cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add chicken and water if needed.
Simmer 5 minutes or until chicken is hot.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Cover bottom of 11 x 15-inch pan with graham cracker crust. Reserve 1/3 cup crumbs.
Slice bananas crosswise and layer over crust.
Slice ice cream 1/2-inch thick and place over bananas. Sprinkle ice cream and place over bananas.
Sprinkle ice cream with nuts.
Freeze until firm.
Melt chocolate chips and butter.
Add powdered sugar and evaporated milk.
Cook mixture until thick and smooth.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Cool chocolate mixture. Pour over ice cream.
Freeze until stiff.
Whip cream until stiff. Spread over chocolate and reserved crumbs.
Store in freezer. Remove 10 minutes before serving.

title: orange feather sponge cake
directions: Cream 4 yolks with sugar.
Add orange juice, flour and baking powder.
