Add water and vanilla.
Fold in 5 beaten egg whites. Line tube pan with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn pan upside down until cool.

title: barbecue marinade
directions: Mix ingredients in a quart jar.
Pour over meat.
Refrigerate and marinate 24 to 36 hours, turning meat occasionally.

title: easy baked chicken(low-fat)
directions: Prepare chicken for cooking.
Cut into pieces.
Remove skin if you desire.
Pat dry.
Season lightly with salt and pepper.
Dip into buttermilk.
On wax paper, crush enough stuffing mix to thoroughly coat chicken pieces.
Place in baking dish or pan. Cover.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer or until lightly browned.
(I frequently set oven timer and place this in oven shortly before leaving for church.)

title: lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna, adding cooking oil to prevent sticking.
Drain. Cook beef, onion and garlic together; brown.
Add tomato paste, tomatoes, salt, pepper, basil and oregano.
Cook over low heat until starts to thicken, about 15 minutes.
Grease a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Arrange layers of ingredients as follows: tomato-meat mixture, Parmesan cheese, noodles, Mozzarella and Ricotta.
Repeat layers, ending with meat mixture and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: coat of many colors bread
directions: Make three separate batches.

title: better than shoney's potato soup
directions: Using a 5-quart Dutch oven, melt margarine.
Add onion and celery (this should fill about 1/3 of the pan) and saute until tender.
Add potatoes and enough water to cook.
Simmer, covered, until potatoes are cooked.
Add evaporated milk and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook about 10 minutes.
Add regular milk to make the consistency you like.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Slowly blend in flour over low heat.
Add hominy. Pour in greased casserole dish.
Put cracker crumbs on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: angel flake biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water; set aside.
Mix sugar, flour and shortening with a fork.
Pour in yeast mixture, then pour in buttermilk and mix well.
Add extra flour if you need it to get dough ready to roll out.
Cut out biscuits and place on greased pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from oven to butter.
Makes 20 large biscuits.

title: strawberry-rhubarb pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt, tapioca, nutmeg and lemon juice in a large bowl.
Add rhubarb and strawberries.
Mix well to coat fruit.
Let stand 15 to 20 minutes.
Place fruit mixture in prepared bottom crust.
Dot with butter.
Add top crust; crimp edges and cut holes to vent steam.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes in 350° oven.

title: no bake orange cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients, except decorations.
Shape into balls; roll in decorations.
Store to mellow.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread refried beans (right out of can) on platter, then spread sour cream on top of that; next, spread picante sauce, then chopped green onions, then chopped tomatoes, then grated cheese; in that order.
You can spread as little or as much of each item as you like.
Then use your favorite chips to dip with.

title: pecan pie
directions: Bake pie crust for a few minutes.
Place pecans in crust. Blend all ingredients; pour over pecans.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then lower oven temperature to 350°.
Bake for 35 minutes more.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375.
Mix thoroughly shortening, butter, sugars, eggs, and vanilla.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoons 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 - 10 mins. or until light brown.
Cool sightly before removing. Makes 7 dozen.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saute onion in butter; add to bread.
Stir well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan (greased).
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Place on greased, flat casserole dish.
Add an additional 1/4 cup melted margarine or butter over top.
Optional:
Sprinkle top with Rice Krispies. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mud pies
directions: Put Oreos in the bag.
Crush Oreos.
Put a little bit in the bowl.
Put a little bit of pudding the bowl.
Put some more Oreos in the bowl.
Keep on doing this until they are both gone.
Put the prezel in the bowl.
Put some of the frosting on the end of the prezel.
Put the flower on the prezel.
Then put the worm in the bowl.
Then you have your mud pies!

title: baked potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except bacon. Pour into a greased 9x13 pan. Sprinkle with bacon. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: smoked salmon mold
directions: Beat salmon with softened cream cheese, lemon juice, onion, horseradish, liquid smoke and salt until well blended. Refrigerate mixture until firm enough to shape into ball.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Wrap and refrigerate again until serving time. Serve with crackers.

title: the impossible pie
directions: Put everything in a blender or mixer.
Pour into a 9-inch pie buttered pie plate.
Bake until custard sets at 400°, about 25 or 30 minutes.
Serve cold.
It makes its own crust, custard and topping.

title: homemade chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix well.
Pour into ice cream churn, then add enough sweet milk to fill churn.

title: italian delight
directions: Cook pasta in water with the bouillon cube until tender.
Fry out ground beef with onion until onion is limp or lightly brown. Drain off any fat.
Place cooked pasta in a 2 to 3-quart casserole after draining.
Mix and add other ingredients. Sprinkle about another 1/4 pound cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato dumplings-boiled
directions: Peel potatoes and grate fine.
Strain through clean cloth, squeezing fairly dry.

Allow strained liquid to settle, then pour off liquid carefully until only the white potato starch remains. Add starch to grated potato which has been mixed with onion, egg, flour and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well.
Shape into patties or balls.
Drop into salted boiling water.
Boil 1/2 hour.
Remove from water and let drain.

title: beefed up cornbread
directions: Make cornbread per package directions.
That's where the egg and milk come in.
You can also use your own cornbread recipe if you want to work that hard.
Add 1 seeded jalapeno pepper to your own cornbread.
Add corn; mix thoroughly.
Put half the batter in a large greased skillet or lasagne pan and spread it on the bottom. Spread the crumbled cooked meat over the cornbread mixture.
Spread both the onions and peppers into the pan.
(If you have any leftover peas, carrots or green beans, add them also.
I don't recommend adding leftover corn, that's a bit much!)
Spread the shredded cheese over the concoction in the pan.
Pour the rest of the cornbread batter on the top.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes. Enjoy!

title: hamburger and sausage sandwich
directions: Cook hamburger, sliced sausage, sliced onion and green pepper over low heat, with cover on pan.
Drain off fat and add spaghetti sauce and red pepper.
May not need whole jar of sauce.
Heat to eating temperature.
Spoon into hot dog rolls.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix well.
Place in serving bowl.
Serve with cut fresh fruit.

title: macaroni salad(holiday tradition!)
directions: Boil elbow macaroni in 1/2 teaspoon salt just until done (do not overcook).
Drain.
Mix with the shredded shrimp and shrimp liquid, diced egg and celery; let set covered with foil in refrigerator overnight.
If dry, add additional mayonnaise next day.

title: fried shrimp
directions: Mix together flour, salt and sugar.
Add ice water, egg and oil (you may have to use more or less water to get the right thickness).
Beat smooth.
Dip peeled shrimp into batter.
Fry in deep, hot fat until golden brown.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Combine flour, sugar and milk in a bowl; mix until moistened. Pour into a 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Arrange peaches on top of batter.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Crust will rise to top.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Melt sugar, salt in frypan; add soda.
Remove from heat.
Pour over nuts on a lightly greased cookie sheet or pizza pan.
Let it harden; break into small pieces.

title: pizza snacks
directions: Place English muffins on a paper plate or a paper towel lined dinner plate. Brush each with catsup.
Layer with 4 pieces of pepperoni and 2 tablespoons Mozzarella cheese.
Mix together the Parmesan cheese and Italian seasoning.
Sprinkle over each English muffin half.
Microwave on High (100%) for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until cheese just begins to melt.
Recipe yields 4 servings.

title: pork bones with sauerkraut
directions: Line up the bones in a single layer in the bottom of a 6-quart kettle.
Top with a layer of cabbage and then a layer of drained (not rinsed) sauerkraut.
Repeat the layers, sprinkling each with a few caraway seed and a little pepper.
Salt only if sauerkraut is not salty.

title: hopscotch jumbles
directions: Melt peanut butter and butterscotch bits in double boiler over hot water.
Remove from heat.
Stir in noodles and marshmallows. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Chill until set.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together sugar, salad oil and eggs.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and allspice and add to sugar mixture.
Then add water, pumpkin and nuts.
Grease and flour 2 bread pans and fill each 1/2 full.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.
Cool on wire racks.

title: sweet coconut pie
directions: Melt chocolate with butter in saucepan over very low heat, stirring constantly, until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in eggs, sugar, flour and vanilla.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan. Combine milk and coconut; spoon over chocolate mixture, leaving 1/2-inch to 1-inch border.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: peanut butter kiss cookies
directions: Mix flour, soda and salt.
Cream together sugars, shortening and peanut butter.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Mix until creamy. Add flour gradually and mix well.

title: broccoli chicken
directions: Cook chicken and debone. Cook broccoli. Mix soup, curry powder and mayonnaise. Layer chicken and broccoli in a casserole dish and pour soup mixture over it. Bake at 300° for 1 hour. Top with grated cheese and bread crumbs. Brown on broil 1 to 2 minutes.

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix everything together.
Put in baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: mile high strawberry pie
directions: Mix flour with brown sugar.
Cut in margarine as for pie crust.
Stir in pecans.
Spread crumbs in 9 x 13-inch pan (do not pat).
Bake 15 minutes at 325°.
Stir twice with fork during baking.
Remove 1/2 cup crumbs for top.
Beat egg whites to form soft peaks.
Add strawberries and juice, lemon juice and sugar. Beat with mixer for 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pile mixture over crumbs in pan.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 crumbs over all. Freeze until firm.
(Will keep.)

title: hamburger slices
directions: Wash cucumbers and slice.
Add sliced onions.
Sprinkle salt over.
Now mix a tray of ice cubes through pickles and onions. Put another tray of ice on top and let stand 3 hours.
You may need more ice.
This ice, salt water makes pickles especially crisp.
Drain cucumbers, discarding ice water.
Combine vinegar, sugar and spices; bring to a boil.
Add cucumbers and boil 8 to 10 minutes.
Put into jars and seal.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Put sugar, margarine, cocoa and milk in nonstick boiler and bring to a rolling boil for 1 minute.
Stir in oatmeal, peanut butter, vanilla and pecans quickly.
Drop with spoon onto wax paper.

title: cherry nut surprise
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish with butter.
Mix pineapple and cherries and pour in baking dish.
Spread by handfuls the dry cake mix on top of fruit. Sprinkle with nuts.
Pour melted butter over top of cake.
Bake until golden brown.
Good warm or cold.

title: peach pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into pie shell (double crust).
Add top crust and seal.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° for 45 minutes or longer if needed.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes and combine with all other ingredients except 1/2 cup melted margarine and corn flakes.
Put in large casserole dish. Combine the 1/2 cup melted margarine and corn flakes.
Spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken and stuffing
directions: Place chicken breasts in the bottom of a 9 x 12 cake pan. Mix soups and sour cream. Pour over chicken. Pour stuffing on top of soup. Melt butter and mix with chicken broth. Pour over stuffing. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: sinful salad
directions: Combine jello and water; stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Add bananas, pecans, strawberries and pineapple to jello.
Stir well. Pour 1/2 of mixture into a 12 x 8-inch dish.
Refrigerate until set, 1 hour.
Keep remaining jello mixture at room temperature. Spread sour cream evenly over set jello.
Pour remaining jello over sour cream.
Cover and chill 1 1/2 hours.

title: double chocolate brownies(makes 32 bars)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In mixing bowl, blend Crisco and sugar; beat in eggs and vanilla.
Blend in chocolate syrup, flour and salt; stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool slightly, about 5 minutes.
Top with Quick Frosting.
Cool and cut into bars.
Makes 32 brownies.

title: walnut toffee bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In medium bowl, combine flour and sugar; cut in margarine until crumbly.
Press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes. Meanwhile, in large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk, egg and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in candy pieces and walnuts.
Spread evenly over prepared crust.
Bake 25 minutes or until golden brown. Cool.
Cut into bars.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: neiman-marcus cookies
directions: Mix together, then spoon on cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer all ingredients.
Do not stir or toss.
Cover tightly overnight.
Before serving, toss with a bottle of creamy Italian salad dressing.

title: lemon muffins
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream the butter and sugar. Add egg yolks.
Add flour mixture alternately with lemon juice. Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold into batter with lemon peel.
Fill lightly greased muffin pan 3/4 full.
Mix cinnamon and sugar. Sprinkle 1/2 teaspoon over each muffin. Bake at 375° about 25 minutes.
Makes about 10 muffins.

title: hamburger pie with french fry crust
directions: Cook celery and onions in butter until tender.
Add hamburger and brown lightly.
Add soup, catsup, salt and pepper.
Pour into 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange French fries over top.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until potatoes are brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Combine flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda and sugar in a large bowl.
Add butter and cut in with a knife until crumbly or use pastry blender.
Add raisins and caraway seed.
Mix eggs with buttermilk and blend with dry ingredients.
Divide dough in half and shape into 2 round loaves.
Place in an 8-inch cake and pie tin.
Cut crosses on top.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine popcorn and almonds in large microwaveable bowl.
In 4-cup microwaveable measuring cup, combine brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir. Microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes or until mixture comes to a rolling boil.
Stir in baking soda; pour over popcorn and almonds. Mix well.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Spread on foil or waxed paper to cool.
Makes 6 cups.
Yum!

title: richard's tomato chili sauce
directions: Chop vegetables and mix well with other ingredients.
Cook until it thickens, stirring occasionally.
Put in jars and seal.

title: stewed chicken in gravy
directions: Cut
chicken
into
frying pieces.
Pour soup and water into large saucepan.
Add chicken and a dash of pepper.
Cover and simmer until tender, about 1 hour.
Add butter during last 10 minutes of cooking.
The combination of the chicken flavor with the
other
ingredients
will
yield
a delicious stewed chicken with
a rich savory gravy.
Serve in a large crockery dish, piping hot.
Hot split biscuits or rolls make an excellent base for smothering with this delicious gravy.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Stir in next 8 ingredients.
Simmer uncovered 30 minutes.
Add brown hamburger and simmer 30 minutes or longer.

title: reception punch
directions: Boil 2 cups water and sugar until sugar is completely dissolved; cool.
Mix juices, 3 cans water and sugar syrup, stirring well.
Add soda water, ginger ale and ice ring just before serving.
A few thin slices of orange and fruited ice rings will add color.
Yield: 20 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli in a small amount of water.
Drain.
In a mixing bowl, add the sour cream, soup (undiluted), onion, broccoli, dabs of butter and a little of bread crumbs.
Butter baking dish.
Pour mixture into dish.
In small pan, melt 1 stick butter; toss in bread crumbs until coated.
Put coated bread crumbs on mixture. Cover dish and bake until bubbly at 300°.

title: sweet potatoes in sherry sauce
directions: Arrange potatoes in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle lightly with salt. In a saucepan, mix brown sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Blend in orange juice. Add raisins. Cook and stir over high heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Mix in sherry, walnuts and orange peel.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until potatoes are well drained.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook hamburger and onions; drain off grease.
Cook squash. Cook rice.
Mix all ingredients together.
Heat through in microwave or in oven.
Stir and serve.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Place cream cheese on platter.
If using fresh or frozen shrimp, cut into small pieces.
If using canned shrimp, drain and rise.
Add shrimp and sauce together.
Spoon over cream cheese. Serve with crackers.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll out biscuits.
Fill each with chopped apples.
Fold over and seal.
Heat in saucepan the soda, sugar, apple pie spice and margarine.
Put the dumplings in a greased baking pan.
Pour the apple mixture over the dumplings.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: farmhouse barbecue muffin cups
directions: Separate dough into 10 biscuits; flatten into 5-inch circles and press into bottom and sides of greased muffin cups.
Set aside.
In skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
In small bowl, mix catsup, brown sugar, vinegar and chili powder; stir until smooth. Add to meat and mix well.
Divide between biscuit lined cups, about 1/4 cup each.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes or until golden.
Cool 5 minutes before removing from tins.
Makes 10 servings.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in an 11 x 13-inch pan.
Add remaining ingredients (except milk) by layering in the order listed.
Pour condensed milk over the top of the layers.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes until golden brown.
When cool, cut into squares and serve.

title: jelly roll cake
directions: Beat eggs, until eggs are fluffy and then add sugar gradually and beat until lemon colored and double in amount.
Add vanilla. Fold in flour which has been sifted with baking powder.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into jelly roll pan which has been covered with wax paper and greased.
Bake in 400° oven for 12 minutes.
When cake is baked, put on dampened dish towel and pull wax paper off and roll in towel.
When cool, unroll and spread with currant jam and roll.
Before serving, dust with powdered sugar.

title: pork tenderloin(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Rub tenderloins with salt, pepper, sage and nutmeg.
Brown in olive oil on stove.
Add garlic, parsley, onion, bay leaf, red wine and consomme.
Transfer to baking or roasting pan.
Bake for 2 to 3 hours at 350°.
Slice when cooled.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar and butter.
Add eggs and continue beating until mixture is well mixed.
Add maple and vanilla flavorings. Put flour, salt, baking powder, and soda into sifter.

title: roma meat roll
directions: Combine hamburg, crushed crumbs, onion, 1/3 cup tomato sauce with cheese, salt, oregano and pepper.
Mix well and shape into a rectangle about 10 x 12 inches on waxed paper.
Sprinkle pizza cheese evenly over mixture.
Roll up like a jelly ball and press ends of roll to seal.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Do not cover.

title: french quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Fry bacon until crispy and drain on paper towel. Crumble bacon into pie shell in a 9-inch pie pan. Top with grated cheese. Combine milk, eggs, salt, white pepper and cayenne in blender.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 30 minutes. This can be prepared and frozen (wrapped in aluminum foil) before baking. Serves 6 to 8.

title: sugarless banana bread
directions: Blend ingredients and bake in loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: asparagus au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2-quart casserole.
Brown mushrooms in margarine until tender, drain.
Carefully combine mushrooms, asparagus (cut into 1/2-inch pieces) and eggs in casserole.
Melt margarine, add flour and gradually stir in milk. Add cheese, Worcestershire sauce, pepper and salt until cheese melts.
Pour over asparagus mixture.
Edge the casserole with bread crumbs and sprinkle the center generously with paprika.
Bake 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat the margarine, eggs, sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Mix together with creamed mixture the flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Chill and roll.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add pie filling and pineapple.
Pour into flat dish and refrigerate until set. Combine sugar, sour cream, cream cheese and vanilla.
Spread over gelatin layer.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: festive chicken salad log
directions: Mix cheese, mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt, ginger, pepper and pepper sauce.
Stir in chicken, eggs and 1/4 cup onions.
Shape into log, 8 x 2-inches.
Wrap in plastic wrap; refrigerate until firm, about 4 hours.

title: spinach cheese soup
directions: Add onion soup mix and broth mix to 6 cups water.
Bring to boil.
Add spinach.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add noodles.
Cook 5 minutes longer.
Add milk.
Heat just to boil.
Do not boil.
Add cheeses. Stir until melted.

title: jelly roll
directions: Beat eggs until lemon colored; add sugar gradually.
Sift all the dry ingredients together.
Add all ingredients together and beat with mixer on low until it is well mixed, about 2 minutes, no more.
Cook cake about 10 to 15 minutes, until lightly brown. Sprinkle dish towel with confectioners sugar.
Lay cake on towel and begin to roll.
Let stand 3 minutes, then unroll.
Spread with any soft jelly (leave jelly out overnight), then roll up and wrap in towel until cool.

title: seafood salad fey style
directions: Mix all ingredients and
chill
for 1 hour before serving.

title: miracle cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add lemon juice and let cool.
Cream together cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add cooled jello.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Mix cracker crumbs with margarine. Pack all but 1/2 cup into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add filling and sprinkle remainder on top.
Refrigerate.

title: wild rice stuffing
directions: Soak wild rice in hot water for 1 hour and drain.
Saute rice in margarine until golden brown.
Add chicken broth and salt. Cover and simmer about 25 minutes or until tender.
Add green onions, celery, mushrooms, marjoram and nutmeg.
Toss lightly to mix.
Yields about 1 1/4 cups.
Also can use rice boiled in a bag.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into greased and floured tube pan. Put in cold oven.
Turn on heat at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes. Do not open door.
Remove immediately.
Freezes well.

title: linzertorte(almond cake)
directions: A day before you are going to serve the Linzertorte, prepare the dough in the following manner:
In a large bowl, using the mixer at medium speed, beat the butter and sugar until creamy. Gradually beat in the 2 eggs, salt, lemon peel, cinnamon and cloves.
Fold in the almonds and flour until well blended.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate overnight.
Use about 3/4 of the dough to press on the bottom of a 9-inch layer cake pan, building a rim around the edge slightly higher than the center.
Over the center of the dough, spread 1/2 cup raspberry jam.
Preheat the oven to 350°.
On a floured board, roll out the rest of the dough to about 1/4-inch thick.
With a pastry wheel, cut out 6 strips 3/4-inch wide.
Place them, lattice-fashion, over the raspberry jam.
Cut the rest of the dough into 1-inch strips and lay around the top edge of the torte or cut out small shapes with cookie cutter and place them around the edge, slightly overlapping.
Brush dough with beaten egg.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until golden.
Cool on a wire rack.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: slush punch
directions: Boil water and sugar; simmer 3 minutes.
Add jello and juices. Freeze.
Remove from freezer; add ginger ale.

title: oyster scallop
directions: Melt butter. Add crumbs and mix well.
Spread 1/3 of the mixture in greased baking dish.
Put half of the oysters on top of crumbs in one layer. Season with salt and pepper.
Add a layer of crumbs, then a layer of oysters, then a final layer of crumbs. Pour milk over the top. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes until top is browned. Garnish with parsley.

title: creamy peanut butter fudge
directions: In a heavy 2 1/2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, margarine and milk.
Bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly. Continue boiling over medium heat for 5 minutes, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter, stirring until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme and vanilla; beat until well blended.
Spread in a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature, then refrigerate.
Cut into squares when firm.
Makes 3 pounds candy.

title: oatmeal rolls
directions: Mix altogether.
Let rise 2
hours.
Shape
into rolls. Let rise about 45 minutes.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: crazy eggs
directions: Grease 9X13 inch pan and a 8X8 inch pan. Tear bread into 1 inch pieces, divide between the 2 baking dishes. Sprinkle ham and onion over bread pieces. Mix eggs and milk together; pour over bread and ham mixture. Melt butter and cheese together; pour over above mixture. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes (8X8 inch pan) - 60 minutes (9X13 inch pan).

title: ritz pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff. Add sugar slowly.
Add the other ingredients and put into greased pie tin.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and top with Cool Whip and nuts.
Makes its own crust.

title: pea pickin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Put all ingredients in mixing bowl and mix well.
Pour into four 9-inch cake pans and bake at 325° in oven for 20 minutes.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cocoa.
Add vegetable oil, vanilla and vinegar.
Mix well.
Mix water into batter and mix until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool cake and sprinkle with powdered sugar before frosting.

title: easy drop rolls
directions: Melt margarine and cool.
Add all other ingredients and stir until well blended.
Dough should be soft and sticky.
Place in an airtight container and store in refrigerator at least 2 hours before using.
(This will keep up to a week.) To serve, spoon into greased muffin tins and bake for 20 minutes.
Yields 2 dozen large rolls.

title: rosy apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Pare and slice apples.
Simmer peelings in water, covered for 10 minutes.
In a small bowl, combine sugar, flour, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add lemon and lemon juice to apples. Mix thoroughly.

title: spinach swinger
directions: Soften gelatine in beef broth.
Stir over low heat until dissolved.
Stir in salt, water and lemon juice.
Gradually add gelatine to Miracle Whip and mix until well blended.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in spinach, onion, eggs and bacon.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart mold.
Chill until firm.
Garnish with pimento strips.

title: bhujia(mixed vegetables)
directions: Fry onion.
Add salt, pepper, turmeric powder and cumin.
Stir. Add eggplants, tomatoes and garlic.
Stir and leave it on low fire. When eggplants are cooked, put green pepper.
Cover.
Leave it on fire for 5 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press rolls into 10 x 17-inch pan and bake until light brown. Mix together cream cheese, mayo and spices.
Spread on crescent rolls.
Top with assorted vegetables.
Slice and serve.

title: taco salad(club member: keisha hudson)
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet. Sprinkle soup mix over top. Stir in 3/4 cup water; mix well. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Combine next 6 ingredients in large bowl; toss well. Place lettuce mixture on individual salad plates. Spoon ground beef mixture on top. Sprinkle corn chips on top. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: casey's monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in quarters.
Shake bag with 1 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon of cinnamon.
Put in greased Bundt pan.
Boil butter, 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon
and pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: apricot-cream cheese tart
directions: In medium saucepan, heat 1 tablespoon butter and just enough water to cover bottom of pan (about 1/4 cup).
Cut apricots into fourths or half. Add apricots to saucepan; pour sugar on top and mix.
Place saucepan over medium heat, stirring occasionally, to keep apricots from sticking and until apricots are softened. This takes about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: beer cake
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening. Beat eggs. Add to mixture. Beat in nuts, dates and spices.
Sift flour with soda and salt. Alternate stirring in flour and beer to creamed mixture, mixing well. Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: wild rice company casserole
directions: Wash rice and cook in water with salt for 45 minutes.
Drain rice.
Brown beef; set aside.
Saute mushrooms, celery and onion in oleo for 5 minutes.
Combine soy sauce, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Add rice, beef, onion, mushrooms and celery.
Add almonds.
Place mixture in a lightly greased 3-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Add water, if needed, and season to taste.
Stir several times.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add egg whites, sifted dry ingredients, milk, nuts and grated lemon rind.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
When baked, pour juice of one lemon and 1/3 cup sugar mixed together over bread while hot.

title: fudgie scotch ring
directions: Melt all chips with milk in top of double boiler over hot water; stir occasionally, until chips melt and all is blended. Remove from heat; add chopped walnuts and blend well.
Chill for 1 hour until mixture thickens.
Line bottom of 9-inch pie pan with 12-inch square of foil.
Place 3/4 cup walnut halves in bottom of pan, forming 2-inch wide flat ring.
Spoon chocolate mixture in small mounds on top of walnuts to form ring.
Decorate with remaining walnuts.
Chill until firm enough to slice.

title: dip
directions: Put sausage in food processor.
Add other ingredients.
Mix. Serve.
Can be used hot or cold.
If using hot, put half the onions in before heating and then put other half on top after heating.

title: bible's bologna sandwich
directions: Take one slice of bread, apply bologna and cheese.
Spread mayonnaise and mustard as desired.
Apply tomato and lettuce.
Cap with another piece of bread.
Eat carefully with napkin.

title: easy rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: danish chicken with rice
directions: Wash chicken and dry pieces between towels.
Saute chicken and onions in fat until chicken is golden brown on all sides.
Combine salt, paprika, curry powder and catsup.
Add catsup mixture and hot water to chicken.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until tender.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender, pull chicken off bones and layer chicken in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour 1 can cream of mushroom soup over chicken.
Mix 1 can of chicken soup with package of stuffing mix and use broth from boiled chicken until mixture is moist. Pour mixture over layered chicken.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until top is brown.

title: avocado omelet
directions: Heat sour cream, salt and pepper in double boiler.
Add tomatoes and avocado.
Heat for another 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, blend the beaten eggs with milk and salt.
Pour into heated butter in skillet and cook gently, lifting edges occasionally to let uncooked part run underneath.
When set, pour half of sauce mixture over omelet and fold over.
Place on hot platter and pour on the rest of the sauce.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate velvet sauce
directions: Combine ingredients; cook over medium heat until smooth and thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Chill.
Makes about 1 pint.
It takes quite a long time to cook.

title: zucchini pizza
directions: Mix together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into squares.

title: potato celery supreme
directions: Put cut potatoes into greased casserole; add salt and pepper, margarine, soup and water.
Stir lightly.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: angel food cake
directions: At high speed, beat egg whites with salt and cream of tartar until soft peaks.
Add 1 cup sugar to egg.
Sift flour and 3/4 cup sugar together 3 times, then fold into egg whites.
Add vanilla and almond extract.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican vegetable soup
directions: In saucepan, combine the beans, broth or stock, carrots and lime juice.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Serve garnished with salsa and parsley or cilantro.

title: baked fruit french toast
directions: Butter a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Spread can of apple pie filling on bottom of baking dish. Sprinkle on cinnamon, brown sugar and raisins. Lay slices of bread in baking dish. Mix together eggs, milk and vanilla and pour over bread. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 375° for about 40 minutes.

title: whole wheat sausage stuffing
directions: Brown sausage.
Add green pepper and onion.
Cook until crisp and tender.
Stir in chicken broth and seasonings.
Heat to boiling.
Remove from heat.
Stir in bread cubes.
Toss lightly until moisture is absorbed.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Use this with Sausage Stuffed Squash.

title: new england boiled dinner
directions: Place ham and water in multi-cooker.
Set heat control at 250° and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to 212°.
Cover and simmer 1 hour or until meat is nearly tender.
Add remaining ingredients, cover and simmer until vegetables are done.
Add water, if necessary.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: crab-broccoli bake
directions: Blend soup and milk.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
In buttered 8-inch
square
baking dish, place half the broccoli. Top with half
the
crabmeat.
Cover
with
half the stuffing. Pour over half
the soup mixture and top with half the cheese. Layer with
remaining
broccoli,	crabmeat, stuffing and soup. Cover with rest of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken chilies casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine sour cream, light cream, onions, chilies, salt and pepper.
Stir in potatoes, chicken and 2 cups of the cheese.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese before serving.

title: taco salad
directions: First, brown hamburger meat and drain fat.
Then add the taco seasoning plus 3/4 cup of water.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat. Let it simmer for 15 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli divan
directions: In a 2-quart shallow casserole, arrange broccoli.
Top with chicken.
Combine soup, milk and pepper; pour over chicken. Combine crushed crackers, cheese and paprika; sprinkle over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, or until hot and bubbling.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix well and shape into small balls size of a walnut.
Brown in skillet 10 to 15 minutes or bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: "dirt"
directions: Mix together cream cheese, butter and sugar.
In a separate bowl, mix milk and pudding (make fluffy).
Add pudding to first mixture.
Blend well.
Gradually mix in Cool Whip.
Crush cookies in food processor.

title: drunken meatballs(party food)
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in large bowl and shape into small walnut-size balls.
Put last 3 ingredients into large saucepan and bring to a boil.
Place meatballs into the sauce and cook for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve in chafing dish or heated dish with toothpicks.

title: chocolate rice krispie bars
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together. Add eggs and vanilla. Add flour, baking powder and salt all sifted together.
Spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°. Remove and place marshmallows over cake, then cool, for 30 minutes. Add topping.

title: pfeffer kuchen(a german recipe for molasses cookies)
directions: Mix in order with flour enough to make a stiff dough.
Chill. Roll out and cut with the shaped cutter of your choice.
Bake about 10 minutes at 350°.

title: four layer delight
directions: Mix in baking dish and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: tuna cheese dish
directions: Add salt and pepper to bread crumbs.
Put in 8 or 9-inch square dish.
Top with tuna, then cheese.
Combine eggs and milk. Pour over mixture in dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: surprise dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and cream.
Add soup, picante and hominy. Can be made early.
Serve with corn chips.

title: banana split cake
directions: Whip confectioners sugar, egg whites, vanilla and butter 10 minutes.
Pour over crust.
Top with sliced bananas, crushed pineapple and Cool Whip.
Garnish with chopped pecans.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Place pineapple in buttered casserole dish (or spray the dish with butter-flavored PAM).
Mix sugar and flour and sprinkle over pineapple.
Sprinkle cheddar cheese, then crushed crackers. Drizzle oleo on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion together until tender. Drain water from squash and mix with sour cream and soup. Set aside.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Pour into baking dish. Place cheese on top.
Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: red rice and sausage
directions: Fry bacon; remove from grease and cool.
Saute onion and bell pepper in bacon grease.
In a casserole dish, mix rice, tomato paste, salt, pepper, brown sugar, sauteed onions and peppers with grease and crumbled bacon.
Slice sausage and place on top.
Cook, covered, for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 375°.
Fluff with a fork and place back in the oven for 15 minutes.

title: brisket
directions: Pour over brisket and cook 1 1/2 hours longer.
Baste with sauce periodically.
Keep covered.

title: roasted asparagus
directions: Break off tough ends of asparagus.
Peel lower white sections; place in baking dish.
Drizzle with olive oil.
Sprinkle on chopped garlic.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: grilled summer fish(great anytime of the year; four servings)
directions: Grease 12 x 18-inch piece of heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Place fish fillets in center of foil.
Combine vegetables and place over fish.
Sprinkle with dill and salt; drizzle with lemon juice.
Top with Jarlsberg cheese.
Fold up sides of foil, crimping to make a tight seal on top and ends.
Place foil packet on top of hot barbecue grill.
Grill for 25 minutes.
Carefully open packet, if fish is still translucent in the middle, reseal and grill for an additional 5 to 10 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, pour crushed pineapple including juice.
Pour cherry pie filling over pineapple.
Sprinkle cake mix over fruit.
Slice butter in thin pieces and place over cake mix. Bake in a 350° oven for 55 minutes.

title: mexican pie
directions: Brown the ground beef and drain.
Add beans and 1/2 cup cheese.
Stir until melted.
Meanwhile, heat oven to 375°. Separate crescent rolls into 8 triangles and arrange in ungreased 9-inch pie pan.
Press dough pieces together to seal.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Spoon the meat mixture into prepared crust.
Top with lettuce, tomato, remaining cheese and sour cream (sour cream amount can vary).

title: chocolate mint sugar cookie drops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine 1 cup of sugar and vegetable oil.
Mix well.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in mint flavored chocolate bits.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets. Shape into balls; roll in remaining sugar.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 5 1/2 dozen.

title: chipped beef ball
directions: Mix well.
Form in ball and chill.
Serve with party crackers.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine margarine and peanut butter.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Mix with hands.
Roll into balls.
In double boiler melt wax and chocolate chips.
With a toothpick dip balls into the hot mixture.
Place on wax paper until cool.

title: cheesed olives
directions: Blend the cheese with butter 4 or 5 hours ahead. Stir in the flour, salt, paprika and mix well.
Wrap 1 teaspoon dough around each olive.
Cover completely.
Arrange olives on an ungreased baking sheet. Refrigerate.
One-half hour before serving, bake in a 400° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: 7 can soup
directions: Open all cans and pour in large pan; heat and simmer for 15 minutes. Eat and enjoy.

title: snickers pie(club member: lee ann mcraney)
directions: Bake pie crust lightly. Cut candy bars; place in bottom of crust. In bowl, mix cream cheese, sugar and eggs, beating well after each addition. Add sour cream and peanut butter.
Pour over candy bars. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 325° until middle is set. Cool completely.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Grind peppers in food processor or blender.
Combine all ingredients except Certo.
In heavy saucepan over high heat, bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add Certo and pour immediately into clean jars and seal.
For hotter jelly, add more hot or less sweet peppers.
Serve with crackers and cream cheese.

title: zippy beef casserole
directions: Cook elbows as directed.
Brown ground beef, green pepper and onion.
Mix these and all other ingredients, except potato chips, together.
Place in greased 2-quart casserole and add crushed potato chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: carne guisada
directions: Fry steak in 1 tablespoon of grease until brown.
Fry onions now, too.
Add flour to meat and brown.
Add 1/2 can of peeled tomatoes and 1 to 2 cups of water for gravy.
Add salt, pepper, cuminos and garlic powder to taste.
Cover and simmer until gravy is desired thickness.

title: rice and corn casserole
directions: Saute onions and bell pepper in oleo.
Combine with rice, egg, pimento, sugar, salt and pepper.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes large casserole.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Mix together in a saucepan the sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for one minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Stir until well mixed, then drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: ohio buckeyes
directions: Mix together 1 stick Imperial oleo, one pound sifted powdered sugar, 2 cups crunchy peanut butter and 3 cups crushed Rice Krispies.
(Can use a rolling pin and a Ziploc bag to crush them.) Then roll all ingredients into small balls about the size of a half dollar; refrigerate overnight.
Next day, melt over hot water 1/3 bar paraffin and 12 ounces chocolate chips.
Dip each ball in chocolate and drain on waxed paper or wire rack.
Makes 100 balls.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Roll
pretzels	with
rolling
pin (not too fine).
Mix pretzels, 3/4
cup	melted oleo and 3 tablespoons of sugar and press into a
9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes, no longer.
Cool.

title: oven fried coconut chicken
directions: Cut chicken up. Reserve boney back pieces for other use.
Wash and dry chicken.
Mix together the flour, salt, pepper and garlic salt. Dip the chicken pieces in the egg.
Roll in the coconut. Roll in the seasoned flour. Choose baking dish that will hold the chicken pieces in one layer.
Put the butter in baking dish in a hot 400° oven until just melted. Arrange the chicken, skin side down, in the dish.
Bake in hot oven 30 minutes. Turn chicken so skin side is up. Bake 20 to 30 minutes longer or until tender and browned.

title: egg nog non-alcoholic
directions: Beat egg yolks unti light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in half of the sugar.
Beat egg whites until fluffy and gradually beat in remaining sugar.
Fold whites into yolks.
Add cream, milk and flavoring.
Stir well to combine.
Pour in punch bowl and sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Serves about 40 punch cup servings.

title: apple butter pumpkin pie homemade with love
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine filling ingredients in order given; pour into pie shell.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted 2 inches from center comes out clean.
Top with Streusel Topping.
Bake for an additional 15 minutes.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: campfire stew
directions: Brown hamburger meat, onion and salt and pepper to taste.
Add tomatoes, vegetable soup and tomato paste.
Simmer for 30 minutes. Pour over cooked, drained noodles.
Mix and pour in baking dish. Top with cheese slices.
Put in oven to melt cheese.

title: garlic chicken on rice
directions: In small bowl, combine onion, garlic, lemon juice, soy sauce, honey and ginger.
Add chicken.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Slice
cucumbers
1/4-inch
thick.
Combine rest of the ingredients and marinate together for at least 2 hours.
Makes quick and easy good Tsukemono.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Saute bell pepper and onion.
Add hamburger.
In separate pot, simmer tomato sauce, crushed tomatoes, Italian soup and Italian seasoning and water.
Let simmer.
Add hamburger, pepper and onion and simmer.
Cook spaghetti.
Heat oven to 400°.
Place one layer cooked spaghetti in bottom of casserole dish.
Add sauce and then layer with cheese.
Repeat steps until all is used.
Cook in oven for about 20 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Separate stems and caps.
Chop stems and saute with onions. Mix all remaining ingredients, then add mushroom stems and onions. Stuff mushroom caps and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: homemade vegetable beef soup
directions: Clean and cut carrots crosswise in 2 inch pieces;
place in 5 quart cooking pan.
Wash roast, cut up in large pieces, season with salt, ground black pepper and garlic salt.
Transfer meat to 5 quart pan with carrots; add water to top of meat.
Cook covered for 2 hours or longer until very tender.
OR, cook in pressurized cooker (i.e., Presto cooker) with water up to top of meat for 40 minutes.
Remove meat to large bowl or rectangular pan, reserving broth.
Discard suet.
Trim fat from meat and cut into small pieces.
Remove carrots to a small bowl.
Set meat and carrots aside.
Strain beef broth into separate bowl, add water, if necessary, to make 2 cups; set broth aside.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender and drain. Mix with sour cream, soup and cheese. Pour in baking dish and top with cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° until crumbs are brown.

title: homemade steak sauce
directions: Melt butter in small pan over low heat.
Whisk Worcestershire sauce, mustard and tomato paste or catsup until well blended and smooth, about 1 minute.
Serve sauce over steaks immediately.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Cool cake then crumble cake in punch bowl.
Add 1 box of pudding.
Layer 1 can of fruit and pineapple.
Top with half of Cool Whip and coconut.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Top with nuts, cherries and Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: spinach bread
directions: Split bread in half lengthwise.
Melt oleo and saute chopped onion until done.
Add garlic powder and hot sauce to taste.

title: broccoli-rice-cheese casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in oleo until begins to dissolve.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs and extra cheese.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb nut bread
directions: Beat together brown sugar, oil and eggs.
Mix together soda, vanilla and sour milk.
Add to first mixture.
Add flour, mixing well, then add rhubarb and finally nuts.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 8-inch loaf pans.
Sprinkle top with mixture of 1 tablespoon butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: sliced cheese baked potatoes
directions: Preparation for this meal is 15 minutes, cooking time is 1 hour.
Heat oven to 425°.
This recipe is for 4 servings.

title: lasagna
directions: Sauce:
Saute beef, pork, onion and garlic in oil in 4-quart saucepan until meat is well-browned.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, water, salt, oregano, basil and red pepper; simmer, covered, 1 hour.

title: cheese 'n sausage strata
directions: Brown sausage and mushrooms.
Drain.
Stir in Velveeta, bread cubes and onions.
Spoon into greased 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Beat milk and eggs. Pour over sausage mixture.
Cover. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake, uncovered, 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Makes 6 servings.

title: dreamers delight
directions: Combine flour, margarine and 1/4 cup sugar.
Press mixture into bottom of 9 x 13 x 1-inch pan.
Sprinkle chopped nuts onto crust. Bake in moderate oven until golden brown.
Let crust cool.

title: cream chez bisgits
directions: Chop wood, carry into house 'n build fire in stove.
Get out bowl, spoons 'n necessary ingredients...grease pan 'n empty yeast in warm water...take doll 'n toys off table 'n give little Lydia a spoon 'n let her help.

title: tasty taco pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown ground meat; drain.
Add tomato sauce and seasoning.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Spread crescent rolls onto cookie sheet.
Flatten.
Cook in oven 5 minutes.
Turn crescent rolls over.
Spoon on beef mixture.
Place Velveeta slices over beef mixture.
Return to oven until cheese melts. Remove pan from oven; top with lettuce and tomato.
Use taco sauce as desired.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Cook on top of stove all ingredients until heated.
Pour over chicken parts; cook in oven at 350° for 1 hour, then serve.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Pound chicken to 1/4-inch thick.
Place ham and cheese on breasts.
Mix flour, salt and pepper; coat chicken.
Next, dip in egg and then roll in bread crumbs.
Cook until light brown in skillet over medium heat for 10 minutes in oil.
Add water.
Cover and simmer 5 to 10 minutes more.
Top with Cheese Sauce (recipe follows).

title: ginger apple upside-down cake
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Stir well and set aside.
Melt 1/4 cup butter and pour in 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Core, peel and halve apples crosswise.
Arrange flat side down in pan.
Cream together butter, sugar and egg until fluffy. Beat in molasses.
Add to dry ingredients and boiling water.
Mix only until blended and pour over apples.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: austrian almond squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolk and beat well.
Sift together flour and nutmeg. Gradually add to creamed mixture, stirring well.
Spread dough evenly in a 15 1/4 x 10 1/4-inch pan.
Beat egg white slightly and brush over top.
Smooth surface with your fingertips and sprinkle almonds over dough and press in.
Bake in a slow oven at 275° for 1 hour.
While still warm, cut into 40 (2-inch) squares.
Cut 5 lengthwise and 8 crosswise strips.

title: corn and tomato scallop
directions: Beat egg in large bowl.
Add drained corn, tomatoes (crushed into pieces) and onion.
Put in sugar, flour, salt and chili powder.
Save 1/4 cup crackers and 2 tablespoons butter.
Add remaining crackers and butter to corn mixture.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup crackers on top.
Dab with 2 tablespoons of butter.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Whip cream cheese, pudding and milk, then spread on cake.
Spread the crushed pineapple (drained) on cake, then spread the Cool Whip on, then sprinkle coconut on top.

title: belva's punch
directions: Jell-O can be substituted for the Kool-Aid.
Use 1 (3 ounce) box of Jell-O for each package of Kool-Aid.
Use 1/2 cup sugar.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add all liquids.
Mix well.
Cook in pot, stirring constantly.
When thick, pour into 2 baked pie shells. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and mix well. Spread over chocolate mixture.
Brown in a 350° oven.

title: banana split
directions: Mix walnuts, cream cheese, powdered sugar and eggs together and set aside.
Crush vanilla wafers; add cream cheese mixture on top of crust.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 20 minutes; cool. Make Dream Whip according to package directions.
Add to Dream Whip the drained crushed pineapple, cherries, nuts and bananas.
Place on top of cream cheese filling and refrigerate for a while or overnight; cut in squares.

title: turkey and vegetable pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook vegetables according to directions on package.
Drain.
In 2-quart pan over medium heat in hot margarine, cook onion, celery and thyme until onion is tender, stirring occasionally.
Add soup and milk, stirring until smooth.

title: pecan spice cookies
directions: Cream the margarine, sugars and egg.
Sift the dry ingredients together and add to sugar mixture; mix well.
Stir in finely chopped pecans.
Chill dough.
Make in rolls, 1 1/4-inches in diameter.
Slice thinly and bake on greased cookie sheet 8 minutes at 375°.
Dough may be frozen.

title: salt free seasoning mix
directions: Mix together in small glass bowl. Store in tightly covered container or bag.

title: sister theresa's crab dip
directions: Mix cheese and oleo.
Beat until smooth.
Add crabmeat and garlic salt.
Mix well.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Prepare dressing according to package.
Mix with other ingredients.
Cover tightly.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, 1 1/2 cups of milk, sugar and salt in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally until thick and creamy, 15 to 20 minutes.
Blend remaining 1/2 cup milk and egg.
Stir into rice mixture.
Add raisins.
Cook 2 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Add butter and vanilla.
Spoon into serving dishes.
Sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon, if desired. Yield: 4 servings.

title: chocolate fudge custards
directions: Combine all in blender until well blended.
Spray muffin pan with Pam coating.
Half fill a larger pan with water to place muffin pan in.
Place the water pan on lowest rack of oven.
Fill muffin tins 1/4 to 1/3 full.
Carefully place muffin pan into water bath on bottom shelf.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn pan if uneven cooking is occurring.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes longer until edges are pulling away from pan.
Turn off oven and leave them in another 5 minutes until they are "set."
Take out of pan using a blunt knife to help lift them up.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar if you like.

title: red potato pie
directions: Beat eggs; add flour and sugar.
Then add all the other ingredients and pour on unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes; then bake at 350° until done.

title: peaches and cream cheesecake
directions: Drain the peaches, reserve juice and set aside.
Mix together the flour, baking powder, vanilla pudding (not instant), salt, soft butter, egg and milk.
Grease (9-inch) pie pan.
Place peaches over butter.
Mix together the cream cheese, sugar and peach juice. Place over peaches; sprinkle cinnamon sugar over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: clam dip 1
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve warm or cold with crackers.

title: potato and ham chowder
directions: Melt margarine in 3-quart pot over medium heat.
Stir in potatoes, onion and celery.
Cover and cook 10 to 12 minutes, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are almost tender.
Whisk 1/2 cup milk with flour until smooth.
Stir into potato mixture with remaining milk and ham.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring often.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add corn, salt and pepper and simmer for 5 minutes longer until thickened and vegetables are tender.

title: over the stove macaroni
directions: Beat egg with whisk or fork.
Add milk and beat until combined.
Fold cheese into liquid mixture.
Set aside.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Cook onion and pepper in butter. Add cheese and soup and stir until cheese is melted.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in casserole dish.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 2 loaf pans.
In large bowl, mix flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt and baking soda.
Make a well in the center of mixture.
Pour eggs and oil in well.
Stir until dry ingredients are just moist.
With a slotted spoon, dip out berries and gently stir into mixture.
Add juice gradually, stirring until batter is of the proper consistency.
The amount of juice varies in berries when thawed and you do not want the batter to be too thin.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in
pans 15 minutes.
With knife, loosen sides of loaves from pans.
Turn out of pans.
Let cool completely before slicing.

title: cinnamon buns
directions: **Or use instant potato flakes and water.

title: spinach dip
directions: Stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Cover and chill.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water.
Add 7-Up, pineapple and bananas (sliced).
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch container and chill until firm.
Cook pineapple juice (add water to make 1 cup), sugar, flour, egg (slightly beaten) and butter.
Cool.
Fold in Cool Whip and coconut. Spread over Jell-O and sprinkle with pecans.

title: sour cherry salad
directions: Combine sugar and food coloring.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over cherry gelatin.
Add plain gelatin softened in water.
Add rind of orange and lemon.
Add juice, fruits and nuts.

title: three cheese chicken bake
directions: In skillet, saute onion and green pepper in margarine until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soup, mushrooms and basil.
In a large separate bowl, combine cooked noodles, chicken and cheeses.
Add mushroom sauce and mix well. Transfer to greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.
Sprinkle with crumbs. Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes longer.

title: vanilla rice pudding
directions: Gradually mix milk and egg into pudding mix in saucepan.
Add rice and raisins.
Stir over medium heat until mixture comes to boil.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring 2 times.

title: country scrambled eggs(microwave)
directions: Place
sausage in a 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Microwave on High
for
to
minutes or until no longer pink. Drain excess fat.
Stir in eggs, sour cream, chives, mushrooms and basil. Microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes or until eggs are set
but moist.
Stir every minute.
Total cooking time is 6 to 8 minutes. Yield:
4 servings.

title: italian biscuit topped casserole
directions: Grease a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
In a large skillet, brown beef and onion. Drain off all drippings.
Stir in water, pepper, tomato sauce and paste.
Simmer for about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat. Stir in vegetables and half of the cheese.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits. Separate each biscuit into 2 layers.
Place biscuits near outer edge of hot meat mixture, overlapping slightly. Sprinkle remaining cheese in center and around edge. Gently brush biscuits with melted butter. Sprinkle with oregano.
Bake at 375° for 22 to 27 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: canned apples and filling
directions: In a medium size dish, cut up bite size apples.
Put 1 teaspoon of salt over them.
Mix together sugar, water, cornstarch, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cook until it begins to thicken. Take off stove.
Stir in 3 teaspoons of lemon juice and mix. Pour over apples and stir.
Put into jars.
Cook on 10 pounds of pressure for 10 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix in order.
Makes 2 loaves.
Bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: frozen coconut cake
directions: Cook 1 package of coconut in cake mix.
Mix 1 1/2 cups milk with sugar.
Let come to a boil.
Pour over cake.
Let cool completely.
Spread Cool Whip over cake.
Sprinkle with remaining coconut.

title: shoepeg casserole
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients; add salt and pepper.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt oleo and mix with crushed Ritz crackers. Spread on top of vegetable mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: creamy pimiento cheese
directions: Combine cheeses and beat at medium speed with electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add mayonnaise and garlic powder; mix well.
Stir in pimiento.
For best consistency, serve at room temperature.
To store, cover and chill.
Yield:
4 1/2 cups.

title: cream coconut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Mix and bake cake just like directions on box.
(Do not overbake.) Remove cake from oven and punch holes in cake with wooden spoon handle.
Pour on cream of coconut and let it saturate cake.
Then pour on Eagle Brand milk.
Let cool completely.
Spread top of cake with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.
You can add chopped nuts and maraschino cherries to top.
Cake is better the second day.

title: chicken wings pacifica
directions: Disjoint wings, discarding tips.
Arrange in shallow baking pan.
Combine soy sauce, brown sugar, butter, mustard and water; heat until sugar and butter dissolve.
Cool and pour over wings. Marinate in refrigerator 2 hours turning occasionally.
Pour off half of marinade and save for use another time.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot or cold.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Combine all
the
ingredients in a long casserole dish. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted, approximately 20 minutes.

title: special k candy
directions: Cook first 2 ingredients on stove until the sugar dissolves, at a rolling boil (this occurs immediately after it reaches a rolling boil).
Remove from the stove and add peanut butter and cereal.
Drop onto wax paper or foil.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, onion, margarine, soup, sour cream, salt,
pepper and 2/3 cup of stuffing mix.
Pour in casserole dish and bake at 350° until set.
Spread remaining stuffing mix on top of casserole and dot with margarine.
Cook until brown on top.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Add Jell-O to drained pineapple, then add to cottage cheese. Add Cool Whip.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Tip:
These mints make excellent gifts packaged in pretty tins or glass jars.

title: chipped beef and cheese ball
directions: Cut beef into small pieces.
Mix everything together and make a round ball.
Serve with crackers.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Spread into a greased pan.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes, until golden brown.
Let cool.
Cut into squares.
May be used hot or cold.

title: bird's nest pie
directions: Break spaghetti in half; cook in boiling water until al dente. Drain.
While spaghetti is warm, combine with eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Press in bottom and up sides of well-greased, 10-inch pie plate.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in a large bowl.
Add sliced apples and mix to coat.
Place apple slices in pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and rind; dot with butter.
Top with crust; slash vents in center of crust.
Bake at 425° for 50 to 60 minutes, until apples are done and crust is golden brown.

title: fudgy brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat an 8-inch square baking pan with vegetable cooking spray; set aside.
Cut chocolate in 1-inch pieces.
Place in heatproof bowl.
Set over low heat in skillet with 1/2 inch simmering water.
Stir occasionally, just until melted.
Remove from heat.
Set aside.

title: tuna noodle crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles in boiling, salted water according to package directions; drain.
Melt Crisco in large skillet.
Add onion and green pepper and cook until tender.
Stir in soup, milk, pimento and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Add cooked noodles and tuna.

title: bread pudding
directions: Simmer raisins in water until plump.
Combine diced bread, eggs, cream, sugar and spices and mix well by hand.
Add raisins and mix gently.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes until golden brown.
Place pan in larger pan of water to prevent burning while baking if necessary.

title: peanut butter treat
directions: Mix cookies and margarine in bowl; reserve 1/4 cup.
Press remaining cookie mixture into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes.
Cool completely.
Prepare pudding mix according to package directions using 1 3/4 cups milk.
Stir in peanut butter and chocolate.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread evenly over cooled crust.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Chill, covered, for several hours or overnight.

title: minestrone meatball soup
directions: Spray Dutch oven or large saucepan with nonstick cooking spray.
Heat over medium-high heat until hot.
Add onions, celery and garlic.
Cook and stir until crisp-tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except rotini and meatballs.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover; simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in rotini and meatballs.
Simmer, uncovered, an additional 10 to 12 minutes or until vegetables and rotini are tender.
If desired, serve with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 8 (1 1/2-cup) servings.

title: microwave hamburger stew
directions: Combine beef coarsely into 3 to 5-quart casserole.
Mix in carrots and celery.
Cover and microwave on High for 3 1/2 to 6 1/2 minutes or until beef is set, stirring once or twice.
Add remaining ingredients.
Microwave, covered, 12 to 18 minutes, or until vegetables are tender, stirring once or twice.
Remove bay leaf before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pig eaten cake
directions: Combine cake mix, oranges, eggs and oil.
Beat for 4 minutes. Pour in 3 layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: beer bread
directions: Stir all ingredients well and pour into buttered loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients; add eggs, oil, strawberries and nuts. Stir just until all ingredients are moistened.
Spoon into 2 well greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes; glass 325°.
Cool in pan 5 minutes before removing.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: dirt cake
directions: Grind cookies in food processor.
Press 1/2 of the crumb mixture in bottom of layer cake pan.
Cream together powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Add pudding and milk.
Beat until it thickens, then add Cool Whip.
Pour mixture into pan.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Chill for several hours.

title: rob's favorite leftover
directions: Melt butter in a pan.
Put milk in a shaker; add flour and shake well.
Over medium heat, stir in flour mixture, stirring constantly.
Add ham; stir together.
To this mixture you can add leftover peas, carrots or broccoli.
Serve over toast.

title: chinese dumplings
directions: Boil cabbage for 1 minute, drain and chop.
Mix beef with remaining ingredients and stir in cabbage.
Stir water into flour, knead and shape into a ball.
Roll dough into a sausage shape. Tear off bits of dough and shape each into a ball.
Roll each with a rolling pin until you have a circle.
Place 2 teaspoons filling in center of each and fold circle in half.
Score edges.
Drop one-by-one into boiling water and boil for 1 minute, then drain. Serve warm with soy sauce or other Chinese sauces.

title: fruit dip
directions: Let first 2 items warm to room temperature.
Mix together with 1 teaspoon of fresh orange juice (this is optional).
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Place lettuce in 9 x 12-inch pan or dish.
Layer rest of ingredients.
Add sugar to Miracle Whip and spread over top. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix together and let stand in refrigerator 3-4 days before eating. Will keep in refrigerator for days.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Blend all ingredients together on high for 15 seconds.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes. Cool and refrigerate.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix all of above ingredients.
Grease and flour cake pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip custard pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and add sugar and milk.
Place in double boiler and cook over hot water until thick. Add gelatin softened in water and vanilla. Cool.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle with chocolate. Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add cream of tartar and continue beating, adding sugar gradually and beating until very stiff. Spread over chocolate and chill before serving.

title: chicken breasts diane(microwave)
directions: Place chicken between sheets of waxed paper and pound slightly. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
In a microwave-safe dish, melt butter and mix in oil.
Place chicken breasts in dish, coating breasts on both sides.
Microwave on High power for 3 minutes.
Let rest for 1 minute.
Turn breasts over.
Microwave again on High power for 3 minutes until chicken breasts are done, not overcooked.
Set aside.

title: strawberry ice
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover and freeze.
Stir every hour or so.
Will be slushy-solid in 4 hours.
Good as a slushy drink (less than 4 hours) or as a sherbet (more than 4 hours).

title: sister waggoner's homemade slaw
directions: Grind cabbage day before (or shred).
Then add salt, vinegar and shredded carrots.
Keep covered and refrigerated until serving.

title: rice casserole
directions: Top with grated sharp cheese and sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: roll recipe
directions: Mix all together and knead.
Cover and let rise.
Punch down and let rise again.
Form into balls and let rise.
Bake until browned.
Recipe makes 100 rolls.

title: hot artichoke hearts
directions: Drain artichokes.
Combine all ingredients in small saucepan. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: granny's million dollar pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice and set aside.
Dice peaches and oranges.
Drain all fruit.
Mix fruit with Cool Whip.
Blend with milk and lemon juice.
Add about 2/3 cup powdered sugar.
Fill graham cracker crust and refrigerate at least four hours.

title: overnight zucchini relish
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in bowl; let stand overnight.
Rinse with cold water; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Place in sterilized hot jars and seal.
Makes 12 jars.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat the eggs in a mixing bowl; add 2 cups of sugar.
Sift together the flour and baking powder; add to egg-sugar mixture. Warm oil in small pan.
Add orange juice to warm oil.
Add to cake batter in bowl; batter will now become bubbly looking and look like a cake batter should.
In separate bowl, cut up apples. Combine apples with cinnamon and 5 tablespoons of sugar. Alternate cake batter and apples in angel food pan; do not use too much batter on any layer.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: red cabbage(serves  6)
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Add shredded cabbage and chopped onion; mix well with bacon and drippings.
Add vinegar, water, sugar, salt, pepper and spices.
Bring to a boil; reduce to simmer, cover and cook 45 to 60 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Sift cocoa and powdered sugar.
Add dry milk and dry coffee cream.
Mix all these ingredients together.
Store in a tightly covered container.

title: pina colada dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Chill well. Serve with your choice of fruit (strawberries, pineapple chunks, etc...).

title: bruce's pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cook at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: bunny's chocolate squares
directions: Mix in order given except chips and nuts.
Beat until well blended.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into ungreased pan.
Sprinkle with nuts and chips.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Cut and serve.

title: applesauce-raisin drops
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray cookie sheets with nonstick baking spray.
Into a small bowl, sift together first seven ingredients and set aside.
In a large bowl, cream margarine until fluffy.
Blend in brown Sugar Twin and egg.
Alternately add sifted dry ingredients and applesauce.
Blend well.
Stir in vanilla, oats and raisins.
Drop by tablespoons onto prepared cookie sheets and then flatten.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes until firm.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: tuna apple salad
directions: Mix together with small amount of Miracle Whip.
Chill. Serves 2.

title: oven omelet
directions: Fry bacon and drain well. Chop half of bacon and leave half in strips. Butter bottom of 8-inch cake or pie pan. Arrange cheese in bottom of pan. Beat eggs and milk. Add chopped bacon. Pour over cheese. Top with remaining bacon strips. Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pecans.
Spread in pie shell and bake in 450° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 30 additional minutes.
Decorate pie with pecan halves.

title: meal-in-one casserole
directions: In a bowl, prepare sauce by adding the soup diluted with 1 can water and tomato sauce with 1/4 cup water.
Stir well.
Add sugar and chili powder to your taste.
Set aside.
In pan or casserole, slice a row of potatoes, onions, chopped meat and rice; salt and pepper each row.
Repeat until all ingredients used.
Pour sauce over layers.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: apple tea cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Sift all dry ingredients.
In small bowl, add 1/2 cup to apples and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 9 x 5-inch greased loaf pan.

title: southern tea cakes(cookies)
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
In separate bowl, mix the beaten eggs, oil, vanilla and sugar.
Pour egg mixture into dry ingredients. Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet; flatten with greased bottom of glass.
Bake until golden brown in a 350° oven.

title: lazy lasagna
directions: Cook beef in large skillet over medium-high heat until meat is brown, stirring to separate meat.
Drain fat.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Reduce heat to low.
Heat through, stirring occasionally. Set aside.
Combine cottage cheese and sour cream in medium bowl. Blend well.
Spoon 1 1/2 cups of the meat sauce in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.

Place 1/2 of the uncooked noodles over sauce, then 1/2 of the cottage cheese mixture, 4 slices of the Mozzarella, 1/2 of the remaining meat sauce and 1/4 cup of the Parmesan cheese. Repeat layers starting with the noodles.
Top with remaining 4 slices of Mozzarella cheese.
Pour water around the sides of the pan.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 1 hour.
Uncover; bake 20 minutes more or until bubbly.
Let stand 15 to 20 minutes.
Garnish as directed.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: mitzi's chili
directions: Brown ground beef and drain thoroughly.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook on high for 5 minutes, then simmer for 1 hour or less.
Serve over cooked spaghetti if desired and sprinkle with grated cheese and chopped onion (optional).

title: south-of-the-border special
directions: In large frypan, brown ground beef and onions, add green peppers, cooking slightly.
Then add tomato sauce and the next six ingredients.
Simmer at least five minutes.
Serve over tortilla chips and top with shredded lettuce, diced fresh tomatoes, chopped onions, green peppers, shredded sharp cheese, sour cream and salsa, if desired.

title: snickers salad
directions: Cut Snickers bars into bite-sized pieces.
Add sliced bananas and unpeeled, cored, chopped apples.
Add Cool Whip.

title: banana cake (icing)
directions: Cook on low heat.
Stir all the time until bubbling.
You can cook in the microwave.
Put on cake while bananas are hot!
(At least 4 cake layers.)

title: "hot dip"
directions: Mix
and
place
in glass pie plate or shallow dish and top with 1/2 cup finely chopped pecans which have been sauteed in
2 tablespoons
butter
and
teaspoon
salt.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve with Ry-Krisp crackers.

title: orange-coconut cake
directions: Beat yolks until light and add sugar.
Add flour and orange juice (with rind) alternately.
Add baking powder and salt to beaten whites and add last.
Bake in ungreased stem pan for 1 hour at 300°.
Wait until cool to cut out but invert pan as for angel food.
When cold, cut in two as for layer cake and put generous amount of filling between layers and fill cavity; completely ice all over.

title: sausage and rice
directions: Brown first 4 ingredients together in large skillet.
Add dry soup mix, rice, almonds and water.
Put in large casserole.
Cook 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: tex-mex enchiladas
directions: Prepare chili as directed; place two Tbsp. chili mixture on each tortilla; roll tightly.
Place seam down in 12x8 inch dish. Top with remaining chili.
Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.
Top with cheese and continue baking uncovered until cheese is melted.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients.
Mix until very smooth.
Mix corn, nuts and gumdrops together.
Pour melted mixture over corn mixture and quickly stir and pour into tube pan.
Let cool, then slice. Do not bake.
M&M's can be substituted for the gumdrops.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Cook everything in a 10-quart pan.
Cook about 1 1/2 hours or until all vegetables are tender.
Use pepper and garlic.
This is a low-calorie soup.

title: brisket
directions: Combine all ingredients; marinate brisket overnight, covered. Bake 6 hours at 275°, turning after 3 hours.
Leave it covered with foil as it bakes.
Leftovers make good sandwiches in buns.

title: opie's clam supreme
directions: Peel and slice eggplant; add onion and salt.
Boil until tender but not mushy; drain, mash and add 2 tablespoons butter. Drain clams, reserving juice.
Butter a casserole dish.
Layer alternately eggplant, clams and Ritz crackers, ending with crumbs. Blend the milk with clam juice. Salt to taste and pour over mixture.
Dot with 3 teaspoons butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine corn and other ingredients.
Pour into greased baking dish and bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crumble cookies.
