Set aside some for top of cake.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add milk, pudding, sugar and vanilla.
Put 1/2 of the cookies in bottom of pan.
Top with pudding mixture. Put the other half of cookies on top of this.
Layer Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with remaining cookie crumbs.
An oblong dish or cake pan is best.
Chill overnight.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Add all ingredients together, except macaroni.
Turn to low heat, crumble beef in skillet and brown lightly.
Add meat to soup.
Cook about 1 1/2 hours on low heat.
Stir frequently. Serves 8 to 10.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Sift flour, salt and sugar together.
Cut shortening in mixture.
Add lukewarm water in which yeast has been dissolved. Mix well.
Put in refrigerator until 3 hours before needed.
Roll out on floured board; cut like biscuits.
Dip in melted margarine. Put close together in pan; let rise 3 hours.
Bake at 450° until a golden brown.

title: marvelous meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, mix thoroughly 1/2 cup of Prego sauce, beef, bread crumbs, onions and egg.
In a 12 x 8-inch baking pan, firmly shape meat into 8 x 4-inch loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.
In a 1-quart saucepan, over medium heat, heat remaining Prego sauce to boiling, stirring occasionally. Serve sauce with meat loaf.
Makes 6 servings.

title: creamy carrot casserole
directions: In a saucepan, cook carrots just until tender; drain.
Save 1/4 cup liquid.
Place carrots in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Combine mayonnaise, onion, horseradish and liquid.
Spread evenly over carrots.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: beet salad
directions: Mix vegetables well.
Pour dressing over all.
Add sugar, if you desire.
Refrigerate overnight.
Toss well before serving. Serve cold.

title: hidden valley ranch oyster crackers
directions: Mix Ranch dressing mix, oil and spices.
Pour over oyster crackers on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 225° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: wyatt's eggplant recipe
directions: Peel eggplant.
Soak it in salted water in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Soak dry bread crumbs in evaporated milk plus whole milk.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli.
Add with the two soup mixes and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cabbage beef soup
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in a large skillet. Simmer on low heat until hamburger is done. Chop cabbage fine and put in a large pot. Add tomatoes and ingredients from skillet. Add remaining ingredients and cook about 1 hour. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: sesame oven fried chicken
directions: Combine egg and milk.
Mix dry ingredients in plastic bag. Dip chicken in egg mixture, then shake in plastic bag.
Place chicken in baking dish, skin side up.
Pour melted butter over chicken and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: lemon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add milk and mix well.
Combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Add margarine and mix well.
Stir until smooth.
Add lemon juice, peel and nuts.
Pour into greased pan and bake for 1 hour or until done.

title: cran chicken sandwich
directions: Prepare charcoal grill or broiler.
Cook chicken breasts until done completely, turning often.
Sprinkle with Lawry's. Just before removing from heat, add 2 tablespoons of whole berry sauce; spread over top of each fillet.
Sizzle until sauce is warm.
Place on bun with lettuce leaf.
Serve with a salad of your choice.
Enjoy!

title: salmon casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Put in greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake 45 minutes or until done in a 325° oven.

title: israelite tomato bread
directions: Heat tomato juice, sauce and butter to 120°.
Assemble doughmaker.
In large mixer bowl, combine 3 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and warmed tomato mixture.
Mix with doughmaker at setting #12 for 3 minutes.
Gradually add enough remaining flour to form a stiff dough.
Knead with doughmaker until smooth and satiny, about 4 minutes.
Place dough in greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.

title: baked southwest dip
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Cut a 1/4-inch slice from top of bread. Set aside.
Remove center from bread, leaving a 1/2-inch thick shell. Cut center in 1-inch cubes. Bake until toasted, about 5 minutes.
With an electric mixer, beat the cream cheese, sour cream and salsa until smooth.
Stir in Cheddar cheese. Spoon into bread shell.
Place reserved slice on top.
Wrap into foil. Bake until hot, about 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with sliced vegetables and toasted bread cubes. Dip can be baked and served in a 1-quart baking pan for 30 minutes.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: palmer's company casserole
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter and brown ground beef.
Add garlic powder, salt, pepper and tomato sauce; mix and simmer 30 minutes. Mix sour cream, cottage cheese and cream cheese in bowl, blending well.
Add green onions and mix again.
Cook the noodles in salted water until al dente (firm); drain and mix with 2 tablespoons butter.

title: wild rice salad
directions: Cook rice and toss with olive oil and raisins.
Season with 1 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper.
Let cool to room temperature.
Add parsley, onion, tomato and mint.
Add vinegar and toss.
Serves 1.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Boil potatoes, then drain them.
Mash them with butter and milk.
Brown the ground chuck and drain off the fat.
Add the chopped onion to the meat and continue to cook the meat until no pink is seen.
Add gravy mix and 1 cup of water or add the can of beef gravy.
To this mixture, add the baked beans and cook for one or two minutes further.
Mix well.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Make graham cracker crumb crust according to package directions using a 9 x 13-inch pan or use 2 ready-made graham cracker crumb crusts.
Combine in a double boiler and melt the Hershey bars, milk and marshmallows.
Cool.
Whip the cream.
Mix with cooled chocolate mixture.
Pour into crust.
Serves 8.

title: barbecued sparerib appetizers
directions: Place spareribs in a 2-quart glass utility dish.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over ribs.
Cover and cook in microwave for 45 minutes.
Turn and rearrange ribs every 10 minutes.

title: broccoli puff casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions, omitting the salt;
drain
thoroughly.
Place
broccoli
in 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking
dish.
Combine
soup
and cheese;
add milk, mayonnaise and
egg,
stirring until well blended.
Pour over broccoli. Combine
enough
margarine to stuffing mix to moisten.
Spread over
soup mixture.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for
to
45 minutes or until bubbly and crumbs are lightly browned.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Melt chocolate and butter; remove from heat.
Add sugar, alternately with milk.
Bring to boil on medium heat.
Stir constantly.
Cook and stir 8 minutes or until creamy.
Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease or spray 2 loaf pans and line with aluminum foil.
Mix dry ingredients.
Make a well in center of mixture and add eggs and oil.
With a slotted spoon, dip strawberries out of juice and add to mixture.
Add just enough juice to make batter the consistency of cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until it tests done with fork.
Cool for 15 minutes.

title: chicken-in-a-garden
directions: Combine chicken, soup, Veg-All and half the onions in bowl, mixing well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle remaining onions over pie.
Bake until onions are roasted.
Yields 6 servings.

title: play dough for children
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients, then bring 2 cups water to boil.
Add food coloring, then pour over flour mixture.
Stir well.
It will be lumpy; knead thoroughly as soon as it is cool enough to handle.
Keep in airtight container.

title: dump cake
directions: Put pie filling, pineapple and walnuts in bottom of pan.
Pour dry cake mix over top.
Put margarine squares on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: punch
directions: Mix half and half.

title: crabmeat maryland
directions: In a large pan melt butter.
Work in flour and then add milk. Stir constantly until white sauce is thick.
Add the remaining ingredients and heat until all ingredients are hot.
Serve from a chafing dish with toast rounds or your favorite crackers.
Serves 50.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk.
Then add vanilla pudding and 3 cups of milk, then add 1/2 cup of Cool Whip.
Put between vanilla wafers and bananas.
The rest of Cool Whip goes on top of pudding.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Place chicken in large pot and cover with water.
Add bouillon, salt and pepper and boil for approximately 20 minutes.
Add celery, carrots and onion and return to a boil for another 20 to 25 minutes.
Turn off heat and remove chicken and let cool.
When chicken and stock are cool, skim some of the fat off the top of the broth and discard.
Pick the chicken meat off the bones into bite size pieces.
Mix cornstarch and 3 tablespoons of water and add to chicken stock.
Bring to a boil and add chicken.
Return to a boil again and add Dumplings.

title: sparkle paint
directions: Mix all ingredients well, beating out all the large lumps. Divide into four containers.
Add coloring as desired and pour into squeeze bottles. Save ketchup and mustard squeeze bottles for this activity.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients in large bowl.
Place in buttered or lightly sprayed 9 x 13 baking dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: old fashioned coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour in saucepan.
Stir in milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until bubbly, approximately 6 to 8 minutes. Stir 1 cup hot mix into beaten egg yolks; return to pan and cook until thick, 3 or 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in 1 cup coconut, butter and vanilla.
Pour into cooked pie crust; set aside.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar and then add sugar. Continue beating until egg whites stand up in peaks.
Spread on pie.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Place in 350°
oven until brown, approximately 15 minutes.

title: everything cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Divide and wrap in wax paper, making a roll.
Chill.
Slice cookies about 1/4 to 1/2 inch thick. Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: cheesecake
directions: In a medium bowl, beat cream cheese until light and fluffy. Add Eagle Brand milk.
Blend thoroughly.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set.

title: delicious prune cake
directions: Sift together self-rising flour and sugar into a bowl.

In another bowl stir together eggs, olive oil, prunes and flavoring. Use the 2 to 3 tbsp. of flour to dust walnuts (4 oz. of raisins may also be used) mix into a batter; then pour in flour mixture. Grease and dust a tube pan and pour in cake batter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: bacon crisps
directions: Put heaps of cheese on top of each cracker.
Wrap in bacon, no toothpick required.
Place on broiler pan rack.
No need to turn at all.
Bake at 200° for 2 hours.
Leave on pan to drain.
Eat hot or cold.
May be frozen.
One pound bacon makes 35 appetizers.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate until served. Use in three or four weeks.

title: kelley and kim's quick 'n easy irish soda bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in butter.
Add raisins or chocolate chips, then milk.
Grease and flour loaf pans (2 or 3). Pour batter and let sit 10 minutes, then put in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Should be slightly browned on top.

title: party fruit punch
directions: Mix sugar and water.
Boil and cool.
Add juices and enough water to make 2-1/2 gallons.
Mix well.
Add Ginger Ale before serving.
Add orange or pineapple slices for color.
Cherries may also be added.

title: caramel pecan pinwheels
directions: In a 9 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pan stir topping and butter together.
Sprinkle with pecan halves.
Separate but do not uncoil bread sticks.
Arrange coils atop of mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes.
Loosen sides and invert on serving plate.
Serve warm.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Combine salmon, soup, cheese and rice.
Saute onions and celery in butter.
Add celery and onions to salmon mixture.
Pour in casserole dish.
Top with cornflake crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: white chocolate cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream margarine and shortening. Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg and mix well.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture. Blend in vanilla.
Stir in chocolate and nuts.
Cover and chill dough for 1 hour.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls about 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes or until lightly brown.
Let stand for a few minutes before removing cookies to a wire rack to cool.
Yields about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: halloween fruit caramels
directions: Chop all fruit and nuts.
A food chopper is good for this purpose.
Mix thoroughly; add fruit juices and roll into balls. Roll in powdered sugar and store for several days to ripen the flavor before serving.

title: enchilada casserole ii
directions: Brown meat.
Drain off fat.
Mix soups and sauce together with meat.
Crunch the tortilla chips into pieces.
Mix the chips with the meat mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Top with cheese slices.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: catfish stew
directions: Slowly cook fish in water covering meat just until done.
Fry bacon; add onions and saute 5 minutes.
Add potatoes and fish stock to cover vegetables.
Cook until done on low heat.

Add tomato soup, salt and pepper, hot pepper sauce and Worcestershire sauce. Bring to boil and add fish and more stock to desired consistency. Return to soft boil; stir in sliced eggs and serve with corn bread. The entire cooking process may take 2 to 3 hours.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: beef and cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in water for 7 minutes.
Drain.
Brown beef in oil, stirring often.
Mix with cabbage.
Blend in sour cream, cheese and seasonings.
Top with little cheese and Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: caramel candy
directions: Caramelize sugar until it is all liquid.
Add 1/4 cup milk slowly.
Finally, add 1/2 cup peanuts (more or less).
Remove from heat and beat until it thickens.
Pour into buttered 9-inch square pan.
Cut in squares and serve after candy has cooled.

title: lasagne
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef and drain.
Return to pan.
Add Ragu or Prego, tomato sauce, Parmesan cheese, Italian seasoning, salt and pepper.
Stir and let simmer 15 minutes.

title: dorothy's potato pie
directions: Put water in a large pot.
Cut ends off potatoes and wash good.
Place in water.
Cover and boil for about 30 to 35 minutes, until potatoes are done.
Slide skin off potatoes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Put potatoes in a large mixing bowl.
Use electric mixer and blend potatoes to get the strings out.
Add butter.
Beat at medium speed or as desired.
Combine sugar, honey, nutmeg, salt, vanilla, lemon juice and cinnamon.
Gradually add milk and eggs; beat well.
Divide evenly into 3 pie pastries.
Bake about 1 hour. (Pie is done when knife inserted in center comes out clean.)

title: chicken pie
directions: Grease pan and put chicken in pan.
Mix cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup and milk.
Spoon over chicken.
Drain can of peas and carrots and spoon over soup.
Mix chicken broth, margarine and Pepperidge Fram mix.
Spread over top and bake until brown in 400° oven.

title: pound cake
directions: Sift flour and baking soda together.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs one at a time beating with mixer after each addition.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately, to
sugar mixture, ending with flour; add flavorings.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in greased tube pan.

title: one dish meal
directions: Brown meat.
Cook macaroni while meat browns.
Add ketchup, stewed tomatoes and Worcestershire sauce to meat.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Pour meat mixture into casserole dish.
Pour drained peas on top of meat.
Place macaroni on top of peas.
Add grated cheese on top.
Place in a 350° oven for 15 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: rum cake
directions: Sift flour and fill powdered sugar box with flour.
Add powdered sugar, butter, eggs (beaten well), one at a time, vanilla and 1/2 bottle of rum flavoring.
Grease and flour tube pan or loaf pan, pour in batter and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Good with green beans with almonds and garlic bread.

title: date-nut loaf cake
directions: Mix marshmallows, dates, nuts, cherries and Cool Whip together into long loaf.
Roll in graham crackers and roll up in wax paper. Put in refrigerator to set.

title: goulash
directions: Brown hamburger and diced onions together.
Add cooked pasta and crushed tomatoes and spices.
Cook together (simmer) for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally (covered skillet) to blend flavors.

title: jamaican black beans
directions: Drain black beans.
In large saucepan, add water, chicken bouillon, beer, rum, garlic and onion.
Simmer 1 to 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 more hour.
Serve as is or with sour cream on top.
Delicious on top of rice.

title: spinach pinwheels
directions: Marinate pounded steak with steak seasoning, garlic and black pepper.
Cover with partially cooked bacon, drained spinach and Parmesan cheese.
Roll from end to end.
Hold with toothpicks. Slice in pinwheels.
Broil each side until desired doneness.
Serve with baked potato and salad.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Combine dressings and cheese; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Chill.
Makes 4 servings.
Add tomato just before serving, if used.

title: 22 minute chocolate cake
directions: Mix in bowl the flour, sugar and soda.
Mix in saucepan the oleo, water, shortening and cocoa.
Heat until it starts to boil. Pour into dry ingredients and mix well.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Mix.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: brownies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, cocoa, flour and salt. Stir.
Add vanilla.
Bake in a shallow pan in a moderate oven at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool for 3 minutes before cutting into squares.

title: helen's fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs 1 at a time.
Add vanilla; mix dates, candy, nuts and coconut with 1/4 cup flour.
Sift remaining dry ingredients alternately; fold them into cream mixture with buttermilk.
Fold in fruit mixture.
Spoon into well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in a slow 300° oven for about 2 1/2 hours.

title: lasagna
directions: Mix Ricotta and cottage cheese with beaten egg.
Set aside. Brown hamburger and sausage.
Add tomato sauce, sugar, oregano, garlic salt and pepper.
Drain and cook lasagna noodles.

title: stuffed mexican peppers
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Add chips.
Mix together well.
Put mixture in peppers.
Place in casserole bowl.
Put water in bowl.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: ann's pickles
directions: Drain and throw away liquid from pickles in jar.
Then slice the pickles thin.
Mix the pickles, onions (sliced), sugar and vinegar.
Put back in jar and if there is not enough liquid, add water.
Shake well, off and on for several days and keep refrigerated.
The longer they stand, the better they are.

title: pea and rice salad
directions: Peel, seed and chop the tomatoes.
Mix peas and tomatoes together; set aside.
While rice is still hot, add oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Toss lightly.
Add peas and tomatoes, parsley and basil.
Mix together and chill several hours before serving. Serves 6 to 8.

title: spicy cheese wafers(makes about 5 dozen)
directions: Cream together all ingredients except Rice Krispies.
Mixture will be very stiff.
Work in Rice Krispies.
Form balls about 1-inch in diameter and flatten onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: oyster stew(yields 4 servings)
directions: Strain oyster liquor into saucepan, heat but do not boil. Heat milk in double boiler; stir in hot oyster liquor.
Add butter and seasonings and oysters.
When oysters puff and are crinkled at edge, serve at once.

title: two hour rolls
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add boiling water and beat.
Add beaten eggs.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix salt with flour and mix all together. Knead slightly.
Let rise for 1 hour.
Shape into rolls.
Let rise another hour.
Bake at 400° until golden brown, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Both seasonings are made by McCormick.
Mix well.

title: royal velvet chiffon cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add wet ingredients and beat until smooth.
Beat 5 egg whites (2/3 cup) with 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar until egg whites are stiff, but not dry.
Add 1/4 cup sugar gradually; beat to a very stiff meringue.
Do not underbeat. Fold egg yolk mixture carefully into egg whites until completely blended.
Pour into ungreased 9 or 10-inch pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 50 to 60 minutes for 9-inch pan; 40 to 50 minutes for 10-inch pan.
Cool in inverted pan about 1 hour.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick of butter and mix with graham cracker crumbs. Press in pan.
Mix egg whites, 2 sticks of butter and powdered sugar together.
Mix for 20 minutes.
Pour over graham cracker mixture.
Layer bananas and pineapple (drained), then top with Cool Whip.
Put cherries and nuts on top.

title: snicker pie(fat-free or sugar-free)
directions: Soften ice cream in a "large" bowl.
Sprinkle instant pudding out of box over ice cream and mix.
Add peanut butter and Cool Whip.
Stir until well blended.
Spray an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch dish or two 8-inch pie plates with Pam.
Pour mixture into desired dish and freeze.
Cut oblong dish into 16 squares.
Cut pie plate into 8 slices.
Cover and store in freezer.

title: holiday brittle
directions: Melt chocolate in a 2-quart Tupperware bowl (2 minutes on High).
Add peppermint; stir.
Spread on wax paper in a thin layer.
Cool in fridge/freezer.
Then break into pieces.

title: fried yellow squash
directions: Slice squash (as many as you wish).
Sprinkle with salt, sugar and pepper.
Cover both sides of sliced squash with flour.
Fry in hot oil until done.
If they are crisp, they are good too.

title: pat's sweet and sour meatballs(world's best meatballs)
directions: Mix together on low heat; stir until cranberry sauce has dissolved into tomato sauce.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix all of the above ingredients together and place on baking sheets in round balls.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Chop stems very fine; combine with all other ingredients. Fill mushroom caps.
Place filled side up under broiler 3 to 4 minutes, until brown.

title: low-fat hamburgers
directions: Preheat grill or broiler.
In a large bowl, combine meats, bread crumbs, onion, egg white and seasonings.
Form into 4 patties.
Grill over charcoal or broil in oven for approximately 3 minutes on each side or to taste.
Serve on hamburger buns, adding lettuce, tomato and 1/2 teaspoon relish to each burger.

title: pecan pie #3
directions: Cream margarine to soften.
Add sugar gradually and cream until fluffy.
Add syrup and salt.
Beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Stir in pecans. Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 50 minutes or until knife comes out clean. Cool before cutting.

title: broccoli mushroom noodle casserole
directions: Chop broccoli, mushrooms and onion.
Saute in butter until tender.
Salt and pepper lightly and remove from heat.
Beat eggs in large bowl.
Whisk in Ricotta cheese and sour cream.
Boil noodles until slightly underdone, then add some butter.
Remove sauteed vegetables from pan and add to cheese mixture with slotted spoon.
Add noodles and 1/4 cup bread crumbs.
Spread into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with more bread crumbs and Cheddar cheese. Bake, covered, for 30 minutes and, uncovered, for 15 more minutes at 350°.

title: chicken bog
directions: Clean fryer.
Put in 5-quart heavy pan.
Cover with water.
Add bacon grease, bouillon cubes, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil and turn down to medium heat.
Cover and cook until chicken falls from bone.
Remove chicken from broth and cool.
Take chicken off bones. Cut into bite-size pieces.
There should be enough broth to fill half of pot.
(If not, add some warm water.)
Add yellow food coloring for a nice, rich yellow color.
Taste and add more salt and pepper, if needed.
Add chicken and rice.
Cook on medium heat until most of juice has cooked out.
Turn to low heat; cover and cook until rice is done.

title: cashew cauliflower salad
directions: Wash and cut cauliflower into bite size pieces.
Marinate at least two hours in Caesar dressing.
Combine marinated cauliflower with green onions and red pepper.
Sprinkle cashews over top just before serving.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Melt butter and saute onion.
Crumble Tater Tots in baking dish.
Mix soup, sour cream, 1/2 stick butter and 1/2 of the cheese (grated); set aside.
Melt other 1/2 stick margarine and pour over Tater Tots, then pour soup mixture over that.
Spread remaining grated cheese over that.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken until no longer pink and cut up.
Stir all ingredients together and put in pie shell (use deep dish pie pan). Cut slits in top crust. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: jalapeno tortilla rolls
directions: Combine everything but the tortillas.
Spread mixture over tortillas, covering completely to the edges.
Roll jelly roll style, tightly.
Put in a Ziploc bag and refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: half hour meat loaf
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into loaf or square pan.
Bake in oven preheated to 350° or in reflector oven for 20 to 25 minutes (until somewhat crusty).
Can wrap in foil and grill over hot coals for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: chocolate pudding or pie filling
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa and salt together.
Add boiling water to sugar mixture and boil until thick.
Add butter and vanilla after you have removed from heat.
Makes 4 servings of pudding. Serve with cream and sugar or Cool Whip.
This is an old family recipe.

title: tuna pie
directions: Toss together tuna, onions and cheese.
Stir together mayonnaise, eggs and milk.
Mix all ingredients and pour in shell.

title: braised red cabbage
directions: In large saucepot, heat oil over medium heat.
Add red cabbage and cook 5 minutes until wilted, stirring occasionally. Add chicken broth, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce heat to low; cover and cook mixture 20 minutes. Carefully drain off any excess liquid; leave pot off heat.
Add balsamic vinegar and brown sugar to cabbage; toss mixture until braised cabbage is well coated.
Just before serving, stir in toasted pecan halves.
Serve immediately.

title: rosy spring salad
directions: Boil water and pour over jello.
Stir in drained pineapple and orange juice.
Add strawberries.
Chill until jelled.
Top with Cool Whip, if desired.
(Add 1/2 cup sugar if strawberries aren't sweetened.)

title: straw and hay fettuccini
directions: In a small saucepan, melt butter.
Add cream and stir in Parmesan cheese.
Just heat.
Do not allow mixture to come to a boil.
Pour over hot drained pasta seasoned with freshly ground pepper and toss.
Serve with additional Parmesan cheese on the side.
Serves 6.

title: grandma's chocolate sauce
directions: Melt chocolate in a double boiler.
Add sugar, cream, butter, salt and vanilla.
Stir until thickens.
Add baking powder; stir. (Mixture will bubble.)
Keep warm.
Especially good on ice cream!

title: flavored pretzels
directions: Spread pretzels on baking sheet.
Melt margarine and add salad dressing mix (dry).
Stir and pour over pretzels.
Stir thoroughly.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Pour onto waxed paper to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, cheese and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat after each addition.
Stir in flour, salt and vanilla; well.
Pour into greased tube cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: lemon or pistachio lush
directions: Mix and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until brown.
Cool.

title: avocado chip dip
directions: Peel, pit and with fork mash the avocados well or force through sieve.
Add other ingredients.
Chill.
Crumbled bacon makes a great garnish.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain grease off.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste, water, onion, garlic, salt and pepper. Simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook noodles as directed on package and drain.
In a 9 x 13-inch dish, cover bottom with a layer of sauce. Layer with noodles, sauce, cottage cheese, 1/2 of the shredded Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Repeat with another layer of same.
For last layer, add sauce and slices of Mozzarella cheese to cover top.
Insert toothpicks and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn bread pie
directions: Preheat oven according to corn bread instructions. Brown the ground beef; drain. In a 13 x 9-inch pan, layer the ground beef, beans and stewed
tomatoes. Cover with corn bread batter and bake until the corn bread is done. Serve topped with shredded cheese.

title: maine pumpkin cookies with frosting
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening together.
Add eggs; beat well. Add pumpkin, then sifted dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add vanilla, candied fruit and nuts.
Drop by spoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Cool, then frost.
Makes 3 dozen medium size cookies.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Stir in beaten eggs, oil, water and vanilla.
Mix in canned pumpkin, dates and nuts.
Stir until smooth textured.
Pour into four 7 x 3 x 2-inch loaf pans or two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans, greased.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool 10 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix in order given and stir well after each ingredient is added.
Chill before serving.

title: vegetable bean soup
directions: In a 4-quart Dutch oven, combine water, kidney beans, black beans, undrained tomatoes, corn, carrot, onion, bouillon cubes and garlic.
Bring to boiling, reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: lasagna salad
directions: Bring water to boil.
Boil noodles until firm.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Cut into strips.
Place noodles in salad bowl.
Add salad dressing; toss well.
Add salad greens, green onions, salami, cheese strips, croutons and Parmesan cheese.
Toss to coat all ingredients.

title: one hundred dollar brownies
directions: Mix by hand.
Melt over low heat in heavy saucepan margarine and chocolate.
Let cool.
Add sugar, then eggs, one at a time. Mix well.
Finally, add flour, salt and vanilla.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Spray skillet with cooking spray. Mix together oregano, salt, garlic powder, pepper and red pepper. Sprinkle on both sides of chicken breasts. Cook in skillet 8 to 10 minutes until no longer pink. Remove from skillet. Keep warm.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar
and
oil.
Add
eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add
to
mixture, alternating with pumpkin. Add nuts and
vanilla.
Grease
and flour loaf pans.
Makes 3 regular loaves or 12 mini loaves.
Bake large loaves for 45 to 50 minutes. The small loaves take 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cookie pudding
directions: Layer the cookies in an 11 x 7-inch dish.
Mix pudding as directed on package.
Cut up bananas over cookies.
Pour pudding over all.
Let sit in refrigerator until chilled.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: crab-and-mushroom casserole
directions: *I blend small amounts of ground red pepper (hot), nutmeg, onion powder, paprika and garlic powder; add dried parsley flakes to make 1 tablespoon.

title: cranberry-apple crisp
directions: Combine apples and cranberries.
Drizzle with honey.
Cut butter into oats, flour and sugar.
Stir in nuts and vanilla. Place apples and cranberries into greased 11 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Top with oatmeal mix.
Bake at 350° approximately 50 minutes until brown and bubbly.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with milk as directed. Stir in sour cream and 1 container Cool Whip. Mix well. Layer pudding mixture with bananas and wafers, ending with bananas. Top with Cool Whip. Chill well.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in small baking dish. Sprinkle slivered almonds on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: strawberry roll
directions: Grease a 17 x 11 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan with oil and line with waxed paper.
Grease waxed paper with oil; set aside. Prepare cake mix according to package directions; spread batter in prepared pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until firm to touch.
Sift powdered sugar in a 17 x 11 1/2-inch rectangle on a linen towel.
When cake is done, immediately loosen from sides of pan and turn out on powdered sugar.
Peel off waxed paper. Starting at narrow end, roll up cake and towel together.
Cool 20 minutes, seam side down.
Combine sliced strawberries and sugar; set aside.
Beat whipped cream until foamy; gradually add 3 tablespoons powdered sugar, beating until soft peaks form.
Drain strawberries.
Unroll cake and remove towel.
Spread cake with half of whipped cream.
Top with berries; reroll.
Place on serving dish, seam side down; spreading remaining whipped cream on all sides.
Chill before serving.

title: spicy pastrami rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Separate crescent rolls into triangles. Cut triangles in half lengthwise to make 2 small triangles.
Cut pastrami into 1 x 2-inch strips.
Spread 1 teaspoon cream cheese and 1/2 teaspoon mustard on each triangle, leaving about 1/4 inch of the pointed end uncovered.
Stack 3 pieces of pastrami at wide end of the triangle.
Beginning at the wide end, roll up triangle and place on an ungreased baking sheet with point side down.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.
Yield:
32 rolls.

title: hot chocolate mix(yield: 1 gallon)
directions: Sift all ingredients together and store in an airtight container.
To serve, combine 1/2 cup mix to 1/2 cup boiling water.

title: vegetable sandwiches
directions: Take quartered vegetable pieces and grind in a meat or vegetable grinder.
If you don't have a grinder, a food processor set on finely minced setting should do okay.
Pour ground mixture into a colander and drain juice into a separate bowl, keeping 4 tablespoons of vegetable juice.

title: stew made easy
directions: In a large roasting pan, mix all ingredients.
Cook, covered, in 350° oven for 3 hours.
Last 1/2 hour, uncover.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Bake cake per directions and cool.
Cook and stir over medium heat milk, sugar, eggs and butter for about 12 minutes.
Add vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Beat until thick enough to spread.

title: yellow rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Add green onions, olives and water chestnuts.
Mix well.
Add curry powder, salt, dill weed and pepper.
Drain artichokes, reserving marinade.
Cut artichokes into quarters; stir into rice mixture.
Mix reserved artichoke marinade with mayonnaise; toss with rice mixture. Refrigerate overnight to let flavors blend.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: chilies rellenos
directions: Pour oil in electric deep fryer.
Preheat at 425° for 25 minutes.
Meanwhile, drain green chilies and remove seeds.
Cut cheese into strips.
Insert a strip into each chile.
Dredge each in flour and set aside.
Beat egg whites to a soft peak.
Beat together egg yolks, flour and salt until mixture is smooth.
Fold in beaten whites.
Coat each cube with egg mixture.
Drop in hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.
Spoon hot oil over chilies, while frying, to brown tops.
Remove and drain.
Serve on warm platter topped with prepared enchilada sauce.

title: chicken potato salad
directions: Mix well and serve on lettuce.

title: bob's world famous spaghetti
directions: Brown meat with onion, garlic salt and pepper.
Drain. Add Ragu, vinegar, wine and mushrooms.
Bring to a boil.
Mix spaghetti in Dutch oven. Simmer, covered, 1/2 hour.

title: grace's popcorn ball syrup
directions: Cook first 3
ingredients
until you get a hard ball in cold water.
Add
vinegar
and
butter.	Pour
over
popcorn. Careful, mixture will
be
hot.
Take a handful of popcorn and roll into a ball.
If hands get too sticky, put some butter on them.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook frozen veggies according to package; drain. Mix veggies, cheese, mayonnaise, onion and celery together in casserole dish. Crush Ritz crackers. Melt margarine. Mix crackers and margarine. Sprinkle on top of vegetable mixture. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until bubbly.

title: coconut balls
directions: Mix ingredients together; form into small balls and dip in chocolate. Use a toothpick to hold ball while dipping. Use chocolate syrup as dip.

title: german chocolate dream cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.
While cake is warm, poke holes down through cake with round handle of wooden spoon at 1-inch intervals.
Pour Eagle brand milk over cake followed by caramel topping.
Refrigerate until cool and top with topping. Refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: my favorite pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add and mix well the pumpkin, egg and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and allspice.
Stir in nuts and/or raisins, if desired.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together; beat at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured two (8 or 9-inch) cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost with chocolate or cream cheese frosting.

title: taco(children)
directions: Heat taco shells at 300° in oven on a cookie sheet until ready to serve.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix chicken pieces, soup and chicken broth.
Add chopped celery, boiled eggs, peas, onion and carrots.
Mix melted margarine, flour and milk and pour over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: oven stew
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer meat, potatoes and vegetables. Pour soup over all.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours.

title: charlotte peter's marinari spaghetti sauce
directions: Soak mushrooms in just enough water to cover.
Saute onion and pepper in oil until soft.
Stir in rest of ingredients including mushrooms and water.
Cook over low heat about 30 minutes.
Pour over cooked spaghetti; top with Parmesan cheese.
(Marinari means meatless.)

title: whoopie pies
directions: Stir dry ingredients together. Add the rest and mix well. Drop on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: microwave shrimp in garlic butter
directions: Place margarine in custard cup.
Microwave on High for 30 to 45 minutes until melted.
Stir in garlic powder and parsley flakes. Separate shrimp.
Place in 9 or 10-inch diameter dish.
Pour butter mixture evenly over shrimp.
Cover tightly.
Microwave 5 to 8 minutes until shrimp are opaque, stirring every 2 minutes.
Let stand, covered, 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Mix softened cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in condensed milk, then beat in peanut butter until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Fold in cream or Cool Whip.
Turn into 9 or 10-inch prepared crust or make your own with icebox chocolate cookies and butter.
Freeze 4 hours or until firm.

title: holiday pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs.
Add butter, sugar, vinegar, vanilla, coconut, pecans and raisins.
Pour into shell.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: delicious farina dumplings(for soup)
directions: Heat milk to boiling point.
Add farina, butter, salt, paprika and nutmeg, if desired, and simmer until thick, stirring frequently.
Remove batter from the heat and beat eggs vigorously one at a time.
The heat of the mixture will thicken eggs.
Drop batter by generous teaspoonfuls at a time into simmering soup stock.
Cook, covered, for about 2 minutes and serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lemon cream chicken
directions: In a large, resealable plastic bag, combine 1/2 cup flour, salt and pepper. Add chicken and shake to coat.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Mix sherbet, apple juice and ginger ale.
Has pretty foam on top.
Makes one punch bowl.

title: sausage egg
directions: Mix egg with sausage meat, water and seasoning.
Pour into skillet with small amount of oil or butter.
Over medium or hot heat, cook as an omelet.
Turn once until edges are brown.
Serve with slices of tomato.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs until foamy; beat in flour, sugar and brown sugar until well blended.
Blend in melted margarine.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: black bean soup
directions: Combine beans, water, oregano, salt, bay leaf, minced garlic and pepper.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat to medium high and continue cooking until beans are tender and almost done.
Stir and add water as needed.
Saute celery and onion in olive oil.
Grate potatoes and carrots.

title: chocolate pound cake(sinful and delicious)
directions: Stir chocolate in 1/4 cup water over low heat until melted. Set aside to cool.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, creaming well after each.
Add melted chocolate.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture until well blended.
Add extracts.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool well on wire rack and frost with Chocolate Butter Frosting.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water and cornstarch together until clear; then add 1/2 package strawberry jello.
Cool; then pour in pie crust. When ready to serve, top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: chocolate carrot cake
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and oil.
Add dry ingredients, then carrots and nuts, mixing well.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Frost when cool.

title: kayleigh's herb dinner rolls
directions: Cook rolls according to package directions. Two minutes before they're done baking, remove from oven; spray tops with butter, then sprinkle with seasoning. Return to oven to finish baking. Serve warm.

title: date and nut bars
directions: Mix the baking powder, salt and flour.
Mix dates and nuts through the flour with fingertips.
Beat eggs until light.
Beat in sugar gradually.
Stir in dry ingredients, nuts and dates. Spread mixture evenly over pan lined with paper or well-greased and dusted with flour.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until the surface will spring back when pressed lightly with one finger. Cut in strips 1 x 4-inches.
Will make 18 bars.
Per bar there are 100 calories.

title: curried pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place the pecans on a baking sheet and toast in the oven for about 10 minutes.
Do not allow the pecans to brown.
Remove the nuts from the oven but leave the oven turned on.
Melt the butter and oil in a large skillet.
Add the brown sugar, salt, curry and ginger.
Blend well.
Add the pecans and stir with a wooden spoon until well coated.
Add the chutney and mix well.
Place the pecan mixture on paper towels on the baking sheet and place in the oven.
Turn the heat off.
Let the pecans dry in the oven about 10 minutes.
Remove from the oven, salt lightly and let cool completely.
Store in an airtight container.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Combine 1 1/3 cups of water, broth and soy sauce in saucepan. Bring to a boil.

title: velveeta salsa dip
directions: Mix together.
Heat in microwave 5 minutes.
Use as potato chip dip.

title: hot cheese hominy
directions: Fry onion in butter until tender.
Add to the hominy, chillies, sour cream, chili powder, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup of cheese.
Bake in a 9 x 12-inch pan at 400° for 20 minutes.
Then add the 1 cup of cheese to top.
Let bake 5 more minutes.

title: pepper relish(from southern living magazine)
directions: Cut the first 4 ingredients into strips.
Pour boiling water over all and let sit for 5 minutes; drain.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over drained peppers.
Bring to a boil for 5 minutes; stir occasionally.
Chill; serve over grilled or fried seafood.
Excellent with shrimp scampi and pilaf.

title: custard pie
directions: Thoroughly mix eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Slowly stir in hot milk.
Pour at once into pie shell.
Dash with nutmeg.
Bake in hot oven at 475° for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to 450°.
Bake 10 minutes longer or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool on rack.

title: cheddary scalloped potatoes
directions: In skillet over medium heat in hot margarine, cook onion until tender.
Stir in soup, milk and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Add potatoes.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes or until hot and bubbling, stirring occasionally.
Preparation time: 25 minutes.
Cooking time:
10 minutes.

title: sesame noodles
directions: Process garlic until minced.
Add tahini, tea, soy sauce, chili oil, 2 tablespoons sesame oil, sugar and vinegar; process until smooth.

title: spaghetti noodle dish
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Mix together the tomato paste, tomato soup, mushrooms, onion salt, garlic salt and pepper.
Mix sour cream and cream cheese until smooth.
In a greased 13 1/2 x 4 x 2 1/2-inch baking dish, place noodles (cooked).
Cover with cheese mixture, then meat sauce.
Sprinkle grated cheese over all.
Bake at 350° until mixture bubbles.
Let set for 15 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: citrus cheesecake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff in small mixer bowl.
Cream butter, sugar, yolks and cheese.
Add herbs, rinds and almonds.

title: orange jello mold
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add cold water to this to measure 1 cup.
Stir boiling water into jello in large bowl until dissolved.
Stir in pineapple juice liquid.
Refrigerate this mixture about 1 1/4 hours.
After this, stir in Cool Whip with wire whisk until smooth.
Refrigerate 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir in pineapple, oranges and marshmallows.
Spoon into 6 cup jello mold. Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm.
To unmold:
Dip mold in hot water and invert on plate.

title: crispy herbed chicken (or fish)(baked, not fried)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine dry ingredients. Dip chicken into milk.
Coat with cornmeal mixture.
Place in pan; brush with margarine. Bake 40 to 45 minutes (less for boneless) or until golden brown and tender.
Makes 5 servings.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: In a greased casserole layer the chilies.
Add Jack cheese, shredded, as second layer.
Mix flour, salt, eggs, milk together until smooth.
Pour over chilies and cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 55 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla. Blend well. Sift flour and 3 spices together. Add to butter mixture. Add nuts.
Mix the applesauce and soda together.
Add last.
Mix well. Keep batter refrigerated and bake as needed. Bake in muffin cups at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: mad dog punch
directions: Mix together the wine and punch; add 1 1/2 liters of ginger ale and taste.
Keep adding ginger ale to taste.
(Watch it; it will knock your socks off.)

title: surprise rhubarb pie
directions: Heat rhubarb and sugar to a boil (add 1/2 cup water if fruit is not juicy).
Add jello and marshmallows; stir until dissolved. Cool.
Add the whipped topping and extract.
Stir well; pour into prepared crust.
Allow to set several hours.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice apples into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with oatmeal, brown sugar, margarine and flour that has been mixed together until it is crumbly.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° until apples are tender.
Uncover and finish baking until apples are done.
Serve with cream or ice cream.
It is better served warm.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Mix together and chill before serving.

title: salmon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 410°.
Get crust from refrigerator to warm up. Remove bones and skin from salmon meat.
Puree with fork.
Mix in eggs, cream, a lot of pepper and salt.
Gently add cubed pineapple and cream cheese, cut in cubes.
Cover 8 1/2-inch form with crust. Make sure there are no leaks.
Pour in salmon mass.
Bake golden brown and dry in 45 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix soups, milk and rice together and spread in the bottom of an oblong pan.
Place the chicken breasts on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: mayfair dressing
directions: This must be done in a blender or food processor.
Peel garlic and cut in half.
Scrape and slice celery.
Peel onion and cut into chunks.
Add these with anchovies, mustard, lemon juice, and everything except eggs and oil into machine and process for 5 seconds.
Add eggs and blend again for a few seconds.
Add oil a tablespoon at a time until 1/2 cup has been added.
Then add a quarter cup at a time, blending well between each addition and for a few seconds after all oil has been added.
Serve over romaine with fresh croutons.

title: unbaked brownies
directions: Measure peanut butter, pecans and oats and set aside.
Mix the first 7 ingredients together in a large heavy pan.
Bring to a boil and boil for 2 minutes, stirring.
Turn heat off but leave pan on burner.
Quickly add peanut butter and pecans; mix together. Quickly add oats and mix.

title: ritzy dessert(quick and easy)
directions: Crush crackers and mix with oleo.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan, reserving a few for the top.
Take 2 packages instant coconut cream pudding and milk; beat 2 minutes and add ice cream and spread on crunch crust.
Sprinkle on reserved cracker crumbs. Refrigerate.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Place skinless chicken breasts in bottom of 9 x 12-inch glass baking dish.
Top with desired amount of fresh-cut broccoli. Cover with undiluted soup, then cover completely with bread crumbs.
Bake 1 hour at 350° to 375°.

title: german coffee cake
directions: Beat sugar and eggs, then add dry ingredients.
Add sour cream.
Grease tube pan.
Put 1/2 of mix in pan.
Mix together sugar, cinnamon, chocolate chips and walnuts.
Sprinkle 1/2 over cake mix.
Put rest of mix over dry ingredients.
Sprinkle the rest of dry ingredients over cake.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
